Name: kLowerPAMemoryLimitForNonMainRenderers
Documentation:
Configures whether we set a lower limit for renderers that do not have a main
frame, similar to the limit that is already done for backgrounded renderers.

Name: kShowSuggestionsOnAutofocus
Documentation:
Allows to show suggestions automatically when password forms are autofocused
on pageload.

Name: kRestrictAbusePortsOnLocalhost
Documentation: Finch-controlled list of ports that should be blocked on localhost.

Name: kIdleDetection
Documentation:
This is intended as a kill switch for the Idle Detection feature. To enable
this feature, the experimental web platform features flag should be set,
or the site should obtain an Origin Trial token.

Name: kSkiaGraphitePrecompilation
Documentation:
Enable Skia Graphite's Pipeline precompilation feature.
Note: This is only meaningful when Skia Graphite is enabled but can then also
be overridden by
--enable-skia-graphite-precompilation and
--disable-skia-graphite-precompilation.

Name: kAvoidResourceRequestCopies
Documentation: Avoids copying ResourceRequest when possible.

Name: kWebViewSurfaceControl
Documentation: Hardware Overlays for WebView.

Name: kAutofillAddressFieldSwapping
Documentation:
When enabled, focusing on an autofilled field that was traditionally filled
with address data (meaning filled with the value of their classified type)
will yield field-by-field filling suggestions without prefix matching.
TODO(crbug.com/339543182): Remove when launched.

Name: kWebrtcMediaCapabilitiesParameters
Documentation:
Used to set a few tunable parameters for the WebRTC Media Capabilities
implementation.

Name: kAutofillEnableAddressFieldParserNG
Documentation:
Enables a new implementation for address field parsing that is based on
backtracking.

Name: kClientHintsXRFormFactor
Documentation: Enable `form-factor` client hint for XR devices.

Name: kOverlayFullscreenVideo
Documentation: Only used for disabling overlay fullscreen (aka SurfaceView) in Clank.

Name: kUseThreadPoolForMediaStreamVideoTaskRunner
Documentation:
Causes MediaStreamVideoSource video frames to be transported on a
SequencedTaskRunner backed by the threadpool instead of the normal IO thread.

Name: kAvoidH2Reprioritization
Documentation: Disable H2 reprioritization, in order to measure its impact.

Name: kFrequencyCappingForOverlayPopupDetection
Documentation:
Enables the frequency capping for detecting overlay popups. Overlay-popups
are the interstitials that pop up and block the main content of the page.

Name: kShowHudDisplayForPausedPages
Documentation: Whether the HUD display is shown for paused pages.

Name: kDelaySuggestionsOnAutofocusWaitingForPasskeys
Documentation:
Only relevant when `kShowSuggestionsOnAutofocus` is on. This prevents
suggestions from being shown while waiting for passkeys to become available,
if the popup was triggered by autofocus without user interaction. It is
enabled by default and can be turned off if it is found to cause any
problems.

Name: kRemotePageMetadata
Documentation: Enables fetching page metadata from the remote Optimization Guide service.

Name: kSharedStorageSelectURLSavedQueries
Documentation: For the Shared Storage API, allows saved queries in `selectURL()`.

Name: kInputStreamOptimizations
Documentation: Enables optimizations to input stream handling.

Name: kInterestGroupStorage
Documentation: Backend storage + kill switch for Interest Group API origin trials.

Name: kEncryptedReportingFeature
Documentation:
Feature to enable/disable encryption.
By default encryption is enabled and supported by server.
Disabled only for testing/stress purposes.

Name: kDrawCutoutEdgeToEdge
Documentation: Enable drawing under System Bars within DisplayCutout.

Name: kHttpsUpgrades
Documentation: Enables automatically upgrading main frame navigations to HTTPS.

Name: kDCompDebugVisualization
Documentation:
Enable DComp debug visualizations. This can be useful to determine how much
work DWM is doing when we update our tree.

Please be aware that some of these visualizations result in quickly flashing
colors.

Name: kContextMenuCopyVideoFrame
Documentation: Enables the "Copy Video Frame" context menu item.

Name: kTPCDAdHeuristicSubframeRequestTagging
Documentation:
Enables ad tagging decisions to be propagated to network requests by removing
an optimization which parallelizes filter list checks and navigation request
start.

Name: kIntegrityPolicyScript
Documentation:
Enables support for the `Integrity-Policy` header with script destinations,
which enables developers to ensure all their external scripts have their
integrity enforced.

Name: kFileSystemAccessDirectoryIterationBlocklistCheck
Documentation: Alphabetical:

Name: kSafetyCheckUnusedSitePermissionsForSupportedChooserPermissions
Documentation:
When enabled, allowlisted website settings are considered for Safety Check,
in addition to content settings that are included by default.

Name: kThrottleInstallingServiceWorker
Documentation:
Enable throttling of fetch() requests from service workers in the
installing state.  The limit of 3 was chosen to match the limit
in background main frames.  In addition, trials showed that this
did not cause excessive timeouts and resulted in a net improvement
in successful install rate on some platforms.

Name: kPrivacySandboxNoticeActionDebouncingAndroid
Documentation: If true, enables debouncing for button clicks on all Android notices.

Name: kAutofillEnableGermanTransliteration
Documentation:
Control if Autofill supports German transliteration.
TODO(crbug.com/328968064): Remove when/if launched.

Name: kServiceWorkerBypassFetchHandlerHashStrings
Documentation:
The set of ServiceWorker to bypass while making navigation request.
They are represented by a comma separated list of HEX encoded SHA256 hash of
the ServiceWorker's scripts.
e.g.
9685C8DE399237BDA6FF3AD0F281E9D522D46BB0ECFACE05E98D2B9AAE51D1EF,
20F0D78B280E40C0A17ABB568ACF4BDAFFB9649ADA75B0675F962B3F4FC78EA4

Name: kUseFusedLocationProvider
Documentation: Use FusedLocationProvider on Android to fetch device location.

Name: kExemptUrlFromNetworkRevocationForTesting
Documentation:
Controls access to an API to exempt certain URLs from fenced frame
network revocation to facilitate testing.

Name: kWebAssemblyInliningCallIndirect
Documentation:
Feature for WebAssembly speculative inlining of indirect calls (see
https://crbug.com/335082212; and https://crbug.com/40898108 for direct call
and call_ref inlining, which has already launched above). Not user visible.

Name: kPartitionAllocFewerMemoryRegions
Documentation:
Whether to make PartitionAlloc use fewer memory regions. This matters on
Linux-based systems, where there is a per-process limit that we hit in some
cases. See the comment in PartitionBucket::SlotSpanCOmmitedSize() for detail.

Name: kTpcdHeuristicsGrants
Documentation:
Enables writing and reading temporary storage access grants from 3PCD
heuristics.

Name: kProactivelyThrottleLowPriorityRequests
Documentation:
When kProactivelyThrottleLowPriorityRequests is enabled,
resource scheduler proactively throttles low priority requests to avoid
network contention with high priority requests that may arrive soon.

Name: kNativeUnpartitionedStoragePermittedWhen3PCOff
Documentation: Forces unpartitioned storage access with third-party cookie blocking.

Name: kWebUITabStrip
Documentation:
Enables a web-based tab strip. See https://crbug.com/989131. Note this
feature only works when the ENABLE_WEBUI_TAB_STRIP buildflag is enabled.

Name: kUpdateRequestForCorsRedirect
Documentation:
Updates the request body, headers, and referrer policy for CORS
redirects, following 4.4. HTTP-redirect fetch:
https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#http-redirect-fetch

Name: kFedCmMetricsEndpoint
Documentation: Enables usage of the FedCM API with metrics endpoint at the same time.

Name: kUrgentPageDiscarding
Documentation: Whether tabs are discarded under high memory pressure.

Name: kWebAssemblyDynamicTiering
Documentation: Enable WebAssembly dynamic tiering (only tier up hot functions).

Name: kEarlyEstablishGpuChannel
Documentation: Enable establishing the GPU channel early in renderer startup.

Name: kEnterpriseActiveUserDetection
Documentation:
Controls whether enterprise features will attempt to attach the active
content area user email to DLP/reporting requests on Workspace sites.

Name: kAutofillIncludeMaxLengthInCrowdsourcing
Documentation:
If enabled, we include a `FormFieldData`'s maxlength in crowdsourcing votes.
TODO(crbug.com/393995180): Clean up in M137.

Name: kIdentifiabilityStudyMetaExperiment
Documentation:
Feature for the Identifiability Study Meta experiment.

If the feature is enabled, the meta experiment is activated on a random set
of clients according to the selection probability.

Name: kRevokeMediaSourceObjectURLOnAttach
Documentation:
Approach original pre-REC MSE object URL autorevoking behavior, though await
actual attempt to use the object URL for attachment to perform revocation.
This will hopefully reduce runtime memory bloat for pages that do not
explicitly detach their HTMLME+MSE object collections nor explicitly revoke
the object URLs used to attach HTMLME+MSE. When disabled, revocation only
occurs when application explicitly revokes the object URL, or upon the
execution context teardown for the MediaSource object. When enabled,
revocation occurs upon successful start of attachment of HTMLME to the object
URL. Note, rather than immediately scheduling a task to revoke upon the URL's
creation, as at least one other browser does and the original File API
pattern used to follow, this delay until attachment start enables new
scenarios that could use the object URL for attaching HTMLME+MSE cross-thread
(MSE-in-workers), where there could be significant delay between the worker
thread creation of the object URL and the main thread usage of the object URL
for starting attachment to HTMLME.

Name: kExperimentalFlingAnimation
Documentation:
Enables the use of a touch fling curve that is based on the behavior of
native apps on Windows.

Name: kUseMapRectForPixelMovement
Documentation: Kill switch for using MapRect() to compute filter pixel movement.

Name: kCanvasHibernationSnapshotZstd
Documentation:
Use ZSTD to compress the snapshot. This is faster to decompress, and much
faster to compress. ZSTD may not be available on all platforms, so this
feature will be a no-op on those.

Name: kPageActionsMigration
Documentation:
Controls whether the new page actions framework should be displaying page
actions.

Name: kHistoryOptInEducationalTip
Documentation: Enables a history sync educational tip in the magic stack on NTP.

Name: kEnabledStructuredMetricsService
Documentation:
Controls whether the structured metrics service is recorder instead of the
provider.

Name: kLensOverlayOmniboxEntryPoint
Documentation: Enables the Lens Overlay omnibox entry point.

Name: kEvictionThrottlesDraw
Documentation:
When enabled, we will not schedule drawing for viz::Surfaces that have been
evicted. Instead waiting for an ActiveTree that is defining a newer
viz::Surface.

Name: kSyncEnableBookmarksInTransportMode
Documentation:
This gates the new single-model approach where account bookmarks are stored
in separate permanent folders in BookmarkModel. The flag controls whether
BOOKMARKS datatype is enabled in the transport mode.
TODO(crbug.com/40943550): Remove this.

Name: kWebAuthnICloudKeychainForInactiveWithDrive
Documentation: Enabled in M118. Remove in or after M121.

Name: kVSyncEncoding
Documentation: Feature flag for driving encoding with the Metronome by VSyncs.

Name: kRendererSideContentDecoding
Documentation:
Enables content decoding in the renderer process.
See https://crbug.com/391950057 and this doc for more details.
https://docs.google.com/document/d/1LwgPlrtQtUhGz_ilTsRun-7o4TuHo9jbXll6FRq-dKk/edit?usp=sharing

Name: kPartitionAllocStraightenLargerSlotSpanFreeLists
Documentation:
Whether to straighten free lists for larger slot spans in PurgeMemory() ->
... -> PartitionPurgeSlotSpan().

Name: kAutofillServerCommunication
Documentation:
Enables or Disables (mostly for hermetic testing) autofill server
communication. The URL of the autofill server can further be controlled via
the autofill-server-url param. The given URL should specify the complete
autofill server API url up to the parent "directory" of the "query" and
"upload" resources.
i.e., https://other.autofill.server:port/tbproxy/af/

Name: kFledgeQueryKAnonymity
Documentation:
Turning on kFledgeQueryKAnonymity loads k-anonymity status at interest group
join and update time. kFledgeQueryKAnonymity is enabled by default. It may
be reasonable to disable kFledgeQueryKAnonymity on clients on which
k-anonymity is not enforced (see related features kFledgeConsiderKAnonymity
and kFledgeEnforceKAnonymity in third_party/blink/public/common/features.h),
as k-anonymity status isn't used in those auctions.

Name: kFledgeEnableWALForInterestGroupStorage
Documentation: Enable write ahead logging for interest group storage.

Name: kProcessPerSiteSkipEnterpriseUsers
Documentation:
The default behavior to opt enterprise users out of
kProcessPerSiteUpToMainFrameThreshold.

Name: kBluetoothFlossTelephony
Documentation: Enables/disables the bluetooth telephony feature for floss

Name: kBackForwardCacheEntryTimeout
Documentation:
Set a time limit for the page to enter the cache. Disabling this prevents
flakes during testing.

Name: kOptimizationGuideOnDeviceModel
Documentation: Whether to use the on device model service in optimization guide.

Name: kFeedImageMemoryCacheSizePercentage
Documentation:
Feature that allows tuning the size of the image memory cache. Value is a
percentage of the maximum size calculated for the device.

Name: kNtpMostRelevantTabResumptionAllowFaviconServerFallback
Documentation:
If enabled, the Tab Resumption module will be allowed to fallback to the
favicon server when fetching favicons for displayed continuation suggestions.

Name: kGoogleStandardDeviceBoundSessionCredentials
Documentation:
Communicated to the server to determine DBSC on google.com. This
allows us to slice metrics by google.com DBSC state without any
Google-specific code in the net stack.

Name: kOverlayScrollbar
Documentation:
Enables or disables overlay scrollbars in Blink (i.e. web content) on Aura
or Linux.  The status of native UI overlay scrollbars is determined in
PlatformStyle::CreateScrollBar. Does nothing on Mac.

Name: kAlpsClientHintParsing
Documentation: Whether ALPS parsing is on for client hint parsing specifically.

Name: kTreatUnsafeDownloadsAsActive
Documentation:
Disable downloads of unsafe file types over insecure transports if initiated
from a secure page. As of M89, mixed downloads are blocked on all platforms.

Name: kDrawQuadSplitLimit
Documentation:
If enabled, overrides the maximum number (exclusive) of quads one draw quad
can be split into during occlusion culling.

Name: kInMemoryCodeCache
Documentation: A feature flag for the memory-backed code cache.

Name: kLowPriorityAsyncScriptExecution
Documentation:
If enabled, async scripts will be run on a lower priority task queue.
See https://crbug.com/1348467.

Name: kV8MinorMS
Documentation: Enables MinorMC young generation garbage collector.

Name: kCodeCacheDeletionWithoutFilter
Documentation: When enabled, code cache does not use a browsing_data filter for deletions.

Name: kPrefetchSchedulerTesting
Documentation: Controls params for tests of `PrefetchScheduler`.

Name: kVaapiOnNvidiaGPUs
Documentation:
NVIDIA VA-API drivers do not support Chromium and can sometimes cause
crashes, disable VA-API on NVIDIA GPUs by default. See crbug.com/1492880.

Name: kInternalBeginFrameSourceOnManyDidNotProduceFrame
Documentation:
When enabled, internal begin frame source will be used in cc to reduce IPC
between cc and viz when there were many "did not produce frame" recently,
and SetAutoNeedsBeginFrame will be called on CompositorFrameSink.

Name: kSavePasswordHashFromProfilePicker
Documentation: Enables saving gaia password hash from the Profile Picker sign-in flow.

Name: kFencedFramesSrcPermissionsPolicy
Documentation:
Enables a bug fix that allows a 'src' allowlist in the |allow| parameter of a
<fencedframe> or <iframe> loaded with a FencedFrameConfig to behave as
expected. See: https://crbug.com/349080952

Name: kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsDeprecationTrial
Documentation:
Enables use of the PrivateNetworkAccessNonSecureContextsAllowed deprecation
trial. This is a necessary yet insufficient condition: documents that wish to
make use of the trial must additionally serve a valid origin trial token.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformOptimizationTargetSegmentationDummy
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling OptimizationTargetSegmentationDummy segment.

Name: kActUserBypassUx
Documentation: Enables displaying ACT features in User Bypass.

Name: kDisplayWildcardInContentSettings
Documentation: Enables wildcard display on the Clank content settings UI.

Name: kPrerender2NewLimitAndScheduler
Documentation:
This was used for enabling a new limit and scheduler for prerender triggers
(crbug.com/40275452). Now the new implementation is used by default and this
flag is just for injecting parameters through field trials.

Name: kTopicsConsentDesktopModalFeature
Documentation: Topics Consent Modal Features

Name: kV8ExternalMemoryAccountedInGlobalLimit
Documentation:
Enable accounting for external memory limits as part of global limits in v8
Heap.

Name: kMediaCastOverlayButton
Documentation: Display the Cast overlay button on the media controls.

Name: kWebIdentityDigitalCredentials
Documentation: Enables the Digital Credential API.

Name: kShareThisTabInsteadButtonGetDisplayMedia
Documentation:
Controls whether a "Share this tab instead" button should be shown for
getDisplayMedia captures. Note: This flag does not control if the "Share this
tab instead" button is shown for chrome.desktopCapture captures.

Name: kSyncPasswordCleanUpAccidentalBatchDeletions
Documentation: Flag to enable clean up of password deletions that may be unintentional.

Name: kVaapiLowPowerEncoderGen9x
Documentation: Enable VA-API hardware low power encoder for all codecs on intel Gen9x gpu.

Name: kSafetyHubDisruptiveNotificationRevocation
Documentation: Automatically revoke disruptive notifications in Safety Hub.

Name: kRenderDocument
Documentation: Enable using the RenderDocument.

Name: kDisableBlackholeOnNoNewNetwork
Documentation:
Enables whether blackhole detector should be disabled during connection
migration and there is no available network.

Name: kFeedShowSignInCommand
Documentation: When enabled, allow show sign in command to request a user signs in / syncs.

Name: kCompressionDictionaryTransportOverHttp1
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, Chromium can use stored shared dictionaries
even when the connection is using HTTP/1 for non-localhost requests.

Name: kFocusFollowsCursor
Documentation: Enables focus follow follow cursor (sloppyfocus).

Name: kUserBypassUI
Documentation: Feature to enable the User Bypass UI.

Name: kUseUtf8EncodingForSvgImage
Documentation: Use the UTF-8 encoding for SVG images instead of UTF-16.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformAndroidHomeModuleRankerV2
Documentation:
Feature flag for enabling on-demand service for ranking android
home modules.

Name: kDeferredSyncStartupCustomDelay
Documentation:
Customizes the delay of a deferred sync startup.
Note from 04/2024: The first attempt to roll this out on 05/2023 ran into
performance regressions (go/deferred-startup-experiment-metrics, sorry
Googlers only). It might still be possible to launch by investigating and
fixing the performance issues. crbug.com/40872516 tracks that.

Name: kZeroCopyRBPPartialRasterWithGpuCompositor
Documentation:
Enables partial raster in ZeroCopyRasterBufferProvider when used with the GPU
compositor.

Name: kBoardingPassDetector
Documentation: Enable boarding pass detector on Chrome Android.

Name: kOptimizationGuidePersonalizedFetching
Documentation: Enables fetching personalized metadata from Optimization Guide Service.

Name: kPrefetchUseContentRefactor
Documentation:
This feature was used to launch the prefetch migration from embedder layer to
content/, and this work has finished and the old implemnetation was deleted.
Now this flag is just for injecting parameters through field trials as an
umberella feature.

Name: kAsyncCheck
Documentation: Note: this feature is a no-op on non-Android platforms.

Name: kFedCmSameSiteLax
Documentation:
Enables sending SameSite=Lax cookies in credentialed FedCM requests
(accounts endpoint, ID assertion endpoint and disconnect endpoint).

Name: kAndroidFallbackToNextSlot
Documentation:
Fallback to next named service slot if launching a privileged service process
hangs. In practice, this means if GPU launch hanges, then retry it once.

Name: kWebApkBackupAndRestoreBackend
Documentation: If enabled, WebAPK data will be synced for Backup&Restore purposes.

Name: kCanvas2DImageChromium
Documentation:
If Canvas2D Image Chromium is allowed, this feature controls whether it is
enabled.

Name: kProgrammaticScrollAnimationOverride
Documentation:
When enabled, the default programmatic scroll animation curve can be
overridden with extra params.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformModelInitializationDelay
Documentation: Feature flag for intoroducing delay while initializing models at startup.

Name: kExternalExperimentAllowlist
Documentation:
Used to deliver the allowlist via a feature param. If disabled, the
allowlist is treated as empty (nothing allowed).

Name: kSiteEngagement
Documentation: Enable site engagement

Name: kSegmentationPlatformTimeDelaySampling
Documentation: Feature flag for controlling sampling of training data collection.

Name: kFedCmButtonMode
Documentation:
Enables usage of the FedCM ButtonMode feature.
Note that actual exposure of the API to web content is controlled by
the flag in RuntimeEnabledFeatures on the blink side. See also the use
of kSetOnlyIfOverridden in content/child/runtime_features.cc. We enable
it here by default to support use in origin trials.

Name: kEvictOnAXEvents
Documentation: Feature to evict when accessibility events occur while in back/forward cache.

Name: kNtpLogo
Documentation:
If enabled, logo will be shown.
This is a kill switch. Keep indefinitely.

Name: kReduceAcceptLanguageHTTP
Documentation:
Enables support for the `Variants` response header and reduce
Accept-Language HTTP header only.

Name: kWebRTCLogUploadSuffix
Documentation:
Changes the crash product under which text and event logs are uploaded
to have a "_webrtc" suffix, and removes the "-webrtc" suffix from the
crash version field.
eg, when enabled: product: "Chrome_Mac_webrtc", version: "121.0.6151.0"
when disabled: product: "Chrome_Mac", version: "121.0.6151.0-webrtc"

Name: kUseParallelRequestsForQUIC
Documentation: Whether parallel download is used for QUIC connections.

Name: kEnableCustomInputStreamBufferSize
Documentation:
Experiment to control the size of the intermediate buffer used to copy from
Java's InputStream into C++'s net::IOBuffer.

Name: kRawDraw
Documentation: Enables Raw Draw.

Name: kOptimizationGuideMetadataValidation
Documentation: Enables the validation of optimization guide metadata.

Name: kAvifGainmapHdrImages
Documentation:
Switch to enabling rendering of gainmap-based AVIF HDR images.
Tracker: https://crbug.com/1451889

Name: kForceSupervisedSigninWithCapabilities
Documentation:
Migrate usages of USM flag to force child account sign-in to use the account
capability `IsSubjectToParentalControls`.

Name: kReportApplicationLanguageInSearchRequest
Documentation: If enabled, hl= is reported in search requests (applicable to iOS only).

Name: kPreferCompositingToLCDText
Documentation:
Whether we should composite a PLSA (paint layer scrollable area) even if it
means losing lcd text.

Name: kV8MegaDomIC
Documentation: Enables faster DOM methods for megamorphic ICs

Name: kNoStatePrefetchHoldback
Documentation: Feature which holdbacks NoStatePrefetch on all surfaces.

Name: kCompressParkableStrings
Documentation:
Disabling this will cause parkable strings to never be compressed.
This is useful for headless mode + virtual time. Since virtual time advances
quickly, strings may be parked too eagerly in that mode.

Name: kGPUDriverBugListTestGroup
Documentation:
This feature allows enabling specific entries in gpu_driver_bug_list.json,
via experimentation. The entries must have test_group property and
test_group feature parameter should be set in the experiment for the entries
that need to be enabled.

Name: kExperimentalAIIPHPromoRampUp
Documentation:
Feature for controlling the users who are eligible to see the IPH promo for
experimental AI.

Name: kAutofillFixValueSemantics
Documentation:
Fixes the overloaded meaning of FormFieldData::value (current value of a
field and initial value of a field): if enabled, AutofillField::value() takes
into accounts its ValueSemantics parameter.
TODO: crbug.com/40227496 - Clean up when launched.

Name: kFledgeBiddingAndAuctionServer
Documentation:
See
https://github.com/WICG/turtledove/blob/main/FLEDGE_browser_bidding_and_auction_API.md

Name: kAndroidWindowOcclusion
Documentation: Enables using occlusion information from Android to save CPU and memory.

Name: kTreeAnimationsInViz
Documentation: Enables Viz service-side layer tree animations for content rendering.

Name: kCanvas2DReclaimUnusedResources
Documentation:
When enabled, unused resources (ready to be recycled) are reclaimed after a
delay.

Name: kSpareRendererProcessPriority
Documentation:
When enabled, sends the spare renderer information when setting the
priority of renderers. Currently only Android handles the spare renderer
information in priority.
The target priority of a spare renderer in Android is decided by the feature
parameters in ContentFeatureList.java.

Name: kAudioWorkletThreadRealtimePriority
Documentation:
A server-side switch for the kRealtimeAudio thread type of
RealtimeAudioWorkletThread object. This can be controlled by a field trial,
it will use the kNormal type thread when disabled.

Name: kOnDeviceClusteringKeywordFiltering
Documentation: Specifies how keywords get filtered and added to a cluster.

Name: kAutofillEnableSupportForHomeAndWork
Documentation:
When enabled, chrome will support home and work addresses from account.
TODO: crbug.com/397940269 - Clean up when launched.

Name: kLiveCaptionAutomaticLanguageDownload
Documentation: Enable automatic downloading of speech recognition language packs.

Name: kCorrectFloatExtensionTestForWebGL
Documentation:
Enable the correction testing for float extension for webgl version 1.
This is simply a killswitch in case we need to restore original behavior.

Name: kAnnouncementNotification
Documentation: Whether to enable announcement notification system.

Name: kExpandCompositedCullRect
Documentation:
Number of pixels to expand in root layout coordinates for cull rect under
scroll translation or other composited transform:
  kCullRectPixelDistanceToExpand *
  (1 + (device_pixel_ratio - 1) * kCullRectExpansionDPRCoef)
If kCullRectExpansionDPRCoef equals 0 (the default), the expansion will be
kCullRectPixelDistanceToExpand in local coordinates.
If kCullRectExpansionDPRCoef equals 1, the expansion will be
kCullRectPixelDistanceToExpand in device coordinates.

Name: kAccessibilityTextFormatting
Documentation:
Enables the addition of text formatting information to the Android
AccessibilityNodeInfo accessibility tree.

Name: kIgnoreDuplicateNavs
Documentation:
Controls whether we ignore duplicate navigations or not, in favor of
preserving the already ongoing navigation.

Name: kHistoryPageHistorySyncPromo
Documentation: Add history sync opt-in promo in the History Page.

Name: kAutofillReplaceCachedWebElementsByRendererIds
Documentation:
Replaces cached web elements in AutofillAgent and FormTracker by their
renderer ids.

Name: kWebUIOmniboxPopup
Documentation: If enabled, shows the omnibox suggestions popup in WebUI.

Name: kDisallowNonAsciiCookies
Documentation: Disallows cookies to have non ascii values in their name or value.

Name: kEnableSavePackageForOffTheRecord
Documentation: Whether to enable save package for off the record mode.

Name: kStorageAccessHeadersRespectPermissionsPolicy
Documentation:
If enabled and `kPopulatePermissionsPolicyOnRequest` is also enabled, storage
access headers will respect the "storage-access" permissions policy when
calculating storage access status.

Name: kFedCmAuthz
Documentation:
Enables usage of the FedCM Authz API.
Note that actual exposure of the API to web content is controlled by
the flag in RuntimeEnabledFeatures on the blink side. See also the use
of kSetOnlyIfOverridden in content/child/runtime_features.cc. We enable
it here by default to support use in origin trials and web platform tests.

Name: kNtpPhotosModuleSplitSvgOptInArtWork
Documentation:
If enabled, the single svg image show in Photos opt-in screen will be
replaced by constituent images to support i18n.

Name: kNonUniformityValidationFeature
Documentation:
Used to assess the reliability of field trial data by sending artificial
non-uniform data drawn from a log normal distribution.

Name: kLCPPInitiatorOrigin
Documentation: If enabled, LCPP learns with a navigation-initiator origin.

Name: kResourceAttributionIncludeOrigins
Documentation:
When enabled, Resource Attribution measurements will include contexts for
individual origins.

Name: kRestorePrimaryAccountInfo
Documentation: Internal feature - exposed only unit testing.

Name: kCrossOriginOpenerPolicy
Documentation:
Enables Cross-Origin Opener Policy (COOP).
https://gist.github.com/annevk/6f2dd8c79c77123f39797f6bdac43f3e
https://html.spec.whatwg.org/C/#cross-origin-opener-policy
Currently this feature is enabled for all platforms except WebView.

Name: kTabGroupSyncAutoOpenKillSwitch
Documentation:
Feature flag to disable auto-open of saved tab groups. Note that the
settings page for auto open will still be visible, and when user is allowed
to change. However the written pref from the user selection will not be
honored. This feature flag should be used only in case of an emergency.

Name: kCustomizeChromeWallpaperSearchInspirationCard
Documentation:
If enabled, shows inspiration card in Customize Chrome Side Panel Wallpaper
Search.

Name: kNewTabPageTriggerForPrerender2
Documentation:
This flag is used for enabling New Tab Page triggered prerendering. See
crbug.com/1462832 for more details of New Tab Page triggered prerendering.

Name: kSetLeakCheckRequestCriticality
Documentation:
Sets request criticality when calling leak check service to detect leaked
passwords.

Name: kForwardMemoryPressureToBlinkIsolates
Documentation:
Whether a memory pressure signal in a renderer should be forwarded to Blink
isolates. Forwarding the signal triggers a GC (critical) or starts
incremental marking (moderate), see `v8::Heap::CheckMemoryPressure`.

Name: kWebUICodeCache
Documentation: Enables code caching for scripts used on WebUI pages.

Name: kPersistentHistogramsFeature
Documentation:
Feature definition for enabling histogram persistence. Note that this feature
(along with its param `kPersistentHistogramsStorage`, declared below) is not
used for Chrome on Linux, ChromeOS, Windows, macOS, and Android. Instead,
histograms are persisted to a memory-mapped file, and set up before field
trial initialization (see //chrome/app/chrome_main_delegate.cc).

Name: kCoopRestrictProperties
Documentation:
Introduce a new COOP value: restrict-properties. It restricts window
properties that can be accessed by other pages. This also grants
crossOriginIsolated if coupled with an appropriate COEP header.
This used solely for testing the process model and should not be enabled in
any production code. See https://crbug.com/1221127.

Name: kAlignWakeUps
Documentation:
Under this feature, wake ups are aligned at a 8ms boundary when allowed per
DelayPolicy.

Name: kPrefetchNetworkPriorityForEmbedders
Documentation:
Enabling this will apply net::RequestPriority::MEDIUM for prefetch
requests triggered by embedders. See crbug.com/353628437 to track this issue.

Name: kTopLevelTpcdTrialSettings
Documentation: Feature to enable consideration of top-level 3PC deprecation trial settings.

Name: kZeroScrollMetricsUpdate
Documentation:
When enabled, we save the `EventMetrics` for a scroll, even when the result
is no damage. So that the termination can be per properly attributed to the
end of frame production for the given VSync.

Name: kNoDiscardableMemoryForGpuDecodePath
Documentation:
Enabling this will make the GPU decode path use a mock implementation of
discardable memory.

Name: kUnoPhase2FollowUp
Documentation:
Flag that controls Uno fast-follow features which are:
- Batch upload of left-behind bookmarks from the bookmark manager
- Turn on bookmarks and reading list when signing in from bookmark manager
- Confirmation dialog when turning off “Allow Chrome sign-in”
- Promo for signed-in users with bookmarks toggle off

Name: kUIExperimentMaxAutocompleteMatches
Documentation:
Feature used to cap max suggestions shown according to the params
UIMaxAutocompleteMatches and UIMaxAutocompleteMatchesByProvider.

Name: kLiveCaption
Documentation: Enables the Live Caption feature on supported devices.

Name: kEnsureExistingRendererAlive
Documentation:
Ensures the renderer is not dead when getting the process host for a site
instance.

Name: kFledgeBiddingAndAuctionNonceSupport
Documentation: Enable response authorization using the Ad-Auction-Result-Nonce header.

Name: kReuseDetectionBasedOnPasswordHashes
Documentation: Detects password reuse based on hashed password values.

Name: kDownloadServiceFeature
Documentation:
Used to set configuration of download service through Finch. This is not used
to turn on/off the feature.

Name: kNoReferrers
Documentation:
When kNoReferrers is enabled, most HTTP requests will provide empty
referrers instead of their ordinary behavior.

Name: kEnablePixelCanvasRecording
Documentation:
If enabled, all draw commands recorded on canvas are done in pixel aligned
measurements. This also enables scaling of all elements in views and layers
to be done via corner points. See https://crbug.com/720596 for details.

Name: kRemoveRendererProcessLimit
Documentation:
A feature to experiment with removing the soft process limit. See
https://crbug.com/369342694.

Name: kLCPPFontURLPredictor
Documentation:
If enabled, fetched font URLs are observed to predict font usage in the
future navigation.

Name: kMoveThemePrefsToSpecifics
Documentation:
If enabled, uses new fields ThemeSpecifics to replace theme prefs, thus
avoiding use of preferences to sync themes.

Name: kEnableWindowsGamingInputDataFetcher
Documentation:
Enables the Windows.Gaming.Input data fetcher.

Note: This feature is used by the "never expire" flag
chrome://flags/#enable-windows-gaming-input-data-fetcher and should not be
removed. See crbug.com/40287784.

Name: kDeviceBoundSessions
Documentation:
This feature will enable the Device Bound Session Credentials protocol to let
the server assert sessions (and cookies) are bound to a specific device.

Name: kBookmarksExportUseSaf
Documentation: disabled by default because of an issue on Android 6.0

Name: kExtensionTelemetryForEnterprise
Documentation:
Enables the telemetry service to collect signals and generate reports to send
for enterprise.

Name: kPersistDeviceBoundSessions
Documentation:
This feature will enable the browser to persist Device Bound Session data
across restarts. This feature is only valid if `kDeviceBoundSessions` is
enabled.

Name: kV8DecommitPooledPages
Documentation: Decommit (rather than discard) pooled pages.

Name: kAutofillEnableRankingFormulaCreditCards
Documentation:
When enabled, autofill will use the new ranking algorithm for credit card
autofill suggestions.

Name: kAllowHardwareBufferUsageFlagsFromVulkanForScanout
Documentation:
Same as above (and depends on it) and allows using extra usage even if we use
USAGE_COMPOSER_OVERLAY.

Name: kNtpSafeBrowsingModule
Documentation: If enabled, SafeBrowsing module will be shown to a target user.

Name: kFilterAdsOnAbusiveSites
Documentation: Enables the blocking of ads on sites that are abusive.

Name: kFingerprintingProtectionUx
Documentation: Enables fingerprinting protection setting UX.

Name: kDCompTripleBufferVideoSwapChain
Documentation: Use BufferCount of 3 for direct composition video swap chains.

Name: kDeferredOverlaysRelease
Documentation:
On platforms with delegated compositing, try to release overlays later, when
no new frames are swapped.

Name: kHardwareMediaKeyHandling
Documentation: Enables handling of hardware media keys for controlling media.

Name: kPermissionElementPromptPositioning
Documentation:
Enables different positioning of the permission dialog, so that it's placed
near the permission element, if possible.
This feature should be enabled with blink::features::kPermissionElement.

Name: kFencedFramesCrossOriginEventReporting
Documentation:
Enable sending event-level reports through reportEvent() in cross-origin
subframes. This requires opt-in both from the cross-origin subframe that is
sending the beacon as well as the document that contains information about
the reportEvent() endpoints.

Name: kSetIsolatesPriority
Documentation: Set a tri-state priority on v8 isolates reflecting the renderer priority.

Name: kEnableUrlRestriction
Documentation: Enables checking for URLs before syncing them to remote devices.

Name: kLiveCaptionUseWaitK
Documentation:
Use a wait-k approach to reduce flickering when translating partial speech
recognition results.

Name: kTranslateRankerQuery
Documentation:
Features used to enable ranker query, enforcement and logging. Note that
enabling enforcement implies (forces) enabling queries.

Name: kBiometricTouchToFill
Documentation: Enables Biometrics for the Touch To Fill feature. This only effects Android.

Name: kClientSideDetectionBrandAndIntentForScamDetection
Documentation:
Create a response containing the brand and the intent of the page using the
on-device model LLM.

Name: kBackgroundResourceFetch
Documentation:
Enable background resource fetch in Blink. See https://crbug.com/1379780 for
more details.

Name: kTabGroupsCollapseFreezing
Documentation:
Enables tabs to be frozen when collapsed.
https://crbug.com/1110108

Name: kSecurePaymentConfirmationDebug
Documentation:
Used to control whether to remove the restriction that PaymentCredential in
WebAuthn and secure payment confirmation method in PaymentRequest API must
use a user verifying platform authenticator. When enabled, this allows using
such devices as UbiKey on Linux, which can make development easier.

Name: kJXL
Documentation: Enables the JPEG XL Image File Format (JXL).

Name: kPostMessageThirdPartyToThirdPartyDifferentBucketSameOriginBlockedIfStorageIsPartitioned
Documentation:
Whether third-party to third-party different-bucket same-origin post messages
are blocked when storage partitioning is enabled.

Name: kSiteIsolationMemoryThresholdsAndroid
Documentation:
kSiteIsolationMemoryThresholdsAndroid is checked before individual site
isolation mode base::Features (such as kSitePerProcess or
kSiteIsolationForPasswordSites), and (if enabled) can restrict those modes
to not apply to low-memory devices below a certain memory threshold.  The
threshold for what is considered a "low memory" device can be set (in MB)
via field trial params with the names defined below, with independent params
for strict site isolation (kSitePerProcess) and partial site isolation modes
(kSiteIsolationForPasswordSites, kSiteIsolationForOAuthSites, etc). These
thresholds are compared against base::SysInfo::AmountOfPhysicalMemoryMB().
On devices below the memory threshold, the site isolation features such as
kSitePerProcess won't be checked at all, and field trials won't activate
either the control or the experiment group.

Name: kThrottleFrameRateOnManyDidNotProduceFrame
Documentation:
Whether frame rate should be throttled when there were many "did not produce
frame" recently.

Name: kDesktopPWAsElidedExtensionsMenu
Documentation:
Moves the Extensions "puzzle piece" icon from the title bar into the app menu
for web app windows.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformEphemeralBottomRank
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling the URL visit resumption ranker.

Name: kParallelDownloading
Documentation: Whether a download can be handled by parallel jobs.

Name: kBrowsingTopicsDocumentAPI
Documentation:
Enables calling the Topics API through Javascript (i.e.
document.browsingTopics()). For this feature to take effect, the main Topics
feature has to be enabled first (i.e. `kBrowsingTopics` is enabled, and,
either a valid Origin Trial token exists or `kPrivacySandboxAdsAPIsOverride`
is enabled.)

Name: kPlusAddressFilledPlusAddressViaManualFallbackSurvey
Documentation: TODO: crbug.com/348139343 - Move back to components/plus_addresses.

Name: kFedCmLightweightMode
Documentation: Enables Lightweight FedCM Mode

Name: kCorsNonWildcardRequestHeadersSupport
Documentation: https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#cors-non-wildcard-request-header-name

Name: kLensStandalone
Documentation: Enables context menu search by image sending to the Lens homepage.

Name: kThreatDomDetailsTagAndAttributeFeature
Documentation:
Specifies which non-resource HTML Elements to collect based on their tag and
attributes. It's a single param containing a comma-separated list of pairs.
For example: "tag1,id,tag1,height,tag2,foo" - this will collect elements with
tag "tag1" that have attribute "id" or "height" set, and elements of tag
"tag2" if they have attribute "foo" set. All tag names and attributes should
be lower case.

Name: kEnterpriseRealTimeUrlCheckOnAndroid
Documentation:
When on, enterprise policy EnterpriseRealTimeUrlCheckMode on Android is
supported.

Name: kAutofillExtractInputDate
Documentation:
When enabled, extracts <input type=date>, which may be filled by Autofill AI.
This is a kill switch.
TODO(crbug.com/396325496): Clean up after M137 branch (April 28, 2025).

Name: kWebAppEnableScopeExtensions
Documentation:
Controls scope extensions feature in web apps. Controls parsing of
"scope_extensions" field in web app manifests. See explainer for more
information:
https://github.com/WICG/manifest-incubations/blob/gh-pages/scope_extensions-explainer.md

Name: kV8SideStepTransitions
Documentation: Faster object cloning

Name: kAllowForceMergeRenderPassWithRequireOverlayQuads
Documentation:
Allow SurfaceAggregator to merge render passes when they contain quads that
require overlay (e.g. protected video). See usage in |EmitSurfaceContent|.

Name: kTabGroupSyncDelegateAndroid
Documentation:
Feature flag for Java controller layer migration to use TabGroupSyncDelegate.
Noop when disabled.

Name: kJavaScriptRegExpModifiers
Documentation: Enables the RegExp modifiers proposal.

Name: kConvertTrackpadEventsToMouse
Documentation:
Enables converting trackpad click gestures to mouse events in
order for them to be interpreted similar to a desktop
experience (i.e. double-click to select word.)

Name: kUnifiedAutoplay
Documentation:
Enables the Unified Autoplay policy by overriding the platform's default
autoplay policy.

Name: kNtpDriveModule
Documentation:
If enabled, Google Drive module will be shown.
This is a kill switch. Keep indefinitely.

Name: kLoginDetection
Documentation: Enables login detection to sited based on various heuristics.

Name: kGlobalMediaControlsUpdatedUI
Documentation: Updated global media controls UI for all the non-CrOS desktop platforms.

Name: kAccessibilityUnifiedSnapshots
Documentation: Enables the use of a unified code path for AXTree snapshots.

Name: kAggregationServiceMultipleCloudProviders
Documentation: This feature is no longer checked, and only the feature param is used.

Name: kSkipEarlyCommitPendingForCrashedFrame
Documentation:
Enables skipping the early call to CommitPending when navigating away from a
crashed frame.

Name: kAlpsParsing
Documentation: Whether ALPS parsing is on for any type of frame.

Name: kHidePastePopupOnGSB
Documentation: Whether to hide paste popup on GestureScrollBegin or GestureScrollUpdate.

Name: kShoppingUserSegmentFeature
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling shopping user segment feature.

Name: kEnterpriseFileObfuscation
Documentation:
Feature to enable insecure obfuscation and deobfuscation of files sent to
WebProtect deep scanning service for enterprise users.

Name: kPartitionedPopinsHeaderPolicyBypass
Documentation:
Partitioned Popins must have a Popin-Policy in their top-frame HTTP Response
that permits the opener origin. This feature disables that check for purposes
of testing only, this must never be enabled by default in any context.
See https://explainers-by-googlers.github.io/partitioned-popins/

Name: kDisambiguateTabMatchingForEntitySuggestions
Documentation: Entity suggestion disambiguation.

Name: kTailoredSecurityIntegration
Documentation: Controls whether the integration of tailored security settings is enabled.

Name: kWebLockScreenApi
Documentation:
Enable the web lockscreen API implementation
(https://github.com/WICG/lock-screen) in Chrome.

Name: kInteractiveDetectorIgnoreFcp
Documentation: Don't require FCP for the page to turn interactive. Useful for testing.

Name: kWebAuthnEnclaveAttestation
Documentation: Checks attestation from the enclave service.

Name: kEnableSaveDataHeader
Documentation: Enable save-data header separately (without enabled data reduction service).

Name: kFedCmMultipleIdentityProviders
Documentation:
Enables usage of the FedCM API with multiple identity providers at the same
time.

Name: kResamplingScrollEvents
Documentation:
Enables resampling GestureScroll events on compositor thread.
Uses the kPredictorName* values in ui_base_features.h as the 'predictor'
feature param.

Name: kDisallowSpaceCharacterInURLHostParsing
Documentation: When enabled, treat space characters as invalid in URL host parsing.

Name: kPolicyPagePromotionEligibilityCheckedBanner
Documentation:
If enabled, the banner on the chrome://policy page to be shown only to
eligible users passing through the promotion eligibility checker.

Name: kCrashReportingAPIMoreContextData
Documentation:
Enables more context data to crash reports reported via the Crash Reporting
API. See https://crbug.com/400432195.

Name: kReportNotificationContentDetectionData
Documentation:
Enables reporting notification contents and metadata to the server, upon user
consent.

Name: kAllowDevToolsMainThreadDebuggerForMultipleMainFrames
Documentation:
Allows running DevTools main thread debugger even when a renderer process
hosts multiple main frames.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformSearchUser
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling search user segment.

Name: kPeriodicSyncPermissionForDefaultSearchEngine
Documentation:
If enabled, the installability criteria for granting PBS permission is
dropped and the content setting is checked. This only applies if the
requesting origin matches that of the browser's default search engine.

Name: kUseSettingsAddressEditorInPaymentsRequest
Documentation:
When enabled, the address add/edit editor in the payments request would be
removed and instead, the address editor from the settings will be used.
TODO: crbug.com/399071964 - Remove when launched.

Name: kAllowLCDTextWithFilter
Documentation:
When enabled, LCD text is allowed with some filters and backdrop filters.
Killswitch M135.

Name: kMultipleSpareRPHs
Documentation:
When enabled, additional spare RPHs will be warmed up when the browser is
not busy.

Name: kEnableHardwareMirrorMode
Documentation:
A temporary flag to control hardware mirroring until it is decided whether to
permanently remove hardware mirroring support. See crbug.com/1161556 for
details.

Name: kFeedHeaderRemoval
Documentation: Feature that removes feed header.

Name: kHappinessTrackingSurveysForComposeClose
Documentation: Enables or disables the Happiness Tracking System for Compose on close.

Name: kPrerenderFallbackToPreconnect
Documentation: Allows Chrome to do preconnect when prerender fails.

Name: kWebViewEnableADPFGpuMain
Documentation:
If enabled, the GPU Main thread is included in the set of threads reported
to the HWUI. This feature works only when WebViewEnableADPF is enabled,
otherwise this is a no-op.

Name: kFledgeSellerSignalsRequestsOneAtATime
Documentation:
Send each trusted seller signals request right after it is queued, so
that it does not get batched.

Name: kWebOTPAssertionFeaturePolicy
Documentation:
Enables WebOTP calls in cross-origin iframes if allowed by Permissions
Policy.

Name: kMlUrlScoreCaching
Documentation:
If enabled, the ML scoring service will make use of an in-memory ML score
cache in order to speed up the overall scoring process.

Name: kBackForwardCachePrioritizedEntry
Documentation:
When a prioritized BFCache entry needs to be evicted, it will be kept
in the cache instead. Only the latest prioritized entry outside the limit
will be handled in this way.

Name: kV8Turboshaft
Documentation: Enables Turbofan's new compiler IR Turboshaft.

Name: kEnhancedFieldsForSecOps
Documentation:
Enabled additional device and network information to RealTimeUrlCheck
requests, WP scan requests, and reporting events. These will be visible from
the chrome://safe-browsing page.

Name: kShowWarningsForSuspiciousNotifications
Documentation:
Enables replacing notification contents with a Chrome warning when the
on-device model returns a sufficiently suspicious verdict.

Name: kAutofillAiUploadModelRequestAndResponse
Documentation:
When enabled, requests and responses of client-triggered Autofill AI model
runs are uploaded to MQLS.

Name: kCacheControlNoStoreEnterBackForwardCache
Documentation:
Allows pages with cache-control:no-store to enter the back/forward cache.
Feature params can specify whether pages with cache-control:no-store can be
restored if cookies change / if HTTPOnly cookies change.
TODO(crbug.com/40189625): Remove this feature and clean up.

Name: kKAnonymityService
Documentation: When enabled, allows other features to use the k-Anonymity Service.

Name: kAllowRecentSessionTracking
Documentation: Kill switch for recent session tracking. Enabled by default.

Name: kUserVisibleDebug
Documentation:
Enables debug info in user-visible surfaces, like the actual WebUI page.
Does nothing if `kJourneys` is disabled.

Name: kNtpMostRelevantTabResumptionModule
Documentation: If enabled, the Tab Resumption module will be shown.

Name: kEnableBandATriggeredUpdates
Documentation: Enable parsing triggered updates from B&A response.

Name: kMemoryPressureBasedSourceBufferGC
Documentation:
Make MSE garbage collection algorithm more aggressive when we are under
moderate or critical memory pressure. This will relieve memory pressure by
releasing stale data from MSE buffers.

Name: kInlineFullscreenPerfExperiment
Documentation:
Controls whether a performance improvement in browser feature support
checking is enabled.

Name: kLocalHistoryZeroSuggestBeyondNTP
Documentation:
Enables local history zero-prefix suggestions in every context in which the
remote zero-prefix suggestions are enabled.

Name: kNoThrowForCSPBlockedWorker
Documentation:
Don't throw exception from worker constructor when the worker url is blocked
by CSP, fire error event asynchronously instead.
See https://crbug.com/41285169.

Name: kStripCredentialsForExternalProtocolHandler
Documentation:
When enabled, it strips credentials from URL to mitigate the mitigate the
risk of credential leakage when registering protocol handlers for standard
schemes. This feature is enabled by default and meant to be used as a
killswitch.
https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/system-state.html#security-and-privacy

Name: kAImageReaderVideoOutput
Documentation: Enables the Android Image Reader path for Video decoding(for AVDA and MCVD)

Name: kAutoPictureInPictureForVideoPlayback
Documentation:
Allows the AutoPictureInPictureTabHelper to automatically enter
picture-in-picture for websites with video playback (instead of only websites
using camera or microphone).

Name: kEncryptedAndPlaintextValuesAreInvalid
Documentation:
If enabled, then a cookie entry containing both encrypted and plaintext
values is considered invalid, and the entire eTLD group will be dropped.

Name: kGetCookiesOnSet
Documentation:
When enabled, returns the output of GetCookiesString when calling
SetCookiesString, so that it can be cached in the renderer to avoid an IPC
on subsequent Get requests.

Name: kPrivacySandboxAdsAPIsOverride
Documentation:
Enables exposure of ads APIs in the renderer: Attribution Reporting,
FLEDGE, Topics, along with a number of other features actively in development
within these APIs.

Name: kVisibilityAwareResourceScheduler
Documentation:
Enables visibility aware network service resource scheduler. When enabled,
request may be prioritized or de-prioritized based on the visibility of
requestors.
TODO(crbug.com/40066382): Remove this feature.

Name: kFastFilePathIsParent
Documentation:
Whether a fast implementation of FilePath::IsParent is used. This feature
exists to ensure that the fast implementation can be disabled quickly if
issues are found with it.

Name: kRenderThrottleFrameRate
Documentation:
Allow the main thread to throttle the main frame rate.
Note that the composited animations will not be affected.
Typically the throttle is triggered with the render-blocking API <link
rel="expect" blocking="full-frame-rate"/>.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformEphemeralCardRanker
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling the Ephemeral Card ranker.

Name: kEnableAriaElementReflection
Documentation:
Support aria element reflection. For example:
    element.ariaActiveDescendantElement = child;

Name: kIntensiveWakeUpThrottling
Documentation:
When enabled, wake ups from throttleable TaskQueues are limited to 1 per
minute in a page that has been backgrounded for 5 minutes.

Intensive wake up throttling is enforced in addition to other throttling
mechanisms:
 - 1 wake up per second in a background page or hidden cross-origin frame
 - 1% CPU time in a page that has been backgrounded for 10 seconds

Feature tracking bug: https://crbug.com/1075553

The base::Feature should not be read from; rather the provided accessors
should be used, which also take into account the managed policy override of
the feature.

The base::Feature is enabled by default on all platforms. However, on
Android, it has no effect because page freezing kicks in at the same time. It
would have an effect if the grace period ("grace_period_seconds" param) was
reduced.

Name: kAsyncQuicSession
Documentation: A flag to use asynchronous session creation for new QUIC sessions.

Name: kAutofillPreferSavedFormAsSubmittedForm
Documentation:
Replaces blink::WebFormElementObserver usage in FormTracker by updated logic
for tracking the disappearance of forms as well as other submission
triggering events. See `AutofillAgent::GetSubmittedForm()` for more
documentation.
TODO(crbug.com/40281981): Remove when launched.

Name: kV8OffThreadFinalization
Documentation: Enables finalizing streaming JS compilations on a background thread.

Name: kPageSpecificDataDialogRelatedInstalledAppsSection
Documentation:
Controls whether the site-specific data dialog shows a related installed
applications section.

Name: kAttributionDebugReportingCookieDeprecationTesting
Documentation:
Enables attribution reporting transitional debug reporting for the cookie
deprecation experiment.

Name: kRemoteOptimizationGuideFetching
Documentation: Enables fetching from a remote Optimization Guide Service.

Name: kTreesInViz
Documentation: Enables Viz service-side layer trees for content rendering.

Name: kSkipTpcdMitigationsForAds
Documentation:
This feature allows skipping TPCD mitigation checks when the cookie access
is tagged as being used for advertising purposes. This means that cookies
will continue to be blocked for cookie accesses on ad requests even if the
3PC mitigations would otherwise allow the access.

Name: kRestrictOrientationLockToPhones
Documentation:
If enabled, then orientation lock won't claim to work on anything but phone
form factors.  Tablets already do unpredictable things, such as letterboxing
vs rotating and/or (successfully) ignoring the request entirely.  Setting
this flag turns off those use-cases which nobody should be relying on right
now anyway; they don't work.

Name: kComposeUpfrontInputModes
Documentation: Enables or disables upfront input modes in the dialog.

Name: kSeamlessRenderFrameSwap
Documentation: When enabled, change the ordering of frame swap in render (crbug/357649043).

Name: kBackForwardCache
Documentation: Enable using the BackForwardCache.

Name: kHistoryClustersVisitDeduping
Documentation: Enables experimentation for how to dedupe visits in clusters.

Name: kAdSamplerTriggerFeature
Documentation:
Controls various parameters related to occasionally collecting ad samples,
for example to control how often collection should occur.

Name: kCastStreamingVp9
Documentation:
Controls whether mirroring negotiations will include the VP9 codec for video
encoding.

NOTE: currently only software VP9 encoding is supported.
TODO(https://crbug.com/1311770): hardware VP9 encoding should be added.

Name: kHistoryClustersKeywordFiltering
Documentation: Enables use of additional keyword filtering operations on clusters.

Name: kStarterPackExpansion
Documentation: Site search/Keyword mode related features.

Name: kTabScrollingButtonPosition
Documentation: Enables buttons when scrolling the tabstrip https://crbug.com/951078

Name: kWebViewThreadSafeMediaDefault
Documentation:
This is used as default state because it's different for webview and chrome.
WebView hardcodes this as enabled in AwMainDelegate.

Name: kEnableAccessibilityAriaVirtualContent
Documentation: Recognize "aria-virtualcontent" as a valid aria property.

Name: GetIOSDesktopPromoFeatureEngagement
Documentation:
GetIOSDesktopPromoFeatureEngagement gets the correct "Feature Engagement
Tracker" feature for the given promo type.

Name: kPageContentAnnotations
Documentation: Enables page content to be annotated.

Name: kOsFeedbackSaveReportToLocalForE2ETesting
Documentation: Alphabetical:

Name: kSendTabToSelfIOSPushNotifications
Documentation:
If this feature is enabled, allow the user to receive Send Tab to Self
notifications as a push notification to their target iOS device.

Name: kLowLatencyWebGLImageChromium
Documentation:
Allow low latency WebGL to be in overlay (generally meaning scanned out
directly to display), even if regular canvas are not in overlay
(WebGLImageChromium is disabled).

Name: kSerialPortConnected
Documentation:
Expose serial port logical connection state and dispatch connection events
for Bluetooth serial ports when the Bluetooth device connection state
changes.

Name: kMigrateSessionsOnNetworkChangeV2
Documentation:
Whether QuicParams::migrate_sessions_on_network_change_v2 defaults to true or
false. This is needed as a workaround to set this value to true on Android
but not on WebView (until crbug.com/1430082 has been fixed).

Name: kCommittedOriginTracking
Documentation:
Turn on the tracking of origins committed in each renderer process in
ChildProcessSecurityPolicy. This is required for committed origin
enforcements, which is gated behind kCommittedOriginEnforcements.
Temporarily disabled while investigating https://crbug.com/377793089.

Name: kAutofillFixEmptyFieldAndroidSettingsBug
Documentation:
If enabled, empty autofill settings fields will be correctly saved.
TODO: crbug.com/402020076 - Clean up when confirmed that this is safe.

Name: kNewBrowsingContextStateOnBrowsingContextGroupSwap
Documentation:
Currently there are two paths - legacy code, in which BrowsingContextState
will be 1:1 with FrameTreeNode, allowing us to move proxy storage to it as a
no-op, and a new path hidden behind a feature flag, which will create a new
BrowsingContextState for cross-BrowsingInstance navigations.

Name: kPriorityOverridePendingViews
Documentation:
This feature makes it so that having pending views increase the priority of a
RenderProcessHost even when there is a priority override.

Name: kLegacyPKCS1ForTLS13
Documentation:
Enables support for codepoints defined in draft-ietf-tls-tls13-pkcs1, which
enable RSA keys to be used with client certificates even if they do not
support RSA-PSS.

Name: kAutofillGreekRegexes
Documentation: When enabled, Greek regexes are used for parsing in branded builds.

Name: kSpeculativeServiceWorkerWarmUp
Documentation: TODO(crbug/1431792): Speculatively warm-up service worker.

Name: kInstalledApp
Documentation: Kill switch for the GetInstalledRelatedApps API.

Name: kV8IntelJCCErratumMitigation
Documentation:
Add additional alignment for some jumps in generated x64 code, to mitigate
the performance impact of the Intel JCC erratum (https://crbug.com/v8/14225).
Currently disabled by default in V8, but adding here temporarily to test
real-world performance impact via a Finch experiment.

Name: kFrequentFeatureUserSegmentFeature
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling frequent feature user segment.

Name: kMediaPowerExperiment
Documentation: Enable aggregate power measurement for media playback.

Name: kEnableADPFScrollBoost
Documentation:
Used to enable the HintSession::Mode::BOOST mode. BOOST mode try to force
the ADPF(Android Dynamic Performance Framework) to give Chrome more CPU
resources during a scroll.

Name: kVaapiJpegImageDecodeAcceleration
Documentation:
Controls the decode acceleration of JPEG images (as opposed to camera
captures) in Chrome OS using the VA-API.
TODO(andrescj): remove or enable by default in Chrome OS once
https://crbug.com/868400 is resolved.

Name: kFeedStamp
Documentation: Feature that enables StAMP cards in the feed.

Name: kNtpMostLikelyFaviconsFromServerFeature
Documentation:
Feature to allow the new Google favicon server for fetching favicons for Most
Likely tiles on the New Tab Page.

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessPermissionPrompt
Documentation:
When kPrivateNetworkAccessPermissionPrompt is enabled, public secure websites
are allowed to access private insecure subresources with user's permission.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformFeature
Documentation: Core feature flag for segmentation platform.

Name: kEnableServiceWorkersForChromeScheme
Documentation: Enables service workers on chrome:// urls.

Name: kIncreasedCmdBufferParseSlice
Documentation:
Use a 100-command limit before forcing context switch per command buffer
instead of 20.

Name: kAppStoreBillingDebug
Documentation:
Used to control whether to remove the restriction that TWA has to be
installed from specific app stores.

Name: kMigrateAccountPrefs
Documentation:
If enabled, holds the account preference values under a dictionary in the
main preferences file.

Name: kLanguageDetectionModelForTesting
Documentation:
Allows supplying a local model file. The file cannot be opened if we're in
a sandbox. You can use --no-sandbox when running tests that rely on this
flag.
TODO(https://crbug.com/354069716): Move this to the model service in the
browser.

Name: kFontsFingerprintMitigation
Documentation: Filter the list of fonts allowing the use of only standard fonts

Name: kPushSubscriptionChangeEventOnResubscribe
Documentation:
Fires the `pushsubscriptionchange` event defined here:
https://w3c.github.io/push-api/#the-pushsubscriptionchange-event
upon manual resubscription to previously unsubscribed notifications.

Name: kWebSQLAccess
Documentation: Allow access to WebSQL APIs.

Name: kSchemefulSameSite
Documentation:
When enabled this feature will cause same-site calculations to take into
account the scheme of the site-for-cookies and the request/response url.

Name: kQueueNavigationsWhileWaitingForCommit
Documentation:
When enabled, queues navigations instead of cancelling the previous
navigation if the previous navigation is already waiting for commit.
See https://crbug.com/838348 and https://crbug.com/1220337.

Name: kPushMessagingBackgroundMode
Documentation:
Enables or disables push subscriptions keeping Chrome running in the
background when closed.

Name: kFractionalScrollOffsets
Documentation:
Enables scrollers inside Blink to store scroll offsets in fractional
floating-point numbers rather than truncating to integers.

Name: kEncryptedReportingPipeline
Documentation: static

Name: kFailUrlProvisionFetcherForTesting
Documentation:
Prevents UrlProvisionFetcher from making a provisioning request. If
specified, any provisioning request made will not be sent to the provisioning
server, and the response will indicate a failure to communicate with the
provisioning server.

Name: kSelectiveInOrderScript
Documentation:
If enabled, parser-blocking scripts are loaded asynchronously. The target
scripts are selectively applied via the allowlist provided from the feature
param. See https://crbug.com/1356396

Name: kCastStreamingVp8
Documentation:
Controls whether mirroring negotiations will include the VP9 codec for video
encoding.

NOTE: this is the default codec for Cast Streaming. Be careful when
disabling.

Name: kScrollbarAnimations
Documentation:
Disable to keep scrollbars visible forever once shown, and immediately
update scrollbar states instead of animating. This is used to ensure
ref tests in WPT do not flake based on the time taken before the
screenshot is captured.

Name: kFeedRecyclerBinderUnmountOnDetach
Documentation: Feature that unmount RecyclerBinder on view detach to fix a memory leak.

Name: kKAnonymityServiceStorage
Documentation:
When enabled, the k-Anonymity Service can use a persistent storage to cache
public keys.

Name: kPrefetchPrerenderIntegration
Documentation:
Use code paths for prefetch/prerender integration.
See also `kPrerender2FallbackPrefetchSpecRules`.

Name: kPsDualWritePrefsToNoticeStorage
Documentation: Enables the notice storage for pref storage.

Name: kGuestViewMPArch
Documentation:
Whether GuestViews (see components/guest_view/README.md) are implemented
using MPArch inner pages. See https://crbug.com/40202416

Name: kAutofillSupportPhoneticNameForJP
Documentation: Enables using a custom address model for Japan, overriding the legacy one.

Name: kFedCmAutofill
Documentation:
Enables RPs to enhance autofill with federated accounts fetched by the FedCM
API.

Name: kPrivacyPolicyInsights
Documentation: Enables the privacy policy insights Learning Experiment UI.

Name: kAutofillAiAlwaysTriggerServerModel
Documentation:
If enabled (and if `AutofillAiServerModel` is also enabled), this ignores
the `may_run_server_model` boolean sent by the Autofill server and, instead,
queries the server model for every encountered form that is not already
cached locally.
Only intended for testing.

Name: kGooglePayViaAndroidIntents
Documentation:
If enabled, use Android intents for the following payment methods:
- https://google.com/pay
- https://pay.google.com/authentication.

Name: kEnableExtensionsExplicitBrowserSignin
Documentation:
Enables users to perform an explicit signin upon installing an extension.
After this, syncing for extensions will be enabled when in transport mode
(when a user is signed in but has not turned on full sync).

Name: kOnDeviceHeadProviderIncognito
Documentation: On Device Suggest.

Name: kAutofillEnableVirtualCardJavaPaymentsDataManager
Documentation:
When enabled, the Virtual Card enrollment bottom sheet uses the Java
payments data manager and associated image fetcher to retrieve the cached
card art images (when available on Android). When not enabled, the native
payments data manager and associated image fetcher are used, where the image
is not cached.

Name: kMetricsLogTrimming
Documentation:
Controls trimming for metrics logs. This feature allows tuning of the log
trimming behaviour via serverside parameters. Do not remove. See
components/metrics/metrics_service_client.cc and
components/metrics/unsent_log_store.cc.

Name: kAnchovyUseProdServer
Documentation: Enables Anchovy Prod Server

Name: kExtensionTelemetryFileDataForCommandLineExtensions
Documentation:
Allows the Extension Telemetry Service to include file data of extensions
specified in the --load-extension commandline switch in telemetry reports.

Name: kCollectAndroidFrameTimelineMetrics
Documentation: Whether to report frame metrics to the Android.FrameTimeline.* histograms.

Name: kDCompTripleBufferRootSwapChain
Documentation: Use BufferCount of 3 for the direct composition root swap chain.

Name: kClientSideDetectionSamplePing
Documentation:
Send a sample CSPP ping when a URL matches the CSD allowlist and all other
preclassification check conditions pass.

Name: kAudioFocusEnforcement
Documentation:
Enables Audio Focus enforcement which means that only one media session can
have audio focus at any one time.

Name: kLensOverlayUpdatedClientContext
Documentation: Enables the Lens overlay updated client context.

Name: kPrerender2FallbackPrefetchSpecRules
Documentation:
Enables fallback from prerender to prefetch for Speculation Rules.
See https://crbug.com/342089123 for more details.

Effects:

- Use code paths for prefetch/prerender integration. (The effect of
  `kPrefetchPrerenderIntegration`).
- Trigger prefetch ahead of prerender.

Name: kAllowEyeDropperWGCScreenCapture
Documentation: Enables the use of WGC for the Eye Dropper screen capture.

Name: kVerifyDidCommitParams
Documentation:
Enables comparing browser and renderer's DidCommitProvisionalLoadParams in
RenderFrameHostImpl::VerifyThatBrowserAndRendererCalculatedDidCommitParamsMatch.

Name: kWarmUpCompositor
Documentation:
When enabled, the renderer asks the compositor to request warming up and
create FrameSink speculatively even if invisible. Currently, this is intended
to be used when prerender initial navigation is happening in background.
Please see crbug.com/41496019 for more details.

Name: kCastEnableStreamingWithHiDPI
Documentation: TODO(crbug.com/40255351): Should be removed once working properly.

Name: kWebFeedAwareness
Documentation: Feature that provides the user assistance in discovering the web feed.

Name: kContentCaptureConstantStreaming
Documentation: Enables the constant streaming in the ContentCapture task.

Name: kDiscountConsentV2
Documentation: Feature flag for Discount user consent v2.

Name: kAndroidPaymentIntentsOmitDeprecatedParameters
Documentation:
If enabled, remove the deprecated parameters from the intents that are sent
to Android payment apps.

Name: kReportUserNoisedUserBirthYearAndGender
Documentation:
Enables adding the synced user's noised birth year and gender to the UKM
report. For more details, see doc of metrics::DemographicMetricsProvider in
components/metrics/demographics/demographic_metrics_provider.h.

Name: kEnableProfileTokenManagement
Documentation: Controls whether token-based profile management is enabled.

Name: kPopulateVisitedLinkDatabase
Documentation:
When enabled, this feature flag begins populating the VisitedLinkDatabase
with data.

Name: kV8FlushCodeBasedOnTime
Documentation: Enables code flushing based on time.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformUserVisibleTaskRunner
Documentation:
Feature flag to increase segmentation platform background processing task
runner priority.

Name: kEnhancedSecurityEventFields
Documentation: Enables the addition of new security fields for SecOps.

Name: kDwaFeature
Documentation: Enables DWA recording.

Name: kForceRemoveClosedTabGroupsOnStartup
Documentation:
Force remove all closed tab groups from the sync local DB on startup if this
feature flag is enabled.

Name: kOriginIsolationHeader
Documentation:
Controls the Origin-Agent-Cluster header. Tracking bug
https://crbug.com/1042415; flag removal bug (for when this is fully launched)
https://crbug.com/1148057.

The name is "OriginIsolationHeader" because that was the old name when the
feature was under development.

Name: kWebRtcAllowWgcScreenCapturer
Documentation:
When enabled we will tell WebRTC that we want to use the
Windows.Graphics.Capture API based screen capturer, if it is available.

Name: kV8BaselineBatchCompilation
Documentation: Enables batch compilation for Sparkplug (baseline) compilation.

Name: kCompressionDictionaryTransport
Documentation:
When both this feature and the kCompressionDictionaryTransportBackend feature
are enabled, the following will happen:
  * A <link rel=compression-dictionary> HTML tag and a
    `Link: rel=compression-dictionary` HTTP header will trigger dictionary
    download.
  * HTMLLinkElement.relList.supports('compression-dictionary') will return
    true.
  * The network service may register a HTTP response as a dictionary if the
    response header contains a `use-as-dictionary` header.
This feature can be enabled by an Origin Trial token in Blink. To propagate
the enabled state to the network service, Blink sets the
`shared_dictionary_writer_enabled` flag in resource requests.

Name: kExtensionTelemetryDeclarativeNetRequestActionSignal
Documentation:
Enables collection of telemetry signal whenever an extension invokes the
declarativeNetRequest actions.

Name: kEnableAppMenuButtonColorsForDefaultAvatarButtonStates
Documentation:
Enables using the same colors used for the default app menu button for the
avatar button states using default colors.

Name: kHoldbackDebugReasonStringRemoval
Documentation:
Holdback the removal of debug reason strings in crrev.com/c/6312375
to measure the impact.

Name: kPartitionAllocUseDenserDistribution
Documentation:
If enabled, switches the bucket distribution to a denser one.

We enable this by default everywhere except for 32-bit Android, since we saw
regressions there.

Name: kDetailedLanguageSettings
Documentation: This feature enables setting the application language on Android.

Name: kEnableHistoryScoringSignalsAnnotatorForSearches
Documentation:
If true, enables history scoring signal annotator for populating history
scoring signals associated with Search suggestions. These signals will be
empty for Search suggestions otherwise.

Name: kNtpWallpaperSearchButtonAnimation
Documentation: If enabled, animates New Tab Page's Wallpaper Search Button.

Name: kOmniboxMaxURLMatches
Documentation:
Feature used to cap the number of URL-type matches shown within the
Omnibox. If enabled, the number of URL-type matches is limited (unless
there are no more non-URL matches available.) If enabled, there is a
companion parameter - OmniboxMaxURLMatches - which specifies the maximum
desired number of URL-type matches.

Name: kV8Turbofan
Documentation: Enables the Turbofan compiler.

Name: kDirectCompositionSoftwareOverlays
Documentation:
Allow overlay swapchain to present on all GPUs even if they only support
software overlays. GPU deny lists limit it to NVIDIA only at the moment.

Name: kFledgeMaxGroupLifetimeFeature
Documentation:
Controls the max interest group lifetime in milliseconds. If
kFledgeMaxGroupLifetimeFeature is enabled, then the max interest group
lifetime will be kFledgeMaxGroupLifetimeFeature; otherwise, it will be 30
days.

*WARNING*: Some UMA histograms assume a particular max lifetime for the
purposes of choosing appropriate bucketing, such as
Ads.InterestGroup.Auction.GroupFreshness*. As bucketing should not be changed
for an existing metric, consider adding a new metric with new bucketing if
increasing this value.

NOTE: This value is only enforced when interest groups are joined -- the
lifetimes of groups already in the database will not be affected.

Name: kWebAuthnAmbientSignin
Documentation: Enable non-autofill sign-in UI for conditional mediation.

Name: kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsFromUnknown
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, requests to localhost initiated from non-secure
contexts in the `unknown` IP address space are blocked.

See also:
 - kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequests

Name: kFledgeConsiderKAnonymity
Documentation:
Configures FLEDGE to consider k-anonymity. If both
kFledgeConsiderKAnonymity and kFledgeEnforceKAnonymity are on it will be
enforced; if only kFledgeConsiderKAnonymity is on it will be simulated.

Turning on kFledgeEnforceKAnonymity alone does nothing.

Name: kWebAssemblyDeopt
Documentation:
Enable WebAssembly deoptimization support (not user visible), see
https://crbug.com/42204618.

Name: kFledgeEnableUserAgentOverrides
Documentation: Enable the user agent header in auction requests to be overridden.

Name: kStopExportDFCMetrics
Documentation: When enabled, stops the export of most DFCMetrics.

Name: kTimeLimitedInsecureCookies
Documentation:
Enables expiration duration limit (3 hours) for cookies on insecure websites.
This feature is a no-op unless kEnableSchemeBoundCookies is enabled.

Name: kEnableAsyncNotificationManagerForDownload
Documentation: Whether to enable async notification manager for downloads.

Name: kHstsTopLevelNavigationsOnly
Documentation: When enabled HSTS upgrades will only apply to top-level navigations.

Name: kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequests
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, private network requests initiated from
non-secure contexts in the `public` address space  are blocked.

See also:
 - https://wicg.github.io/private-network-access/#integration-fetch
 - kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsFromPrivate
 - kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsFromUnknown

Name: kAnimateSuggestionsListAppearance
Documentation: Animate appearance of suggestions list.

Name: kPermissionSiteSettingsRadioButton
Documentation:
When enabled, site settings pages use radio button groups other than toggles.
In the meanwhile, CPSS if exist will be a separate radio button group.

Name: kDesktopPWAsTabStripSettings
Documentation: Adds a user settings that allows PWAs to be opened with a tab strip.

Name: kFedCmDelegation
Documentation: Enables usage of the FedCM Delegation API.

Name: kAutofillOverridePredictions
Documentation:
Allows passing a set of overrides for Autofill server predictions.
Example command line to override server predictions manually:
chrome --enable-features=AutofillOverridePredictions:spec/1_2_4-7_8_9
This creates two manual overrides that supersede server predictions as
follows:
* The server prediction for the field with signature 2 in the form with
  signature 1 is overridden to be 4 (NAME_MIDDLE).
* The server prediction for the field with signature 8 in the form with
  signature 7 is overridden to be 9 (EMAIL_ADDRESS).

See
components/autofill/core/browser/crowdsourcing/server_prediction_overrides.h
for more examples and details on how to specify overrides.

Name: kVideoDecodeBatching
Documentation:
Controls whether to pre-dispatch more decode tasks when pending decodes is
smaller than maximum supported decodes as advertiszed by decoder.

Name: kLoadingPredictorDisregardAlwaysAccessesNetwork
Documentation:
Modifies loading predictor so that the value of the |always_access_network|
attribute is not used when computing the predicting score for an origin.

Name: kEnableMSAAOnNewIntelGPUs
Documentation: Enables the use of MSAA in skia on Ice Lake and later intel architectures.

Name: kDirectCompositorThreadIpc
Documentation:
Enables input IPC to directly target the renderer's compositor thread without
hopping through the IO thread first.

Name: kMigrateAlwaysTranslateLanguagesFix
Documentation:
Whether to migrate the obsolete always-translate languages pref to the new
pref during object construction as a fix for crbug/1291356, which had
previously not been migrated at all on iOS. This also enables a more
conservative pref merging process that aims to merge in old always-translate
language values from the obsolete pref without conflicting with any values in
the new pref that may have been added.

TODO(crbug.com/40826252): This base::Feature only exists to allow a less
risky merge into iOS M98. This base::Feature should be removed once it's no
longer relevant and the enabled behavior should become the only behavior.
