Name: kDiscoFeedEndpoint
Documentation: Use the new DiscoFeed endpoint.

Name: kSiteIsolationForCrossOriginOpenerPolicy
Documentation:
Controls whether to isolate sites of documents that specify an eligible
Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy header.  Note that this is only intended to be
used on Android, which does not use strict site isolation. See
https://crbug.com/1018656.

Name: kJavaScriptPromiseTry
Documentation: Enables the Promise.try proposal.

Name: kAutofillRelaxAddressImport
Documentation:
Allows the import of an Autofill profile if duplicate fields were present
with identical field values.
TODO(crbug.com/395855125): Remove when launched.

Name: kPlatformHEVCDecoderSupport
Documentation: Enables HEVC hardware accelerated decoding.

Name: kXsurfaceMetricsReporting
Documentation:
Feature that enables xsurface to provide the metrics reporting state to an
xsurface feed.

Name: kNoForcedFrameUpdatesForWebTests
Documentation: Disables forced frame updates for web tests. Used by web test runner only.

Name: kEmbeddingRequiresOptIn
Documentation:
Requires documents embedded via <iframe>, etc, to explicitly opt-into the
embedding: https://github.com/mikewest/embedding-requires-opt-in.

Name: kGPUBlockListTestGroup
Documentation:
This feature allows enabling specific entries in
software_rendering_list.json, via experimentation. The entries must have
test_group property and test_group feature parameter should be set in the
experiment for the entries that need to be enabled.

Name: kLCPPPrefetchSubresource
Documentation:
If enabled, LCPP prefetches the subresources based on LCP prewarmed HTTP disk
cache data.

Name: kUseAudioLatencyFromHAL
Documentation:
Use the (hacky) AudioManager.getOutputLatency() call to get the estimated
hardware latency for a stream for OpenSLES playback.  This is normally not
needed, except for some Android TV devices.

Name: kOrganicRepeatableQueries
Documentation: Organic Repeatable Queries

Name: kWebFeedSort
Documentation: Feature that enables sorting by different heuristics in the web feed.

Name: kPlusAddressPreallocation
Documentation:
When enabled, plus addresses are preallocated to avoid having to query the
server for every reserve call.

Name: kBookmarksUseBinaryTreeInTitledUrlIndex
Documentation:
Determines which container is used internally in `TitledUrlIndex`,
leading to slightly different performance characteristics. If enabled,
a std::set is used per indexed term instead of base::flat_set.

Name: kWebRtcAllowWgcScreenZeroHz
Documentation:
When enabled we will tell WebRTC that we want to use the 0Hz mode of the
Windows.Graphics.Capture API based {Screen/Window} capturer, if the WGC
capturer is available and enabled. In this mode, only frames with new content
will be sent to the client leading to to 0fps for a static {Screen/Window}
source.
This flag only has an effect if kWebRtcAllowWgcScreenCapturer is enabled.

Name: kAdjustFastMainThreadThreshold
Documentation:
Permits adjusting the threshold we use for determining if main thread updates
are fast. Specifically, via a scalar on the range [0,1] that we multiply with
the existing threshold. I.e., |new_threshold| = |scalar| * |old_threshold|.

Name: kLoginDbDeprecationAndroid
Documentation:
If enabled, the password store no longer uses the Login DB as a backend.
Instead, it either uses the Android-specific storage or an empty backend
if the client isn't eligible for the former.

Name: kPrecompileInlineScripts
Documentation:
If enabled, inline scripts will be stream compiled using a background HTML
scanner.

Name: kSendTabToSelfEnableNotificationTimeOut
Documentation:
If this feature is enabled, the notification shown to users will disapear
after a fixed timeout. When disabled, instead it will remain until the
user interacts with it either by dismissing or openning it.

Name: kPostPowerMonitorBroadcastReceiverInitToBackground
Documentation:
If enabled, post registering PowerMonitor broadcast receiver to a background
thread,

Name: kDefaultANGLEOpenGL
Documentation: Default to using ANGLE's OpenGL backend

Name: kDeviceAuthenticatorAndroidx
Documentation:
The feature is a no-op, it replaces android.hardware.biometrics library on
Android with androidx.biometric.

Name: kFeatureParamWithCache
Documentation: Alphabetical:

Name: kAutofillVirtualViewStructureAndroidInCct
Documentation:
Safe-guard for a crucial fix that prevented consistent use of 3P in CCTs.
It's ineffective when AutofillVirtualViewStructureAndroid is disabled.
TODO: crbug.com/409579377 - Delete after M140.

Name: kPlusAddressUserCreatedMultiplePlusAddressesSurvey
Documentation: TODO: crbug.com/348139343 - Move back to components/plus_addresses.

Name: kEnableVariableRefreshRate
Documentation: Enables the variable refresh rate feature for Borealis gaming only.

Name: kLoadingPreconnectToRedirectTarget
Documentation:
Modifies loading predictor so that the predictions also contain origins of
the redirect target of the navigation.

Name: kDownloadNotificationServiceUnifiedAPI
Documentation:
Whether download notification service uses new unified API based on offline
item and native persistence of notification IDs.

Name: kSafeBrowsingSyncCheckerCheckAllowlist
Documentation:
Enables sync checker to check allowlist first on Chrome on Android. This is
an optimization to improve the speed of Safe Browsing checks.
See go/skip-sync-hpd-allowlist-android for details.

Name: kV8IgnitionElideRedundantTdzChecks
Documentation:
Elide redundant TDZ hole checks in bytecode. This only sets the V8 flag when
manually overridden.

Name: kFreezingWithoutBatterySaver
Documentation: activates freezing of tabs with high background cpu usage

Name: kAutofillCapturedSiteTestsUseAutofillFlow
Documentation:
If enabled, Captured Site Tests will use 'AutofillFlow' utility to trigger
the autofill action. This feature is for testing purposes and is not supposed
to be launched.

Name: kSelfSignedLocalNetworkInterstitial
Documentation:
Enables a special interstitial for self signed cert errors in local network
URLs.

Name: kDiscardableMemoryBackingTrial
Documentation: Feature flag enabling the discardable memory backing trial.

Name: kInputMethodSettingsUiUpdate
Documentation:
Update of the virtual keyboard settings UI as described in
https://crbug.com/876901.

Name: kCompressionDictionaryTransportRequireKnownRootCert
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, Chromium will use stored shared dictionaries
only if the request URL is a localhost URL or the transport layer is using a
certificate rooted at a standard CA root.

Name: kRestrictAbusePorts
Documentation: Finch-controlled list of ports that should be blocked due to ongoing abuse.

Name: kWebRtcApmTellsIfPlayoutReferenceIsNeeded
Documentation:
When enabled, the Audio Processing Module is used to determine whether the
playout reference is needed. Otherwise the decision is based on
`media::AudioProcessingSettings`.

Name: kAdAuctionSignals
Documentation:
Controls the capturing of the Ad-Auction-Signals header, and the maximum
allowed Ad-Auction-Signals header value.

Name: kLinkCopiedToast
Documentation: Individual toasts

Name: kSharedStorageAPI
Documentation:
Enable the shared storage API. Note that enabling this feature does not
automatically expose this API to the web, it only allows the element to be
enabled by the runtime enabled feature, for origin trials.
https://github.com/pythagoraskitty/shared-storage/blob/main/README.md

Name: kAutofillStructuredFieldsDisableAddressLines
Documentation:
If this feature is enabled, the AddressFieldParser does NOT try to parse
address lines once it has found a street name and house number or other
combinations of fields that indicate that an address form uses structured
addresses. This should be the default in all countries with fully supported
structured addresses. However, if a country is not sufficiently modeled,
autofill may still do the right thing if it recognizes "Street name, house
number, address line 2" as a sequence.
TODO(crbug.com/40266693) Remove once launched.

Name: kPrivateAggregationApi
Documentation: Enables the Private Aggregation API.

Name: kSearchEnginePreconnect2
Documentation: Enables a more efficient SearchEnginePreconnector

Name: kAutofillEnableNewFopDisplayDesktop
Documentation: When enabled, card and IBAN autofill will be shown in new FOP style.

Name: kCloseOmniboxPopupOnInactiveAreaClick
Documentation:
When enabled, clicks outside the omnibox and its popup will close an open
omnibox popup.

Name: kFencedFrames
Documentation:
Enable the <fencedframe> element; see crbug.com/1123606. Note that enabling
this feature does not automatically expose this element to the web, it only
allows the element to be enabled by the runtime enabled feature, for origin
trials.

Name: kWebAssemblyTiering
Documentation: Enable WebAssembly tiering (Liftoff -> TurboFan).

Name: kWebBluetoothAllowGetAvailabilityWithBfcache
Documentation:
When enabled, calling navigator.bluetooth.getAvailability() does not prevent
the frame from entering the back forward cache.

Name: kAutofillUnifyRationalizationAndSectioningOrder
Documentation:
If enabled, the ordering for rationalization and sectioning is the same for
server and heuristic predictions.
TODO(crbug.com/408497919): Remove when launched.

Name: kEnableLazyLoadImageForInvisiblePage
Documentation:
Whether to respect loading=lazy attribute for images when they are on
invisible pages.

Name: kRefreshExpirationDate
Documentation: Whether download expiration date will be refreshed on resumption.

Name: kResamplingScrollEventsExperimentalPrediction
Documentation:
Enables resampling of scroll events using an experimental latency of +3.3ms
instead of the original -5ms.

Name: kOnDeviceModelTestFeature
Documentation: Allow on-device model support for Test feature, to be used in tests.

Name: kFeedContainment
Documentation: Feature that enables feed containment.

Name: kHeavyAdInterventionWarning
Documentation:
Enables or disables reporting on the intervention that unloads ad iframes
with intensive resource usage.

Name: kAutofillEnableCvcStorageAndFillingEnhancement
Documentation:
When enabled, will enhance CVV storage project. Provide better suggestion,
resolve conflict with COF project and add logging.

Name: kDynamicColorGamut
Documentation:
When wide color gamut content from the web is encountered, promote our
display to wide color gamut if supported.

Name: kVaapiVideoMinResolutionForPerformance
Documentation:
Ensure the advertised minimum supported resolution is larger than or equal to
a given one (likely QVGA + 1) for certain codecs/modes and platforms, for
performance reasons. This does not affect JPEG decoding.

NOTE: This feature is default-enabled, but selectively disabled by tests
so they can test resolutions below the threshold.  See crbug.com/40650027

Name: kWebUsb
Documentation:
Controls whether the WebUSB API is enabled:
https://wicg.github.io/webusb

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessSendPreflights
Documentation:
Enables sending CORS preflight requests ahead of private network requests.
See: https://wicg.github.io/private-network-access/#cors-preflight

Name: kSafetyHubUnifiedPasswordsModule
Documentation: Enables the unified passwords module in Safety Hub.

Name: kEnableInteractiveOnlyADPFRenderer
Documentation:
If enabled, Chrome's ADPF(Android Dynamic Performance Framework) hint
session includes Renderer threads only if:
- The Renderer is handling an interacton
- The Renderer is the main frame's Renderer, and there no Renderers handling
  an interaction.

Name: kEnablePortBoundCookies
Documentation: Enables binding of cookies to the port that originally set them by default.

Name: kAccessibilityExposeSummaryAsHeading
Documentation:
Expose <summary>" as a heading instead of a button.
Two reasons to try this:
1. Unlike for a button, JAWS will not enforce leafiness for a heading, so
that things like child links will still be presented to the user.
2. The user can use heading navigation for summaries.
We may decide to scale this back for use cases such as a summary inside of
a table or a list.
Experiment until we validate the approach with ATs and ARIA WG.

Name: kSendCnameAliasesToSubresourceFilterFromBrowser
Documentation:
Enables or disables performing SubresourceFilter checks from the Browser
against any aliases for the requested URL found from DNS CNAME records.

Name: kOptimizationGuideUseContinueOnShutdownForPageContentAnnotations
Documentation:
Enables use of task runner with trait CONTINUE_ON_SHUTDOWN for page content
annotations on-device models.

Name: kRealboxMatchSearchboxTheme
Documentation:
If enabled, the NTP "realbox" will have same border/drop shadow in hover
state as searchbox.

Name: kAllowClientCertificateReportingForUsers
Documentation: Allows the reporting of client certificates for managed users.

Name: kUnloadBlocklisted
Documentation:
If enabled, the usage of unload handlers causes a blocklisted reason for
BFCache. The purpose is to capture their source location.

Name: kGPayAppDynamicUpdate
Documentation:
If enabled, the GooglePayPaymentApp handles communications between the native
GPay app and the browser for dynamic updates on shipping and payment data.

Name: kMediaDrmPreprovisioningAtStartup
Documentation:
Determines if MediaDrmOriginIdManager should attempt to pre-provision origin
IDs at startup (whenever a profile is loaded). Also used by tests that
disable it so that the tests can setup before pre-provisioning is done.
Note: Has no effect if kMediaDrmPreprovisioning feature is disabled.

Name: kSafetyHubAndroidSurvey
Documentation: Enables Safety Hub HaTS survey on Android.

Name: kNtpDriveModuleShowSixFiles
Documentation: If enabled, six files show in the NTP Drive module, instead of three.

Name: kHttpsFirstBalancedMode
Documentation:
Enables HTTPS-First Mode in a balanced configuration that doesn't warn on
HTTP when HTTPS can't be reasonably expected.

Name: kAudioFocusSessionGrouping
Documentation:
Enables Audio Focus grouping which means that multiple media sessions can
share audio focus at the same time provided that they have the same group id.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformDeviceSwitcher
Documentation: Feature flag for device switcher segment.

Name: kAutofillUseNegativePatternForAllAttributes
Documentation:
When enabled, the form field parser won't try to match other attributes if
any of the negative patterns matched.

Name: kWebAppSystemMediaControls
Documentation: Enables per PWA System Media Controls. Only supported on Windows and macOS.

Name: kLoadingPredictorPrefetchUseReadAndDiscardBody
Documentation:
Use the kURLLoadOptionReadAndDiscardBody option to URLLoader to avoid
unnecessarily copying response body data.

Name: kThrottleUnimportantFrameTimers
Documentation:
Throttles Javascript timer wake ups of unimportant frames (cross origin
frames with small proportion of the page's visible area and no user
activation) on foreground pages.

Name: kRestrictCloneParameters
Documentation:
When enabled, restrict clone to just flags used by fork and pthread_create on
android.

Name: kKeepAliveInBrowserMigration
Documentation:
Kill-switch for the fetch keepalive request infra migration.
If enabled, all keepalive requests will be proxied via the browser process.
Design Doc: https://bit.ly/chromium-keepalive-migration
Tracker: https://crbug.com/1356128

Name: kAutofillDisableFilling
Documentation: Kill switch for Autofill filling.

Name: kFedCmIdPRegistration
Documentation: Enables usage of the FedCM IdP Registration API.

Name: kV8VmFuture
Documentation: Enables future V8 VM features

Name: kInterestFeedV2
Documentation:
InterestFeedV2 takes precedence over InterestFeedContentSuggestions.
InterestFeedV2 is cached in ChromeCachedFlags. If the default value here is
changed, please update the cached one's default value in CachedFeatureFlags.

Name: kPushMessagingDisallowSenderIDs
Documentation: Feature flag to disallow creation of push messages with GCM Sender IDs.

Name: kDestroyProfileOnBrowserClose
Documentation:
Destroy profiles when their last browser window is closed, instead of when
the browser exits.

Name: kAndroidMediaPickerAdoption
Documentation: Controls how the Android Media Picker will be introduced.

Name: kOnDeviceModelFetchPerformanceClassEveryStartup
Documentation:
Whether performance class should be fetched each startup or just after a
version update.

Name: kWebRtcHideLocalIpsWithMdns
Documentation:
Causes WebRTC to replace host ICE candidate IP addresses with generated
names ending in ".local" and resolve them using mDNS.
http://crbug.com/878465

Name: kForceStartupSigninPromo
Documentation: Features to trigger the startup sign-in promo at boot.

Name: kGroupingFrameworkForNonZPS
Documentation:
Features that affect the "twiddle" step of AutocompleteController, e.g.,
deduping or `SortAndCull()`.

Name: kConsumeCompileHints
Documentation:
Load V8_COMPILE_HINTS optimization data from OptimizationGuide and
transmit it to V8. See `ProduceCompileHints` for the data producer side of
this feature.

Name: kUseCertTransparencyAwareApiForOsCertVerify
Documentation:
If enabled, Android OS's certificate verification (CertVerifyProcAndroid) is
done using the certificate transparency aware API.

Name: kSwipeToMoveCursor
Documentation: Android only feature, for swipe to move cursor.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformSignalDbCache
Documentation: Feature flag for turning of signal database cache.

Name: kAddTaskLeewayFeature
Documentation:
Under this feature, a non-zero leeway is added to delayed tasks. Along with
DelayPolicy, this affects the time at which a delayed task runs.

Name: kFencedFramesLocalUnpartitionedDataAccess
Documentation:
Controls functionality related to network revocation/local unpartitioned
data access in fenced frames.

Name: kSiteIsolationForPasswordSites
Documentation:
Controls a mode for dynamically process-isolating sites where the user has
entered a password.  This is intended to be used primarily when full site
isolation is turned off.  To check whether this mode is enabled, use
SiteIsolationPolicy::IsIsolationForPasswordSitesEnabled() rather than
checking the feature directly, since that decision is influenced by other
factors as well.

Name: kOpsDisplayScaleFactor
Documentation:
Open Pluggable Specification (OPS) is a special industry standard with
slot-in computing modules.

Name: kEnableCompose
Documentation: Controls whether the Compose feature is available

Name: kAutofillAcceptDomMutationAfterAutofillSubmission
Documentation:
If enabled, we start forwarding submissions with source
DOM_MUTATION_AFTER_AUTOFILL, even for non-password forms.

Name: kPlusAddressDeclinedFirstTimeCreateSurvey
Documentation: TODO: crbug.com/348139343 - Move back to components/plus_addresses.

Name: kStopInBackground
Documentation:
Freeze scheduler task queues in background after allowed grace time.
"stop" is a legacy name.

Name: kMediaLearningFramework
Documentation:
Enables the general purpose media machine learning framework. Adds reporting
only; does not change media behavior.

Name: kCustomizeChromeWallpaperSearch
Documentation:
If enabled, shows wallpaper search within the Customize Chrome Side Panel.
This is a kill switch. Keep indefinitely.

Name: kUserBypassFeedback
Documentation: Feature to enable the feedback button in the User Bypass UI.

Name: kSuppressIntermediateACUpdatesOnLowEndDevices
Documentation:
Prevents intermediate AutocompleteResult updates from being sent to Java on
low-end devices. This aims at eliminating time spent on constructing,
measuring, and laying out views that are about to be discarded, and reducing
the volume of JNI jumps.

Name: kFledgeAlwaysReuseBidderContext
Documentation: Reuse a single V8 context to generate all bids in a bidder worklet.

Name: kDelayAsyncScriptExecution
Documentation:
If enabled, async script execution will be delayed than usual.
See https://crbug.com/1340837.

As of 2023/11, this experiment enables kLCPCriticalPathPredictor.
See third_party/blink/common/loader/lcp_critical_path_predictor_util.cc

Name: kSplitCacheByCrossSiteMainFrameNavigationBoolean
Documentation:
This flag incorporates a boolean into the cache key that is true for
renderer-initiated main frame navigations when the request initiator site is
cross-site to the URL being navigated to. This provides protections against
certain cross-site leak attacks involving cross-site navigations.

Name: kAggressiveShaderCacheLimits
Documentation:
All features in alphabetical order. The features should be documented
alongside the definition of their values in the .cc file.

Name: kDedicatedMediaServiceThread
Documentation: Runs the media service in the GPU process on a dedicated thread.

Name: kVisitedURLRankingDeduplication
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling URL visit resumption deduplication.

Name: kDomainSuggestions
Documentation:
Feature to determine if the HQP should double as a domain provider by
suggesting up to the provider limit for each of the user's highly visited
domains.

Name: kJavaScriptImportAttributes
Documentation: Enables the `with` syntax for the Import Attributes proposal.

Name: kDisableSyncAutogeneratedSearchEngines
Documentation:
Switch guarding TemplateURL syncing of untouched autogenerated search
engines.

Name: kPlusAddressFullFormFill
Documentation:
When enabled, if the user has an existing plus address for the current
domain, address profile suggestions will be updated to reflect the plus
address email instead of the stored one. Note that only profile emails
matching the user's GAIA account will be replaced.

Name: kConsumeCodeCacheOffThread
Documentation: Controls off-thread code cache consumption.

Name: kCustomizeChromeWallpaperSearchButton
Documentation:
If enabled, shows entry point on Customize Chrome Side Panel's Appearance
page for Wallpaper Search.";

Name: kMediaOptimizer
Documentation:
Enable the prototype global optimization of tuneables via finch.  See
media/base/tuneable.h for how to create tuneable parameters.

Name: kMessagesAndroidExtraHistograms
Documentation: Feature that enables extra histogram recordings.

Name: kEnablePixPaymentsInLandscapeMode
Documentation:
When enabled, Chrome will offer to pay with accounts supporting Pix to users
using their devices in landscape mode. Chrome always offers to pay with Pix
accounts for users using their devices in portrait mode.

Name: kSplitCacheByIncludeCredentials
Documentation: Splits cache entries by the request's includeCredentials.

Name: kAutofillEnableAccountStorageForIneligibleCountries
Documentation:
When enabled, addresses of every country are considered eligible for account
address storage.

Name: kDisablePrivacySandboxPrompts
Documentation:
Disables any Privacy Sandbox related prompts. Should only be used for testing
purposes. This feature is used to support external automated testing using
Chrome, where additional prompts break behavior expectations.

Name: kBlockMidiByDefault
Documentation: Block all MIDI access with the MIDI_SYSEX permission

Name: kAutofillSkipSaveCardForTabModalPopup
Documentation:
Kill switch, when enabled, will prevent the display of the save card bubble
within a tab modal pop-up window.

Name: kSecurePaymentConfirmation
Documentation:
Browser-side feature flag for Secure Payment Confirmation (SPC) that also
controls the render side feature state. SPC is not currently available on
Linux or ChromeOS, as it requires platform authenticator support.

Name: kLogUrlScoringSignals
Documentation: Omnibox ML scoring.

Name: kCookieIndicesHeader
Documentation:
If enabled, then the network service will parse the Cookie-Indices header.
This does not currently control changing cache behavior according to the
value of this header.

Name: kWebUIBundledCodeCache
Documentation:
Enables build-time generated resource-bundled code caches for WebUI pages.
See crbug.com/375509504 for details.

Name: kSharedStorageTransactionalBatchUpdate
Documentation:
Enables transactional behavior for sharedStorage.batchUpdate(). This also
disallows the 'withLock' option for methods within batchUpdate().
https://wicg.github.io/shared-storage/#batch-update

Name: kAutofillPaymentsFieldSwapping
Documentation:
When enabled, focusing on a credit card number field that was traditionally
autofilled will yield all credit card suggestions.
TODO(crbug.com/354175563): Remove when launched.

Name: kFedCmFlexibleFields
Documentation:
Allow specifying subsets of "name", "picture", "email" in the fields API.
Requires FedCmAuthz to be enabled.

Name: kLensOverlayContextualSearchbox
Documentation: Enables the Lens overlay searchbox.

Name: kClientSideDetectionAcceptHCAllowlist
Documentation:
Expand allowlist usage beyond CSPP allowlist by using the high confidence
allowlist as well.

Name: kHttpsFirstBalancedModeAutoEnable
Documentation:
Automatically enables HTTPS-First Mode in a balanced configuration when
possible.

Name: kCombineNewWindowIPCs
Documentation:
When enabled, CreateNewWindow() and ShowCreatedWindow() mojo calls are
coalesced into a single call to CreateNewWindow().

Name: kSegmentationPlatformPowerUserFeature
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling Power user segmentation.

Name: kDestroySystemProfiles
Documentation:
DestroyProfileOnBrowserClose only covers deleting regular (non-System)
Profiles. This flags lets us destroy the System Profile, as well.

Name: kUseNewEncryptionKeyForWebData
Documentation:
If enabled, then an Encryptor will be requested that is not always backwards
compatible with OSCrypt Sync. On some platforms, this might mean a key is
used that is stored more securely, such as using App-Bound encryption on
Windows.
If this feature is enabled, any data stored by `WebDatabaseService` is not
guaranteed to be retrievable if OSCrypt Async is not used.

Name: kTimeoutTcpConnectAttempt
Documentation:
Enables a timeout on individual TCP connect attempts, based on
the parameter values.

Name: kMediaLearningSmoothnessExperiment
Documentation:
Enables the smoothness prediction experiment.  Requires
kMediaLearningFramework to be enabled also, else it does nothing.

Name: kDynamicMaxAutocomplete
Documentation:
Feature used to cap max suggestions to a dynamic limit based on how many URLs
would be shown. E.g., show up to 10 suggestions if doing so would display no
URLs; else show up to 8 suggestions if doing so would include 1 or more URLs.

Name: kPlusAddressOfferCreationOnAllNonUsernameFields
Documentation:
When enabled, plus address creation is offered on all email fields that are
not a username field - even if they are on a login form or a change password
form.
Intended as a killswitch to protect against unexpected behavior.
TODO: crbug.com/355398505 - clean up.

Name: kBlockCrossPartitionBlobUrlFetching
Documentation:
Please keep features in alphabetical order.
Enables blob URL fetches to fail when cross-partition.

Name: kWebBluetoothNewPermissionsBackend
Documentation:
Controls whether Web Bluetooth should use the new permissions backend. The
new permissions backend uses ObjectPermissionContextBase, which is used by
other device APIs, such as WebUSB. When enabled,
WebBluetoothWatchAdvertisements and WebBluetoothGetDevices blink features are
also enabled.

Name: kAAudioPerStreamDeviceSelection
Documentation:
Enables selection of audio devices for each individual AAudio stream instead
of using communication streams and managing the system-wide communication
route. This is not fully reliable on all Android devices.

Requires `UseAAudioDriver`, `UseAAudioInput`, and an Android API level >=
`AAUDIO_MIN_API`, otherwise it will have no effect.

Name: kCastVideoEncoderFrameDrop
Documentation: A video encoder is allowed to drop a frame in cast mirroring.

Name: kAutofillEnableFillingPhoneCountryCodesByAddressCountryCodes
Documentation:
Improves the selection of phone country codes by also considering address
country codes / names.
See GetStreetAddressForInput() in field_filling_address_util.cc for a details
description.
TODO(crbug.com/40249216). Clean up when launched.

Name: kEnablePreferencesAccountStorage
Documentation: Enables a separate account-scoped storage for preferences.

Name: kTranslate
Documentation:
This allows the user to disable translate by using the
`--disable-features=Translate` command-line flag.

Name: kDefaultTypedNavigationsToHttps
Documentation: Navigation experiments.

Name: kEnhancedSafeBrowsingPromo
Documentation: Enables Enhanced Safe Browsing promos for iOS.

Name: kDeleteExpiredDownloads
Documentation: Whether to delete expired download.

Name: kAutofillEnableFpanRiskBasedAuthentication
Documentation:
When enabled, server card retrieval will begin with a risk-based check
instead of jumping straight to CVC or biometric auth.

Name: kConfirmSuggestionRemovals
Documentation:
The features should be documented alongside the definition of their values in
the .cc file.

Name: kUseAAudioDriver
Documentation:
Enables loading and using AAudio instead of OpenSLES on compatible devices,
for audio output streams. This feature is disabled on ATV HDMI dongle devices
as OpenSLES provides more accurate output latency on those devices.

TODO(crbug.com/401365323): Remove this feature in the future.

Name: kPaintPreviewDemo
Documentation:
Used to enable a main menu item on Android that captures and displays a paint
preview for the current page. The paint preview UI will be dismissed on back
press and all associated stored files deleted. This intended to test whether
capturing and playing paint preview works on a specific site.

Name: kGCMDoNotIncreaseBackoffDelayOnNetworkChange
Documentation:
When enabled, the first connection attempt won't contribute to backoff
exponential delay. This will mitigate issues when there is no network
connection yet but a lot of network changes.

Name: kLoadingPhaseBufferTimeAfterFirstMeaningfulPaint
Documentation:
A feature to control whether the loading phase should be extended beyond
First Meaningful Paint by a configurable buffer.

Name: kClientHintsDPR_DEPRECATED
Documentation: Enable legacy `dpr` client hint.

Name: kComposeAutoSubmit
Documentation: Enables Auto-submit of compose with a valid selection.

Name: kOmniboxHistoryClusterProvider
Documentation:
Enables the `HistoryClusterProvider` to surface Journeys as a suggestion row
instead of an action chip. Enabling this won't actually disable
`kOmniboxAction` but for user experiments, the intent is to only have 1
enabled. `kJourneys` must also be enabled for this to take effect.

Name: kFledgeEnforcePermissionPolicyContributeOnEvent
Documentation:
Enable enforcement of permission policy for
privateAggregation.contributeToHistogramOnEvent.

Name: kMetricsReportingFeature
Documentation:
Metrics reporting feature. This feature, along with user consent, controls if
recording and reporting are enabled. If the feature is enabled, but no
consent is given, then there will be no recording or reporting.

Name: kSynchronousPageFlipTesting
Documentation:
Indicates whether DrmOverlayManager should used the synchronous API to
perform pageflip tests.

Name: kUseIDNA2008NonTransitional
Documentation:
If you add or remove a feature related to URLs, you may need to
correspondingly update the EarlyAccess allow list in app shims
(chrome/app_shim/app_shim_controller.mm). See https://crbug.com/1520386 for
more details.

Name: kNavigationConfidenceEpsilon
Documentation:
Controls the configurablity of the navigation confidence noise level.
If the feature is not enabled, then the epsilon value will be 1.1.

Name: kFeedNoViewCache
Documentation: When enabled, no view cache is used.

Name: kSpdySessionForProxyAdditionalChecks
Documentation:
Enables more checks when creating a SpdySession for proxy. These checks are
already applied to non-proxy SpdySession creations.
TODO(crbug.com/343519247): Remove this once we are sure that these checks are
not causing any problems.

Name: kAutofillEnableSaveAndFill
Documentation:
When enabled, the 'Save and Fill' suggestion will be offered in the credit
card dropdown menu for users who don't have any cards saved in Autofill.

Name: kLocalCompileHints
Documentation:
Cache information about which functions are compiled and use it for eager-
compiling those functions when the same script is loaded again.

Name: kMediaStreamTrackTransfer
Documentation: Allow cross-context transfer of MediaStreamTracks.

Name: kUseSecurityLevelWhenCheckingMediaDrmVersion
Documentation:
Specify the required security level for MediaDrm when checking the MediaDrm
version.

Name: kBrowsingTopicsParameters
Documentation:
Decoupled with the main `kBrowsingTopics` feature, so it allows us to
decouple the server side configs.

Name: kPrivateAggregationDebugReportingCookieDeprecationTesting
Documentation:
Enables Private Aggregation debug reporting to be enabled during the
third-party cookie deprecation experiment.

Name: kAllowMediaCodecSoftwareDecoder
Documentation:
Allow the media pipeline to prioritize the software decoder provided by
MediaCodec, instead of the built-in software decoders. This is only enabled
for platforms which shows worse performance when using the built-in software
decoders, e.g. Cast on ATV.

Name: kEnableGenericOidcAuthProfileManagement
Documentation: Controls whether the generic OIDC-response profile management is enabled.

Name: kAutofillAcrossIframesIos
Documentation: All features in alphabetical order.

Name: kClientSideDetectionShowLlamaScamVerdictWarning
Documentation:
Show a warning to the user based on the
IntelligentScanVerdict::SCAM_EXPERIMENT_VERDICT_2.

Name: kUseButtonTranslateBubbleUi
Documentation: This feature uses the existing UI for the Full Page Translate bubble.

Name: kSecurePaymentConfirmationUseCredentialStoreAPIs
Documentation:
Used to control whether SecurePaymentConfirmation is able to rely on OS-level
credential store APIs, or if it can only rely on the user-profile database.

Name: kClearSiteDataPrefetchPrerenderCache
Documentation:
If enabled, the Clear-Site-Data header will handle "prefetchCache" and
"prerenderCache" to clear the Prefetch and Prerender caches respectively.

Name: kWebRTCColorAccuracy
Documentation:
Inform webrtc with correct video color space information whenever
possible.

Name: kWebAuthnHybridLinking
Documentation:
Enables linking of hybrid devices to Chrome, both pre-linking (i.e. through
Sync) and through hybrid.

Name: kRedWarningSurvey
Documentation: Enables HaTS surveys for users encountering red warnings.

Name: kBackForwardCacheUnloadAllowed
Documentation:
Controls the interaction between back/forward cache and
unload. When enabled, pages with unload handlers may enter the
cache.

Name: kCodeBasedRBD
Documentation: Feature flag for Code-based RBD.

Name: kAutofillAiWithDataSchema
Documentation:
Enables the second iteration AutofillAI.
This feature is independent of `autofill_ai::kAutofillAi`.

Name: kUseNewAlpsCodepointHttp2
Documentation:
Enables using the new ALPS codepoint to negotiate application settings for
HTTP2.

Name: kMlUrlScoring
Documentation:
If enabled, runs the ML scoring model to assign new relevance scores to the
URL suggestions and reranks them.

Name: kSpdyHeadersToHttpResponseUseBuilder
Documentation: Enables a more efficient implementation of SpdyHeadersToHttpResponse().

Name: kBrowsingTopics
Documentation:
https://github.com/patcg-individual-drafts/topics
Kill switch for the Topics API.

Name: kTimedHTMLParserBudget
Documentation:
If enabled, the HTMLDocumentParser will use a budget based on elapsed time
rather than token count.

Name: kCastDeviceFilter
Documentation: Used in downstream code.

Name: kPreloadingConfig
Documentation:
This Feature allows configuring preloading features via a parameter string.
See content/browser/preloading/preloading_config.cc to see how to use this
feature.

Name: kMediaLearningExperiment
Documentation:
Enables experimental local learning for media. Used in the context of media
capabilities only. Adds reporting only; does not change media behavior.

Name: kPhoneHubStructuredMetrics
Documentation: Controls whether Phone Hub Structured Metrics is enabled or not.

Name: kJourneysImages
Documentation: Enables images for Journeys in UI.

Name: kVariableRefreshRateAvailable
Documentation:
This feature indicates that this device should have variable refresh rates
enabled by default if available. This overrides the default value of
|kEnableVariableRefreshRate|. This flag is added by cros-config and not
exposed in the chrome://flags UI.

Name: kNtpSharepointModule
Documentation: If enabled, sharepoint module will be shown.

Name: kShouldRequestConfigurationFile
kEnableIpProtectionProxy
Documentation: Enables custom proxy configuration for the IP Protection experimental proxy.

Name: kWebAppsEnableMLModelForPromotion
Documentation: ML Installability promotion flags and all the feature params.

Name: kPostFREFixMetricsReportingFeature
Documentation:
Same as |kMetricsReportingFeature|, but this feature is associated with a
different trial, which has different sampling rates. This is due to a bug
in which the old sampling rate was not being applied correctly. In order for
the fix to not affect the overall sampling rate, this new feature was
created. See crbug/1306481.

Name: kRecordLastUnsentLogMetadataMetrics
Documentation:
The feature to record the unsent log info metrics, refer to
UnsentLogStoreMetricsImpl::RecordLastUnsentLogMetadataMetrics.

Name: kLiveCaptionMultiLanguage
Documentation: Live Caption can be used in multiple languages, as opposed to just English.

Name: kRemoveWakeLockInDestructor
Documentation:
Enables removing wake locks in the WakeLock destructor if non-null. Serves as
killswitch while we roll out this functionality. TODO(crbug.com/349860794):
Remove this killswitch post-safe rollout.

Name: kUserLevelMemoryPressureSignalOn3GbDevices
Documentation: (for Android 3GB devices)

Name: kSharedStorageAPIEnableWALForDatabase
Documentation:
Enables WAL (write-ahead-logging) mode for the Shared Storage API SQLite
database backend.

Name: kSmartSuggestionForLargeDownloads
Documentation: Whether to enable smart suggestion for large downloads

Name: kEnableComposeSavedStateNotification
Documentation: Controls whether or not the saved state notification is shown.

Name: kPostMessageThirdPartyToFirstPartyDifferentBucketSameOriginBlocked
Documentation:
Whether third-party to first-party different-bucket same-origin post messages
are blocked.

Name: kSafetyHubAndroidSurveyV2
Documentation: Enables new triggers for the Safety Hub HaTS survey on Android.

Name: kViewTransitionCaptureAndDisplay
Documentation:
A mode of ViewTransition capture that does not display unstyled frame,
instead displays the properly constructed frame while at the same doing
capture.

Name: kVideoPictureInPictureControlsUpdate2024
Documentation: Displays new video picture-in-picture controls for the 2024 UI update.

Name: kAudioFocusDuckFlash
Documentation:
Enables flash to be ducked by audio focus. This is enabled on Chrome OS which
has audio focus enabled.

Name: kNtpModulesOrder
Documentation:
Dummy feature to set param "NtpModulesOrderParam".
This is used for an emergency Finch param. Keep indefinitely.

Name: kClearPrefForUnknownCountry
Documentation:
When an invalid `country_codes::CountryId` is stored in prefs and this
feature is enabled the pref will be cleared allowing a valid country to be
set again.

Name: kWebRtcUseMinMaxVEADimensions
Documentation: Instructs WebRTC to honor the Min/Max Video Encode Accelerator dimensions.

Name: kAudioServiceSandbox
Documentation:
Enables the audio-service sandbox. This feature has an effect only when the
kAudioServiceOutOfProcess feature is enabled.

Name: kPostponeOnLoginSuccessful
Documentation:
Enables postponing detecting a successful submission and showing the
save/update UI by a fixed time.

Name: kPushSubscriptionChangeEventOnInvalidation
Documentation:
Fires the `pushsubscriptionchange` event defined here:
https://w3c.github.io/push-api/#the-pushsubscriptionchange-event
for subscription refreshes, revoked permissions or subscription losses

Name: kDsePreload2
Documentation:
DefaultSearchEngine Preload v2
https://crbug.com/394988793

Name: kFilteringScrollPrediction
Documentation:
Enables filtering of predicted scroll events on compositor thread.
Uses the kFilterName* values in ui_base_features.h as the 'filter' feature
param.

Name: kLessAggressiveParkableString
Documentation:
Enables more conservative settings for ParkableString: suspend parking in
foreground, and increase aging tick intervals.

Name: kBFCacheOpenBroadcastChannel
Documentation: If enabled, open broadcast channels do not block back/forward cache.

Name: kTextSafetyClassifier
Documentation: Whether to download the text safety classifier model.

Name: kNoThrottlingVisibleAgent
Documentation: Don't throttle frames that are same-agent with with a visible frame.

Name: kAutofillEnableCacheForRegexMatching
Documentation:
When enabled, FormFieldParser::MatchesRegexWithCache tries to avoid
re-computing whether a regex matches an input string by caching the result.
The result size is controlled by
kAutofillEnableCacheForRegexMatchingCacheSizeParam.

Name: kCookieDeprecationFacilitatedTesting
Documentation:
Gate access to cookie deprecation API which allows developers to opt in
server side testing without cookies.
(See https://developer.chrome.com/en/docs/privacy-sandbox/chrome-testing)

Name: kServiceWorkerAutoPreload
Documentation:
Enables auto preloading for fetch requests before invoking the fetch handler
in ServiceWorker. The fetch request inside the fetch handler is resolved with
this preload response. If the fetch handler result is fallback, uses this
preload request as a fallback network request.

Unlike navigation preload, this preloading is applied to subresources. Also,
it doesn't require a developer opt-in.

crbug.com/1472634 for more details.

Name: kAndroidBrowserControlsInViz
Documentation:
During a scroll, enable viz to move browser controls according to the
offsets provided by the embedded renderer, circumventing browser main
involvement. For now, this applies only to top controls.

Name: kUseCnameAliasesForFingerprintingProtectionFilter
Documentation:
Toggle to enable CNAME alias checks. Enabling this feature will block URL
aliases matching fingerprinting protection filtering rules.

Name: kEnableADPFSeparateRendererMainSession
Documentation:
If enabled, Chrome puts Renderer Main threads into a separate
ADPF(Android Dynamic Performance Framework) hint session, and does not
report any timing hints from this session.

Name: kPrerender2MemoryControls
Documentation:
Enables restrictions on how much memory is required on a device to use
Prerender2. This is a separate feature from kPrerender2 so that the
restrictions can be disabled entirely to allow bots to run the tests without
needing to explicitly enable Prerender2, which some tests do not want to do
because they want to test the default behavior.

Name: kStorageQuotaSettings
Documentation: Enables customized storage quota settings for embedders.

Name: kNtpMostRelevantTabResumptionModuleFallbackToHost
Documentation:
If enabled, the Tab Resumption module will fallback to host url to find a
favicon if there are none locally available.

Name: kExperimentalContentSecurityPolicyFeatures
Documentation:
Content counterpart of ExperimentalContentSecurityPolicyFeatures in
third_party/blink/renderer/platform/runtime_enabled_features.json5. Enables
experimental Content Security Policy features ('navigate-to').

Name: kDocumentProviderPrimaryAccountRequirement
Documentation:
If enabled, the authentication requirement for Drive suggestions is based on
whether the primary account is available, i.e., the user is signed into
Chrome, rarther than checking if any signed in account is available in the
cookie jar.

Name: kPageVisibilityPageContentAnnotations
Documentation: Enables the page visibility model to be annotated on every page load.

Name: kFledgeBidderUseBalancingThreadSelector
Documentation:
Instead of using a hash to assign group-by-origin IGs to threads, use
a round robin on joining-origin while ensuring a maximum allowed imbalance
is respected.

Name: kV8ReduceConcurrentMarkingTasks
Documentation: Enables reduced number of concurrent marking tasks.

Name: kAllowMediaCodecCallsInSeparateProcess
Documentation:
This feature allows for some MediaDrm functions to be executed in a separate
process so that crashes do not bring down the browser. Flag is available so
that it can be disabled for WebView as separate processes are not allowed.

Name: kPlusAddressSuggestionsOnUsernameFields
Documentation:
When enabled, focusing on a username field will show plus address suggestion
alongside the autocomplete suggestions.
TODO(crbug.com/360791229): Remove when launched.

Name: kIsolateOrigins
Documentation:
Alternative to switches::kIsolateOrigins, for turning on origin isolation.
List of origins to isolate has to be specified via
kIsolateOriginsFieldTrialParamName.

Name: kCacheCodeOnIdle
Documentation:
When enabled, code cache is produced asynchronously from the script execution
(https://crbug.com/1260908).

Name: kAllowFileBufferSizeControl
Documentation: Whether to allow changing the size of file buffer.

Name: kNTPFooterBadgingPolicies
Documentation:
Enables the management notice in the NTP footer if the custom policies are
set. This acts as a kill switch for "EnterpriseCustomLabelForBrowser" and
"EnterpriseLogoUrlForBrowser".

Name: kOptimizationGuideModelDownloading
Documentation: Enables the downloading of models.

Name: kLoadingPredictorPrefetch
Documentation:
Modifies loading predictor so that it does prefetches of subresources instead
of preconnects.

Name: kSpeculativeImageDecodes
Documentation:
When enabled, some in-viewport images will initiate image decode immediately
upon load, rather than waiting for the next BeginMainFrame to trigger decode
as part of rasterization.

Name: kInstalledAppProvider
Documentation: Allow Windows specific implementation for the GetInstalledRelatedApps API.

Name: kCompareManagementInterface
Documentation:
Moves the table management interface from history to chrome://compare and
enables a new context menu for comparison tables under Bookmarks and Lists.

Name: kAvoidUnnecessaryBeforeUnloadCheckSync
Documentation:
Synchronously continuing with navigation can lead to trying to start another
navigation synchronously while the first navigation is still being processed
on the stack. This results in re-entrancy which is unsafe and triggers a
CHECK.

Embedders like Android WebView cannot guarantee that re-entrancy would never
occur - in particular, there are existing Android WebView apps that do the
problematic sync navigation. Hence Android WebView entirely disables this
feature via
ContentBrowserClient::SupportsAvoidUnnecessaryBeforeUnloadCheckSync().

The eventual goal of this feature flag is to make it possible to continue
navigation synchronously for some platforms
(See: https://crbug.com/396998476).

There are several modes that are described in the
AvoidUnnecessaryBeforeUnloadCheckSyncMode enum in the header file.

Name: kNavigationPredictorPrefetchHoldback
Documentation: Preconnects instead of prefetching from NavigationPredictor.

Name: kAutofillMoreProminentPopup
Documentation:
Controls autofill popup style, if enabled it becomes more prominent,
i.e. its shadow becomes more emphasized, position is also updated.
TODO(crbug.com/40235454): Remove once the experiment is over.

Name: kAlwaysBlock3pcsIncognito
Documentation: Privacy UX features start

Name: kScriptStreamingForNonHTTP
Documentation: Enables script streaming for non-http scripts.

Name: kEnableComposeOnDeviceDogfoodFooter
Documentation:
Controls whether to enable the dogfood footer when on device evaluation is
used.

Name: kUseSequencedTaskRunnerForMojoVEAProvider
Documentation: Use SequencedTaskRunner for MojoVideoEncodeAcceleratorProvider.

Name: kEnableOriginatingSavedGroupCleanUp
Documentation: Enables clean up of hidden groups.

Name: kDXGISwapChainPresentInterval0
Documentation:
Force a present interval of 0. This asks Windows to cancel the remaining time
on the previously presented frame instead of synchronizing with vblank(s).
Frames may be discarded if they are presented more frequently than one per
vblank.

Name: kPrivacySandboxAttestationsLoadFromAPKAsset
Documentation:
Allow the Privacy Sandbox Attestations component to load the pre-installed
attestation list from Android APK assets.

Name: kNumNtpZpsRecentSearches
Documentation: Omnibox suggestions tuning

Name: kMostVisitedTilesHorizontalRenderGroup
Documentation:
If enabled, makes Most Visited Tiles a Horizontal render group.
Horizontal render group decomposes aggregate suggestions (such as old Most
Visited Tiles), expecting individual AutocompleteMatch entry for every
element in the carousel.

Name: kOrcaUseProdServer
Documentation: Enables Orca Prod Server

Name: kReplaceSyncPromosWithSignInPromos
Documentation: Feature flag to replace all sync-related UI with sign-in ones.

Name: kV8Sparkplug
Documentation:
Enables Sparkplug compiler. Note that this only sets the V8 flag when
manually overridden; otherwise it defers to whatever the V8 default is.

Name: kAdblockPlusFeature
Documentation: Controls whether ad-blocking feature is enabled.

Name: kNtpFooter
Documentation: If enabled, a footer will show on the NTP.

Name: kFileHandlingIcons
Documentation: File handling icons. https://crbug.com/1218213

Name: kEnableIPv6ReachabilityOverride
Documentation:
If enabled, overrides IPv6 reachability probe results based on the system's
IP addresses.

Name: kCertificateTransparencyAskBeforeEnabling
Documentation:
Enables Certificate Transparency on Desktop and Android Browser (CT is
disabled in Android Webview, see aw_browser_context.cc).
Enabling CT enforcement requires maintaining a log policy, and the ability to
update the list of accepted logs. Embedders who are planning to enable this
should first reach out to chrome-certificate-transparency@google.com.
On builds where CT is enabled, this flag is also used as an emergency kill
switch.

Name: kFledgeDoSampleDebugReportForTesting
Documentation:
Force sampling of forDebuggingOnly reports, for testing purpose. This flag
will always be disabled by default, and will only be enabled in some tests,
or manually enabling it in command for manual testing such as B&A's end to
end test of forDebuggingOnly sampling.

Name: kThrottleUnimportantFrameRate
Documentation:
When enabled, the begin frame rate of visible unimportant frames would be
reduced to half of normal frame rate.

Name: kNtpShortcuts
Documentation:
If enabled, shortcuts will be shown.
This is a kill switch. Keep indefinitely.

Name: kPrefetchBumpNetworkPriorityAfterBeingServed
Documentation:
Enabling this will bupm net::RequestPriority once after the running prefetch
starts to be served.

Name: kStorageAccessApiFollowsSameOriginPolicy
Documentation:
When enabled, the Storage Access API follows the Same Origin Policy when
including cookies on network requests. (I.e., a cross-site cookie is only
included via the Storage Access API if the request's URL's origin [not site]
has opted into receiving cross-site cookies.)

Name: kNtpDriveModuleNoSyncRequirement
Documentation: If enabled, the NTP Drive module does not require sync.

Name: kClientSideDetectionVibrationApi
Documentation:
Expand CSPP beyond phishing and trigger when vibration API is called on the
web page.

Name: kFailedLoginDetectionBasedOnResourceLoadingErrors
Documentation:
Marks form submission as failed whenever a POST request has failed for the
same iframe with 400-403 status code.

Name: kFledgeEnableSampleDebugReportOnCookieSetting
Documentation:
Decide whether to enable forDebuggingOnly report sampling based on user's
third party cookie setting.

Name: kReclaimResourcesDelayedFlushInBackground
Documentation:
When LayerTreeHostImpl::ReclaimResources() is called in background, trigger a
additional delayed flush to reclaim resources.

Enabled 03/2024, kept to run a holdback experiment.

Name: kAdjustLocalHistoryZeroSuggestRelevanceScore
Documentation: Local history zero-prefix (aka zero-suggest) and prefix suggestions.

Name: kPruneOldTransferCacheEntries
Documentation:
Prune transfer cache entries not accessed recently. This also turns off
similar logic in cc::GpuImageDecodeCache which is the largest (often single)
client of transfer cache.

Name: kFileSystemAccessPersistentPermissions
Documentation: Alphabetical:

Name: kAutofillAddressUserPerceptionSurvey
Documentation:
Feature flag to control the displaying of an ongoing hats survey that
measures users perception of Autofill. Differently from other surveys,
the Autofill user perception survey will not have a specific target
number of answers where it will be fully stop, instead, it will run
indefinitely. A target number of full answers exists, but per quarter. The
goal is to have a go to place to understand how users are perceiving autofill
across quarters.

Name: kNtpCalendarModule
Documentation: If enabled, calendar module will be shown.

Name: kEGLDualGPURendering
Documentation:
Allow dual GPU rendering through EGL where supported, i.e., allow a WebGL
or WebGPU context to be on the high performance GPU if preferred and Chrome
internal rendering to be on the low power GPU.

Name: kTouchDragAndContextMenu
Documentation:
This feature allows touch dragging and a context menu to occur
simultaneously, with the assumption that the menu is non-modal.  Without this
feature, a long-press touch gesture can start either a drag or a context-menu
in Blink, not both (more precisely, a context menu is shown only if a drag
cannot be started).

Name: kUserRemoteCommands
Documentation: Controls whether user remote command is enabled.

Name: kForceMigrateSyncingUserToSignedIn
Documentation:
If enabled in addition to `kMigrateSyncingUserToSignedIn`, then all users
with Sync-the-feature enabled are migrated, at browser startup, to the
signed-in non-syncing state. I.e. this bypasses the "eligibility"
requirements.

Name: kDiagnostics
Documentation: Controls various Omnibox Diagnostics features.

Name: kUIPumpImprovementsWin
Documentation:
Under this feature, the Windows UI pump uses a WaitableEvent to wake itself
up when not in a native nested loop. It also uses different control flow,
calling Win32 MessagePump functions less often.

Name: kExcludeLargeBodyReports
Documentation:
Enables exclusion of reports having large body during serialized reports.
When enabled, report bodies exceeding kMaxReportBodySizeKB are omitted. This
helps prevent excessively large reports json stringification.

Name: kAutofillPopupZOrderSecuritySurface
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/334909042): Remove after cleanup.
If the feature is enabled, the Autofill popup widget is initialized with
`Widget::InitParams::z_order` set to `ui::ZOrderLevel::kSecuritySurface`,
otherwise the `z_order` is not set and defined by the widget type (see
`Widget::InitParams::EffectiveZOrderLevel()`). This param makes the popup
display on top of all other windows, which potentially can negatively
affect their functionality.

Name: kMediaLogToConsole
Documentation:
Enables sending MediaLog to the log stream, which is useful for easier
development by ensuring logs can be seen without a remote desktop session.
Only affects builds when DCHECK is on for non-ERROR logs (ERROR logs are
always sent to the log stream). Enabled by default on Android and ChromeOS.

Name: kNotificationScheduleService
Documentation: The feature to enable NotificationScheduleService.

Name: kCopyImageFilenameToClipboard
Documentation: Whether to write filename to the clipboard when copying image downloads.

Name: kDeferImplInvalidation
Documentation:
When enabled, the scheduler will allow deferring impl invalidation frames
for N frames (default 1) to reduce contention with main frames, allowing
main a chance to commit.

Name: kUseMLKEM
Documentation:
Causes TLS 1.3 connections to use the ML-KEM standard instead of the Kyber
draft standard for post-quantum key-agreement. Post-quantum key-agreement
must be enabled (e.g. via kPostQuantumKyber) for this to have an effect.

TODO(crbug.com/40910498): Remove this flag sometime after M131 has reached
stable without issues.

Name: kLoadingOnlyLearnHighPriorityResources
Documentation:
Modifies loading predictor so that it only learns about subresources and
origins that are high priority.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformMostVisitedTilesUser
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling MostVisitedTilesUser segment.

Name: kThirdPartyProfileManagement
Documentation: Controls whether third-party profile management is enabled.

Name: kLogSodaLoadFailures
Documentation:
Logs a DumpWithoutCrashing() call each time the Speech On-Device API (SODA)
fails to load. Used to diagnose issues when rolling out new versions of the
SODA library.

Name: kIPHDemoMode
Documentation: A feature for enabling a demonstration mode for In-Product Help (IPH).

Name: kComposeRequestLatencyTimeout
Documentation: Enables client-side timeout of a Compose request.

Name: kAutoplayDisableSettings
Documentation: Whether we should show a setting to disable autoplay policy.

Name: kDiscardInputEventsToRecentlyMovedFrames
Documentation:
These values are used to implement a browser intervention: if a cross-origin
iframe has moved more than {param:distance} device independent pixels
(manhattan distance) within its embedding page's viewport within the last
{param:time_ms} milliseconds, most input events targeting the iframe will be
quietly discarded.

Name: kDetectHiDpiForMsaa
Documentation: Use 4x MSAA (vs 8) on High DPI screens.

Name: kAutofillAndroidDisableSuggestionsOnJSFocus
Documentation:
Controls whether user tap on an element is needed to show autofill
suggestions. If enabled, this flag would disable android autofill suggestions
if the focus on an element is Javascript-originated.
DidReceiveLeftMouseDownOrGestureTapInNode() will show suggestions if the
focus change occurred as a result of a gesture. See crbug.com/730764 for why
showing autofill suggestions as a result of JavaScript changing focus is
enabled on WebView.
TODO(crbug.com/40286775) Clean up autofill feature flag
`kAutofillAndroidDisableSuggestionsOnJSFocus`

Name: kShutdownForFailedChannelCreation
Documentation:
Remove gpu process reference if gpu context is loss, and gpu channel cannot
be established due to said gpu process exiting.

Name: kCollaborationEntrepriseV2
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling collaboration in entreprise v2.

Name: kBackForwardCacheNonStickyDoubleFix
Documentation:
Enables the fix for a bug that prevents caching of pages for the second time.
TODO(https://crbug.com/360183659): Remove this after measuring the impact.

Name: kDnsTransactionDynamicTimeouts
Documentation:
Support for altering the parameters used for DNS transaction timeout. See
ResolveContext::SecureTransactionTimeout().

Name: kAllowUnmutedAutoplayForTWA
Documentation:
Kill switch for allowing TWAs to autoplay with sound without requiring a user
gesture to unlock, for parity with PWAs.

Name: kBatchMainThreadReleaseCallbacks
Documentation:
When enabled, ClientResourceProvider will take callbacks intended to be ran
on the Main-thread, and will batch them into a single jump to that thread.
Rather than each performing its own separate post task.

Enabled 03/2024, kept to run a holdback experiment.

Name: kFillOnAccountSelect
Documentation:
Enables the experiment for the password manager to only fill on account
selection, rather than autofilling on page load, with highlighting of fields.

Name: kCreateNotificationsAcceptedClientSafeBrowsingReports
Documentation:
Creates and sends CSBRRs when notification permissions are accepted for an
abusive site whose interstitial has been bypassed.

Name: kFedCmAlternativeIdentifiers
Documentation:
Support usernames and phone numbers to identify users, instead of
(or in addition to) names and emails.

Name: kPrivacySandboxRelatedWebsiteSetsUi
Documentation: Enables showing new RWS UI.

Name: kPowerBookmarkBackend
Documentation: Controls the power bookmarks backend.

Name: kLCPCriticalPathPredictor
Documentation:
When enabled, LCP critical path predictor will optimize the subsequent visits
to websites using performance hints collected in the past page loads.
It enables boosting a loading priority of the possible LCP element.
TODO(crbug.com/1419756): rename to represent this is for possible LCP entry
boost.

Name: kHardwareSecureDecryptionFallback
Documentation:
Allows automatically disabling hardware secure Content Decryption Module
(CDM) after failures or crashes to fallback to software secure CDMs. If this
feature is disabled, the fallback will never happen and users could be stuck
in playback failures.

Name: kSyncSecurityDomainBeforePINRenewal
Documentation:
When enabled, a sync with the Security Domain Service is performed before a
GPM PIN renewal.

Name: kBackForwardCacheTimeToLiveControl
Documentation:
Enables controlling the time to live for pages in the BackForwardCache.
The time to live is defined by the param 'time_to_live_seconds'; if this
param is not specified then this feature is ignored and the default is used.

Name: kDefaultSiteInstanceGroups
Documentation:
When enabled, puts non-isolated sites in separate SiteInstances in a default
SiteInstanceGroup (per BrowsingInstance), rather than sharing a default
SiteInstance.

Name: kHighPriorityDatabaseTaskType
Documentation: Enable setting high priority database task type from field trial parameters.

Name: kNoVarySearchIgnoreUnrecognizedKeys
Documentation:
If enabled, unrecognized keys in a No-Vary-Search header will be ignored.
Otherwise, unrecognized keys are treated as if the header was invalid.

Name: kRenderMutedAudio
Documentation: Controls whether muted media stream audio should continue to render.

Name: kLensOverlayMGTInSidePanel
Documentation: Enables opening the Lens overlay MGT feature in the side panel.

Name: kAllowCrossOriginNotRestoredReasons
Documentation: Feature to allow exposing cross-origin subframes' NotRestoredReasons.

Name: kV8PerFrameMemoryMonitoring
Documentation: Enables or disables per-frame memory monitoring.

Name: kDisableGeoLanguageModel
Documentation:
When enabled this feature will disable the GeoLanguage model and default the
user to the fluent language model.

Name: kSuspendMutedAudio
Documentation:
Disables the real audio output stream after silent audio has been delivered
for too long. Should save quite a bit of power in the muted video case.

Name: kClearUndecryptablePasswordsOnSync
Documentation: Delete undecryptable passwords from the store when Sync is active.

Name: kBackForwardCacheUnblockPermissionRequest
Documentation:
Enables or disables whether pages with pending permission requests will
go into back/forward cache.

Name: kThreadedBodyLoader
Documentation: If enabled, reads and decodes navigation body data off the main thread.

Name: kLimitAImageReaderMaxSizeToOne
Documentation:
Used to limit AImageReader max queue size to 1 since many devices especially
android Tv devices do not support more than 1 images.

Name: kAccessibilityManageBroadcastReceiverOnBackground
Documentation:
Enables posting registering, unregistering the broadcast receiver to the
background thread.

Name: kLinkPreview
Documentation:
Enables the Link Preview.
Tracking bug: go/launch/4269184

Name: kLimitLayerMergeDistance
Documentation:
When enabled, PaintArtifactCompositor::Layerizer will limit the distance
(in number of non-mergeable intermediate PendingLayers) between merged
layers to kLayerMergeDistanceLimit, to reduce the cost of layerization.

Name: kSharedStorageWorkletSharedBackingThreadImplementation
Documentation:
If enabled, the shared storage worklet threads (on the same renderer process)
will share the same backing thread; otherwise, each will own a dedicated
backing thread.

Name: kTruncateBodyToContentLength
Documentation: Enables truncating the response body to the content length.

Name: kHistoryPagePromoCtaStringVariation
Documentation:
Makes the History Page history opt-in promo use a different CTA String.
No-op unless "HistoryPageHistorySyncPromo" is enabled.

Name: kAdInterestGroupAPIRestrictedPolicyByDefault
Documentation:
Runtime flag that changes default Permissions Policy for features
join-ad-interest-group and run-ad-auction to a more restricted EnableForSelf.

Name: kNtpDummyModules
Documentation:
If enabled, dummy modules will be shown.
This is a development switch. Keep indefinitely.

Name: kMemorySaverModeRenderTuning
Documentation: Enables v8 memory saver mode on low memory thresholds.

Name: kForceThirdPartyCookieBlocking
Documentation: Enables enabling third-party cookie blocking from the command line.

Name: kDisableProcessReuse
Documentation:
When enabled, OOPIFs will not try to reuse compatible processes from
unrelated tabs.

Name: kSafetyHubAbusiveNotificationRevocation
Documentation: Automatically revoke abusive notifications in Safety Hub.

Name: kIgnoreInputWhileHidden
Documentation:
When enabled all input arriving will be ignored, and the dispatcher will be
notified that the event was not consumed. With the exception of when there
is an attached Dev Tools session, during which input will be dispatched even
if we are hidden.

Name: kEnableExperimentalWebAssemblyJSPI
Documentation: Enable WebAssembly JSPI.

Name: kOverrideAndroidOmniboxSpareRendererDelay
Documentation:
Override the delay to create a spare renderer when the omnibox is focused
on Android.

Name: kTrackingProtectionContentSettingUbControl
Documentation: Enables UserBypass to set/reset TRACKING_PROTECTION content settings.

Name: kTouchpadOverscrollHistoryNavigation
Documentation:
Allows swipe left/right from touchpad change browser navigation. Currently
only enabled by default on CrOS and Windows.

Name: kEnableNudgeForUnspecifiedHint
Documentation: Default nudge allow/deny decision for unspecified hint.

Name: kClearGrShaderDiskCacheOnInvalidPrefix
Documentation:
When enabled, Grshader disk cache will be cleared on startup if any cache
entry prefix does not match with the current prefix. prefix is made up of
various parameters like chrome version, driver version etc.

Name: kPrerender2MainFrameNavigation
Documentation:
Enables the same-origin main frame navigation in a prerendered page.
See https://crbug.com/1239281.

Name: kUpdatePaymentDetailsIntentFilterInPaymentApp
Documentation:
If enabled, PaymentRequest looks up the UPDATE_PAYMENT_DETAILS intent filter
in the payment app.

Name: kMirrorBackForwardGesturesInRTL
Documentation:
Flip the back/forward direction of navigation gestures when the UI language
is an RTL language.

Name: kPrivacyGuideForceAvailable
Documentation:
Force Privacy Guide to be available even if it would be unavailable
otherwise. This is meant for development and test purposes only.

Name: kPdfEnforcements
Documentation:
Enables additional ChildProcessSecurityPolicy enforcements for PDF renderer
processes, including blocking storage and cookie access for them.

TODO(https://crbug.com/40205612): Remove this kill switch once the PDF
enforcements are verified not to cause problems.

Name: kAndroidHubSearchTabGroups
Documentation: (Android only) Show tab groups via the search feature in the hub.

Name: kAutofillUseINAddressModel
Documentation: Enables using a custom address model for India, overriding the legacy one.

Name: kTextFragmentAnchor
Documentation: Enable text snippets in URL fragments. https://crbug.com/919204.

Name: kVisitedURLRankingDecorations
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling URL visit resumption decorators.

Name: kIgnoreHSTSForLocalhost
Documentation: If enabled, ignore Strict-Transport-Security for [*.]localhost hosts.

Name: kAutofillDisambiguateContradictingFieldTypes
Documentation:
If enabled, new heuristics are applied for disambiguating multiple possible
types in a form field. Otherwise, only the already established heuristic for
disambiguating address and credit card names is used.

Name: kWebAppEnableUpdateTokenParsing
Documentation:
A feature to enable using the update token in the manifest or icon url
changes to detect app updates. When this is enabled, automatic icon
downloading is disabled.

Name: kImprovedPasswordChangeService
Documentation: Enables improvements to password change functionality.

Name: kNoReferrerForPreloadFromSubresource
Documentation: Kill switch for https://crbug.com/415810136.

Name: kSyncIncreaseNudgeDelayForSingleClient
Documentation:
If enabled, the local change nudge delays for single-client users are
increased by some factor, specified via the FeatureParam below.

Name: kOptimizationGuidePredictionModelKillswitch
Documentation:
An emergency kill switch feature to stop serving certain model versions per
optimization target. This is useful in exceptional situations when a bad
model version got served that lead to crashes or critical failures, and an
immediate remedy is needed to stop serving those versions.

Name: kAutofillDisableSilentProfileUpdates
Documentation:
If enabled, Autofill will not apply silent updates to the structure of
addresses and names. This feature is mostly for debugging and testing
purposes and is not supposed to be launched.

Name: kAdaptiveButtonInTopToolbarCustomizationV2
Documentation: Alphabetical:

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessForNavigations
Documentation:
Enables Private Network Access checks for navigations.

The exact checks run are the same as for document subresources, and depend on
the state of other Private Network Access feature flags:
 - `kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequests`
 - `kPrivateNetworkAccessSendPreflights`
 - `kPrivateNetworkAccessRespectPreflightResults`

Name: kGeoLanguage
Documentation:
Controls whether the GeoLanguage system is enabled. GeoLanguage uses IP-based
coarse geolocation to provide an estimate (for use by other Chrome features
such as Translate) of the local/regional language(s) corresponding to the
device's location. If this feature is disabled, the GeoLanguage provider is
not initialized at startup, and clients calling it will receive an empty list
of languages.

Name: kAutofillEnableAmountExtractionAllowlistDesktop
Documentation:
When enabled, Chrome will have the ability to load and query the allowlist
for checkout amount extraction, which will be used to check if the current
URL is eligible for products that use the checkout amount extraction
algorithm.

Name: kForcedColors
Documentation: Used to enable forced colors mode for web content.

Name: kAutofillDeepLinkAutofillOptions
Documentation: If enabled, other apps can open the Autofill Options in Chrome.

Name: kPromoBrowserCommands
Documentation: Enables executing the browser commands sent by the NTP promos.

Name: kSecPurposePrefetchHeaderRelPrefetch
Documentation:
If enabled, prefetches from rel="prefetch" will be sent with the
Sec-Purpose: "prefetch" header.

Name: kDeferSpeculativeRFHCreation
Documentation:
Enables deferring the creation of the speculative RFH when the navigation
starts. The creation of a speculative RFH consumes about 2ms and is blocking
the network request. With this feature the creation will be deferred until
the browser initializes the network request. The speculative RFH will be
created while the network service is sending the request in parallel.

Name: kFedCmCooldownOnIgnore
Documentation: Enables cooldown on ignore in FedCM API.

Name: kComposeAllowOnDeviceExecution
Documentation: Enables on-device execution, if available.

Name: kMediaCodecBlockModel
Documentation: Enables block model (LinearBlock) on supported devices.

Name: kWebRTCHardwareVideoEncoderFrameDrop
Documentation: A hardware video encoder is allowed to drop a frame in WebRTC.

Name: kForceProduceCompileHints
Documentation:
For forcing producing compile hints independent of the platform and
kProduceCompileHintsDataProductionLevel.

Name: kAutoApproveSharedPasswordUpdatesFromSameSender
Documentation:
When enabled, updates to shared existing passwords from the same sender are
auto-approved.

Name: kFledgeDelayPostAuctionInterestGroupUpdate
Documentation:
Enables a delay for the post-auction interest group update to avoid
immediately invalidating cached values.

Name: kPaintHolding
Documentation: Enable defer commits to avoid flash of unstyled content, for all navigations.

Name: kTFLiteLanguageDetectionEnabled
Documentation: Controls whether the TFLite-based language detection is enabled.

Name: kEnableDrDcVulkan
Documentation:
This flag is use additionally with kEnableDrDc to enable the feature for
vulkan enabled android devices.

Name: kMediaCapabilitiesWithParameters
Documentation: Enable Media Capabilities with finch-parameters.

Name: kAutofillEnableCardBenefitsForAmericanExpress
Documentation:
When enabled, card benefits offered by American Express will be shown in
Payments Autofill UI.

Name: kResumeHeavyUserSegmentFeature
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling categorization into resume heavy user.

Name: kEnterpriseProfileBadgingPolicies
Documentation:
Enables enterprise profile badging for managed profiles on the toolbar avatar
and in the profile menu when the policies are set. This acts as a kill
switch. This has no effect if `kEnterpriseProfileBadging` is enabled.

Name: kRetainOmniboxOnFocus
Documentation:
Whether the contents of the omnibox should be retained on focus as opposed to
being cleared. When this feature flag is enabled and the omnibox contents are
retained, focus events will also result in the omnibox contents being fully
selected so as to allow for easy replacement by the user. Note that even with
this feature flag enabled, only large screen devices with an attached
keyboard and precision pointer will exhibit a change in behavior.

Name: kVideoBlitColorAccuracy
Documentation: Inform video blitter of video color space.

Name: kFeedPerformanceStudy
Documentation:
When enabled, depending on params selected, enable different
performance-oriented features in Feed.

Name: kVisitedURLRankingHistoryVisibilityScoreFilter
Documentation: Feature flag to disable History visibility score filter.

Name: kEnableReportingFromUnmanagedDevices
Documentation:
TODO(b/281905099): remove after rolling out reporting managed user events
from unmanaged devices

Name: kMerchantTrust
Documentation: Enables the merchant trust section for Page Info.

Name: kClipboardSuggestionContentHidden
Documentation: Suggestions UI - these affect the UI or function of the suggestions popup.

Name: kExemptSpeculationRulesHeaderFromCSP
Documentation:
Controls if the file loaded via the Speculation-Rules header
is exempt from CSP checks. See crbug.com/371595744 for context.

Name: kDocumentProviderNoSyncRequirement
Documentation:
If enabled, the requirement to be in an active Sync state is removed and
Drive suggestions are available to all clients who meet the other
requirements.

Name: kPriceInsights
Documentation: Feature flag for Price Insights.

Name: kLCPPMultipleKey
Documentation: If enabled, LCPP learns with additional first-level-path key to origin.

Name: kHashPrefixRealTimeLookupsSamplePing
Documentation:
Send sample hash-prefix real-time lookups for real-time lookups to catch
"false positives" where real-time lookup says safe but hash-prefix lookup
says unsafe.
Check the design doc (go/sample-esb-ping-send-hprt) for further
details.

Name: kLiveCaptionRightClick
Documentation: Enable or disable Live Caption from the right click menu.

Name: kSkipUndecryptablePasswords
Documentation:
Displays at least the decryptable and never saved logins in the password
manager

Name: kImageServiceSuggestPoweredImages
Documentation: Enabled the capability by default, can be used as a killswitch.

Name: kDefaultEnableGpuRasterization
Documentation:
Enable GPU Rasterization by default. This can still be overridden by
--enable-gpu-rasterization or --disable-gpu-rasterization.
DefaultEnableGpuRasterization has launched on Mac, Windows, ChromeOS,
Android and Linux.

Name: kClientHintsDeviceMemory_DEPRECATED
Documentation:
We do intend to deprecate these when possible, do not remove the feature
until they can be disabled by default.

Name: kIgnoreBubblingCollisionIfSourceDevicesMismatch
Documentation: Flag guard for fix for crbug.com/346629231.

Name: kTopLevelTpcdOriginTrial
Documentation: Controls consideration of top-level 3PCD origin trial settings.

Name: kMaliciousApkDownloadCheck
Documentation: Enables ClientDownloadRequests for APK downloads on Android.

Name: kSyncAutofillLoyaltyCard
Documentation: Enables syncing of Loyalty Cards coming from Google Wallet.

Name: kV8FlushCodeBasedOnTabVisibility
Documentation: Enables code flushing based on tab visibility.

Name: kIdbDecompressValuesInPlace
Documentation:
This flag controls behavior that decompresses
`IDBValue::data_` directly into a buffer that's passed by ownership to
`SerializedScriptValue`.

 * For values that are not compressed, this flag has no effect: `data_` is
 always copied on conversion to a script value.
 * For values that are compressed,
   * Normally `data_` will be decompressed the first time it's serialized,
   overwriting `data_`, and *copied* into `SerializedScriptValue` the first
   time and every subsequent time one is created.
   * When this flag is enabled, `data_` will be decompressed *directly into*
   a buffer that's passed off to `SerializedScriptValue`, which avoids a copy
   and the memory overhead that entails. However this will happen every time
   the value is deserialized, so if that happens more than once, the
   decompression routine must run more than once.

Name: kBrowsingTopicsBypassIPIsPubliclyRoutableCheck
Documentation:
If enabled, the check for whether the IP address is publicly routable will be
bypassed when determining the eligibility for a page to be included in topics
calculation. This is useful for developers to test in local environment.

Name: kWebRtcH265L1T2
Documentation:
When enabled, allows H.265 L1T2 to be used for sending WebRTC streams, if the
accelerator reports support of encoding in L1T2.

Name: kFledgeBidderWorkletThreadPool
Documentation: Enables multi-threaded bidder worklet.

Name: kNetworkQualityEstimatorWebHoldback
Documentation:
Puts network quality estimate related Web APIs in the holdback mode. When the
holdback is enabled the related Web APIs return network quality estimate
set by the experiment (regardless of the actual quality).

Name: kBatchResourceRelease
Documentation:
When enabled, ClientResourceProvider will allow for the batching of
callbacks. So that the client can perform a series of individual releases,
but have ClientResourceProvider coordinate the callbacks. This allows all of
the Main-thread callbacks to be batched into a single jump to that thread.

When disabled each callback will perform its own separate post task.

Name: kSCTAuditingHashdance
Documentation:
SCT auditing hashdance allows Chrome clients who are not opted-in to Enhanced
Safe Browsing Reporting to perform a k-anonymous query to see if Google knows
about an SCT seen in the wild. If it hasn't been seen, then it is considered
a security incident and uploaded to Google.

Name: kExtensionManifestV3NetworkSpeechSynthesis
Documentation: Extension manifest v3 migration for network speech synthesis.

Name: kOverscrollHistoryNavigation
Documentation: History navigation in response to horizontal overscroll (aka gesture-nav).

Name: kHeliumArcvmKiosk
Documentation: Enables Kiosk session for the Helium android app.

Name: kEvictionUnlocksResources
Documentation:
When enabled, ClientResourceProvider will attempt to unlock and delete
TransferableResources that have been returned as a part of eviction.

Enabled by default 03/2014, kept to run a holdback experiment.

Name: kSandboxExternalProtocolBlocked
Documentation:
Gates sandboxed iframe navigation toward external protocol behind any of:
- allow-top-navigation
- allow-top-navigation-to-custom-protocols
