- allow-top-navigation-with-user-gesture (+ user gesture)
- allow-popups

Motivation:
Developers are surprised that a sandboxed iframe can navigate and/or
redirect the user toward an external application.
General iframe navigation in sandboxed iframe are not blocked normally,
because they stay within the iframe. However they can be seen as a popup or
a top-level navigation when it leads to opening an external application. In
this case, it makes sense to extend the scope of sandbox flags, to block
malvertising.

Implementation bug: https://crbug.com/1253379
I2S: https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/g/blink-dev/c/-t-f7I6VvOI

Enabled in M103. Flag to be removed in M106

Name: kLensSearchProtectedPage
Documentation: Enables the protected error page in the Lens side panel.

Name: kVaapiWebPImageDecodeAcceleration
Documentation:
Controls the decode acceleration of WebP images in Chrome OS using the
VA-API.
TODO(gildekel): remove or enable by default in Chrome OS once
https://crbug.com/877694 is resolved.

Name: kWebAuthnICloudKeychainForGoogle
Documentation:
These five feature flags control whether iCloud Keychain is the default
mechanism for platform credential creation in different situations.
"Active" means that the user is an active user of the profile authenticator,
defined by having used it in the past 31 days. "Drive" means that the user
is currently signed into iCloud Drive, which isn't iCloud Keychain
(what's needed), but the cloest approximation that we can detect.

Name: kLocalWebApprovalsWidgetSupportsUrlPayload
Documentation:
Whether the Pacp widget can process a url payload as part of the local
approval request.

Name: kKillPartitionAllocMemoryTagging
Documentation:
Kill switch for memory tagging. Skips any code related to memory tagging when
enabled.

Name: kPostMessageFirstPartyToThirdPartyDifferentBucketSameOriginBlockedIfStorageIsPartitioned
Documentation:
Whether first-party to third-party different-bucket same-origin post messages
are blocked when storage partitioning is enabled.

Name: kLogOnDeviceMetricsOnStartup
Documentation:
Whether the on device service is launched after a delay on startup to log
metrics.

Name: kPreconnectFromKeyedService
Documentation: Feature to control preconnect to search.

Name: kTrustedTypesFromLiteral
Documentation: Enable TrustedTypes .fromLiteral support.

Name: kSyncReuploadBookmarks
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/40780588): remove the feature toggle once most of bookmarks
have been reuploaded.

Name: kAutofillCreditCardUserPerceptionSurvey
Documentation: Same as `kAutofillAddressUserPerceptionSurvey` but for credit card forms.

Name: kSetIntervalWithoutClamp
Documentation:
If enabled, calling setInterval(..., 0) will not clamp to 1ms.
Tracking bug: https://crbug.com/402694.

Name: kFeedStreaming
Documentation: Feature that enables feed streaming.

Name: kFetchChangePasswordUrl
Documentation: Enables fetching of change-password urls on startup or later on demand.

Name: kMetricsTracingCalculationReduction
Documentation:
Currently CC Metrics does a lot of calculations for UMA and Tracing. While
Traces themselves won't run when we are not tracing, some of the calculation
work is done regardless. When enabled this feature reduces extra calculation
to when tracing is enabled.

Name: kServiceWorkerStaticRouterStartServiceWorker
Documentation:
(crbug.com/1371756): When enabled, the static routing API starts
ServiceWorker when the routing result of a main resource request was network
fallback.

Name: kCPUMeasurementInFreezingPolicy
Documentation: When enabled, the freezing policy measures background CPU usage.

Name: kDirectCompositionLetterboxVideoOptimization
Documentation:
Adjust the letterbox video size and position to the center of the screen so
that DWM power optimization can be turned on.

Name: kEnableComposeSavedStateNudge
Documentation: Controls whether or not the saved state nudge is enabled.

Name: kDontSendKeyEventsToJavascript
Documentation:
When enabled, this feature prevent blink sending key event to web unless it
is on installed PWA.

Name: kClearCanvasResourcesInBackground
Documentation:
When a LayerTreeHostImpl is not visible, clear its transferable resources
that haven't been imported into viz.

Name: kHappinessTrackingSurveysForComposeAcceptance
Documentation: Enables or disables the Happiness Tracking System for Compose acceptance.

Name: kLocalIpAddressInEvents
Documentation:
Adds local IP address field to security-sensitive events reported to
chrome://safe-browsing. These events are triggered when the reporting policy
is enabled for managed devices or profiles.

Name: kAutocompleteDictionaryPreload
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, SearchPrefetchService will send a request to
the network service to preload shared dictionary from the disk storage for
the AutocompleteResult's `destination_url`.

Name: kReleaseResourceDecodedDataOnMemoryPressure
Documentation: Whether `blink::Resource` deletes its decoded data on memory pressure.

Name: kIdbPrioritizeForegroundClients
Documentation: See crbug.com/359623664

Name: kListAllDisplayModes
Documentation:
This features allows listing all display modes of external displays in the
display settings and setting any one of them exactly as requested, which can
be very useful for debugging and development purposes.

Name: kDevToolsPrivacyUI
Documentation: When enabled, the DevTools Privacy UI is displayed.

Name: kAllowWindowDragUsingSystemDragDrop
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/40598679): Remove this when the tab dragging
interactive_ui_tests pass on Wayland.

Name: kLiveTranslate
Documentation: Live Translate translates captions generated by Live Caption.

Name: kBuiltInHlsMP4
Documentation:
This feature enables the buildin hls player to play and demux additional
media containers, including Fragmented and unfragmented MP4, as well as
raw AAC bytestreams. It does nothing if kBuiltInHlsPlayer is disabled.

Name: kWebAuthnAndroidUsePasskeyCache
Documentation:
Use the passkey cache service parallel to the FIDO2 module to retrieve
passkeys from GMSCore. This is for comparison only.

Name: kCaptureJSExecutionLocation
Documentation:
Whether to capture the source location of JavaScript execution, which is one
of the renderer eviction reasons for Back/Forward Cache.

Name: kHistoryClustersNavigationContextClustering
Documentation:
Enables context clustering to be performed at navigation time rather than in
batches.

Name: kHttpCacheNoVarySearch
Documentation: Whether or not to apply No-Vary-Search processing in the HTTP disk cache.

Name: kPrefetchClientHints
Documentation: If enabled, prefetches may include client hints request headers.

Name: kAsyncFullscreenWindowState
Documentation: If enabled, fullscreen window state is updated asynchronously.

Name: kClientSideDetectionShowScamVerdictWarning
Documentation:
Show a warning to the user that factors in the IntelligentScanVerdict from
ClientPhishingResponse.

Name: kWebRtcH265L1T3
Documentation:
When enabled, allows H.265 L1T3 to be used for sending WebRTC streams, if the
accelerator reports support of encoding in L1T3. If this is enabled, L1T2 is
also implied to be enabled.

Name: kDontAlwaysPushPictureLayerImpls
Documentation:
When enabled we stop always pushing PictureLayerImpl properties on
tree Activation. See crbug.com/40335690.

Name: kMaxZeroSuggestMatches
Documentation:
Num suggestions - these affect how many suggestions are shown based on e.g.
focus, page context, provider, or URL v non-URL.

Name: kPartitionAllocDisableBRPInBufferPartition
Documentation:
An apparent quarantine leak in the buffer partition unacceptably
bloats memory when MiraclePtr is enabled in the renderer process.
We believe we have found and patched the leak, but out of an
abundance of caution, we provide this toggle that allows us to
wholly disable MiraclePtr in the buffer partition, if necessary.

TODO(crbug.com/40064499): this is unneeded once
MiraclePtr-for-Renderer launches.

Name: kBrowserSignalsReportingEnabled
Documentation:
Enables the addition of device signals fields to Browser-level Chrome
Reports.

Name: kFledgeAlwaysReuseSellerContext
Documentation: Reuse a single V8 context to score all ads in a seller worklet.

Name: kClientSideDetectionSendLlamaForcedTriggerInfo
Documentation:
Pass the LlamaTriggerRuleInfo from RTLookupResponse to ClientPhishingRequest
if it exists and the force request mechanism occurs.

Name: kLiveCaptionWebAudio
Documentation: Enable or disable Live Caption support for WebAudio.

Name: kMaskedDomainList
Documentation:
When enabled, the requests in a third party context to domains included in
the Masked Domain List Component will use the Privacy Proxy to shield the
client's IP.

Name: kCategoricalSuggestions
Documentation: Adds support for categorical suggestion type.

Name: kLoadingPredictorLimitPreconnectSocketCount
Documentation:
If this is enabled, LoadingPredictor restricts the number of preconnects for
the same destination to one.

Name: kPartialLowEndModeOnMidRangeDevices
Documentation:
Used to enable LowEndDeviceMode partially on Android and ChromeOS mid-range
devices. Such devices aren't considered low-end, but we'd like experiment
with a subset of low-end features to see if we get a good memory vs.
performance tradeoff.

TODO(crbug.com/40264947): |#if| out 32-bit before launching or going to
high Stable %, because we will enable the feature only for <8GB 64-bit
devices, where we didn't ship yet. However, we first need a larger
population to collect data.

Name: kFeatureManagementLiveTranslateCrOS
Documentation:
FeatureManagement gate for Live Translate on ChromeOS devices. No impact
outside of CrOS.

Name: kLimitOpenUDPSockets
Documentation:
Enables a process-wide limit on "open" UDP sockets. See
udp_socket_global_limits.h for details on what constitutes an "open" socket.

Name: kLensOverlayLatencyOptimizations
Documentation: Enables the Lens overlay optimizations.

Name: kPlusAddressAndroidOpenGmsCoreManagementPage
Documentation:
When enabled, the user is shown the GMS core plus address management activity
instead of the web page in a Chrome custom tab.

Name: kFluentScrollbar
Documentation:
Fluent scrollbars aim to modernize the Chromium scrollbars (both overlay and
non-overlay) to fit the Fluent design language. For now, the feature will
only support the Windows and Linux platforms. The feature is currently in
development and disabled by default.

Name: kPrerender2DisallowNonTrustworthyHttp
Documentation:
If enabled, disallows non-trustworthy plaintext HTTP prerendering.
See https://crbug.com/340895233 for more details.

Name: kCollaborationAutomotive
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling collaboration on automotive.

Name: kKeyboardAccessibleTooltip
Documentation:
Used to enable keyboard accessible tooltips in in-page content
(i.e., inside Blink). See
::views::features::kKeyboardAccessibleTooltipInViews for
keyboard-accessible tooltips in Views UI.

Name: kVSyncDecoding
Documentation:
Feature flag for driving decoding with the Metronome by VSyncs instead of by
timer.

Name: kCriticalClientHint
Documentation:
Enables support for the `Critical-CH` response header.
https://github.com/WICG/client-hints-infrastructure/blob/master/reliability.md#critical-ch

Name: kAutofillUploadCardRequestTimeout
Documentation: When enabled, adds a timeout on the network request for UploadCard requests.

Name: kAccessibilityPdfOcrForSelectToSpeak
Documentation:
Enable PDF OCR for Select-to-Speak. It will be disabled by default on
platforms other than ChromeOS as STS is available only on ChromeOS.

Name: kWebAuthnUseInsecureSoftwareUnexportableKeys
Documentation:
Use insecure software unexportable keys to authenticate to the enclave.
For development purposes only.

Name: kV8TurboFastApiCalls
Documentation: Enables fast API calls in TurboFan.

Name: kImageLoadingPrioritizationFix
Documentation:
If enabled, a fix for image loading prioritization based on visibility is
applied. See https://crbug.com/1369823.

Name: kLensOverlaySurvey
Documentation: Enables the Lens overlay HaTS survey.

Name: kStarterPackIPH
Documentation:
Enables an informational IPH message at the bottom of the Omnibox directing
users to certain starter pack engines.

Name: kUIEnableSharedImageCacheForGpu
Documentation:
Enables shared image cache for gpu used by CC instances instantiated for UI.
TODO(https://crbug.com/c/1378251): this shall also be possible to use by
renderers.

Name: kEnableBandAPrivateAggregation
Documentation: Enable parsing private aggregation contributions from B&A response.

Name: kRealboxUseGoogleGIcon
Documentation:
If enabled, the real search box ("realbox") on the New Tab page will show a
Google (g) icon instead of the typical magnifying glass (aka loupe).

Name: kTreatNullIPAsPublicAddressSpace
Documentation:
This feature enables treating 0.0.0.0/8 as the public address space instead
of private or local. This is a killswitch for a tightening of a loophole in
Private Network Access. See https://crbug.com/40058874.

Name: kPreviewsResourceLoadingHintsSpecificResourceTypes
Documentation: Enable limiting previews loading hints to specific resource types.

Name: kToastFramework
Documentation: Base feature

Name: kDefaultANGLEMetal
Documentation: Default to using ANGLE's Metal backend.

Name: kMarkAllCredentialsAsLeaked
Documentation:
Marks all submitted credentials as leaked, useful for testing of a password
leak dialog.

Name: kPrivateAggregationApiDebugModeRequires3pcEligibility
Documentation:
Controls whether third-party cookie eligibility should be queried before
allowing debug mode to be used by a context. If enabled, any
`enableDebugMode()` calls in a context that does not have third-party cookie
eligibility will essentially have no effect. This feature has no effect on
debug mode if `blink::features::kPrivateAggregationApiDebugModeEnabledAtAll`
is disabled.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformPasswordManagerUser
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling password manager user segment.

Name: kFeedSignedOutViewDemotion
Documentation: Feature that enables signed-out view demotion.

Name: kStrictOriginIsolation
Documentation:
Controls whether site isolation should use origins instead of scheme and
eTLD+1.

Name: kSlopBucket
Documentation:
Enable the use of extra memory to cache response body data when the render
process is slow to read from the mojo data pipe.

Name: kHttpsFirstModeForAdvancedProtectionUsers
Documentation: Kill switch for crbug.com/1414633.

Name: kReloadHiddenTabsWithCrashedSubframes
Documentation:
Causes hidden tabs with crashed subframes to be marked for reload, meaning
that if a user later switches to that tab, the current page will be
reloaded.  This will hide crashed subframes from the user at the cost of
extra reloads.

Name: kGetDisplayMediaScreenScaleFactor
Documentation:
Makes getDisplayMedia take into account the device's scale factor
to compute screen sizes in calls without size constraints.

Name: kSRIMessageSignatureEnforcement
Documentation:
Should SRI-compliant HTTP Message Signatures be enforced?
https://wicg.github.io/signature-based-sri/

Name: kOnDeviceNotificationContentDetectionModel
Documentation:
Killswitch for fetching and executing the notification content detection
model. This also gates logging metrics related to this model.

Name: kAutofillEnableSecurityTouchEventFilteringAndroid
Documentation:
Controls if Chrome Autofill UI surfaces ignore touch events if something is
fully or partially obscuring the Chrome window.

Name: kCookieSameSiteConsidersRedirectChain
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, redirected requests will be considered
cross-site for the purpose of SameSite cookies if any redirect hop was
cross-site to the target URL, even if the original initiator of the
redirected request was same-site with the target URL (and the
site-for-cookies).
See spec changes in https://github.com/httpwg/http-extensions/pull/1348

Name: kAdTagging
Documentation:
Enables the tagging of ad frames and resource requests by using the
subresource_filter component in dry-run mode.

Name: kRecordFreezingEligibilityUKM
Documentation: When enabled, the freezing eligibility UKM event may be recorded.

Name: kInitImageDecodeLastUseTime
Documentation:
When enabled, fix bug where an image decode cache entry last use timestamp is
initialized to 0 instead of now.

Name: kFledgeNumberBidderWorkletGroupByOriginContextsToKeep
Documentation:
If kFledgeNumberBidderWorkletGroupByOriginContextsToKeep is enabled,
kFledgeNumberBidderWorkletGroupByOriginContextsToKeepValue sets the number of
previously-used group-by-origin contexts to keep in case they can be reused
in a bidder worklet. Defaulted to 1.

Name: kSupportMappableSharedImageOverMojo
Documentation:
Serves as killswitch for rolling out Mappable SharedImage mojom support.
TODO(crbug.com/40263579): Eliminate post safe rollout.

Name: kPrefetchParameterFix
Documentation:
Kill switch to revert the fix of using assistedQueryStats for prefetch source
component. See crbug.com/345275145.

Name: kChangeDiskCacheSizeExperiment
Documentation:
Experiment to increase the cache size to see the impact on various
performance metrics.

Name: kModelQualityLogging
Documentation: Kill switch for disabling model quality logging.

Name: kGlobalMediaControls
Documentation: Show toolbar button that opens dialog for controlling media sessions.

Name: kRealboxCr23Theming
Documentation:
If enabled, NTP "realbox" will be themed for CR23. Includes realbox
matching omnibox theme and increased realbox shadow.

Name: kUseSurfaceLayerForVideoDefault
Documentation:
Hardcoded as disabled for WebView to have a different default for
UseSurfaceLayerForVideo from chrome.

Name: kRemovalOfIWAsFromTabCapture
Documentation:
This flag enables the removal of IWAs surface captures from Chrome Tabs
category in getDisplayMedia() API. When disabled, IWAs surface captures
show both in Chrome Tabs and Windows.

Name: kEstablishGpuChannelAsync
Documentation:
Enables establishing the GPU channel asnchronously when requesting a new
layer tree frame sink.

Name: kUseNewEncryptionMethod
Documentation: Enables new encryption method of OSCrypt inside LoginDatabase (Stage 2).

Name: kAutofillUseFRAddressModel
Documentation:
Enables using a custom address model for France, overriding the legacy one.
TODO(crbug.com/347859030): Delete after M139.

Name: kFledgeDisableLocalAdsAuctions
Documentation: Feature flag to disable locally hosted ad auction.

Name: kClientSideDetectionRedirectChainKillswitch
Documentation: Killswitch for force request redirect chain check.

Name: kPartitionAllocLargeThreadCacheSize
Documentation: Use a larger maximum thread cache cacheable bucket size.

Name: kReportBottomOverscrolls
Documentation: Reports bottom overscrolls on the web page.

Name: kNtpMobilePromo
Documentation: Feature to control the display of a mobile promo on the NTP.

Name: kWebAssemblyLazyCompilation
Documentation: Enable WebAssembly lazy compilation (JIT on first call).

Name: kFlexOrgManagementDisclosure
Documentation:
Enables showing the email of the flex org admin that setup CBCM in the
management disclosures.

Name: kNotificationTelemetry
Documentation:
Enable the collection of Notification Telemetry to track potentially abusive
notifications.

Name: kCastStreamingMediaVideoEncoder
Documentation: TODO(crbug.com/282984511): Remove after M151.

Name: kAutofillUseNLAddressModel
Documentation:
Enables using a custom address model for the Netherlands, overriding the
legacy one.

Name: kDetectInconsistentPageImpl
Documentation:
Enable detecting inconsistency in the `PageImpl` used in the auction. Abort
the auction when detected.

Name: kSafetyHubMagicStack
Documentation: Enables Safety Hub card in magic stack.

Name: kOnDeviceModelPerformanceParams
Documentation:
Allows setting feature params for model download configuration, such as
minimum performance class for download.

Name: kMediaRecorderHEVCSupport
Documentation: Enables HEVC MediaRecorder muxer support.

Name: kAImageReaderMediaPlayer
Documentation: Use android AImageReader when playing videos with MediaPlayer.

Name: kAccessibilityDeprecateTypeAnnounce
Documentation:
When enabled, TYPE_ANNOUNCE events will no longer be sent for live regions in
the web contents.

Name: kDeferRendererTasksAfterInput
Documentation:
If enabled, some task queues are disabled between a discrete input event and
the subsequent frame. Which task types are deferrable depends on the
`TaskDeferralPolicy`.

Name: kHEVCRextCodecStringParsing
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/40232176): Remove after rollout.
Allow parsing HEVC range extension codec string.

Name: kMHTML_Improvements
Documentation: Improvements to MHTML for more accurate snapshots.

Name: kAutofillEnableExpirationDateImprovements
Documentation:
Enables a couple of improvements to credit card expiration date handling:
- The autocomplete attribute values are rationalized with format strings
  like MM/YY from placeholders and labels in mind.
- more fill follow.
TODO(crbug.com/40266396): Remove once launched.

Name: kHttpsFirstModeIncognitoNewSettings
Documentation:
Changes the binary opt-in to HTTPS-First Mode with a tri-state setting (HFM
everywhere, HFM in Incognito, or no HFM) with HFM-in-Incognito the new
default setting. This feature is dependent on kHttpsFirstModeIncognito.

Name: kSpareRendererForSitePerProcess
Documentation:
Controls whether SpareRenderProcessHostManager tries to always have a warm
spare renderer process around for the most recently requested BrowserContext.
This feature is only consulted in site-per-process mode.

Name: kPostDelayedTaskFocusTab
Documentation: Delay focusTab to prioritize navigation (https://crbug.com/374852568).

Name: kV8FlushEmbeddedBlobICache
Documentation: Enables flushing of the instruction cache for the embedded blob.

Name: kPartitionAllocDanglingPtr
Documentation: See /docs/dangling_ptr.md

Name: kRelatedWebsitePartitionAPI
Documentation:
Enables the Related Website Partition API, allowing members of a Related
Website Set to access partitioned non-cookie storage. See
https://github.com/explainers-by-googlers/related-website-partition-api.

Name: kWebOtpCrossDeviceSimpleString
Documentation:
Shows only the remote device name on the Android notification instead of
a descriptive text.

Name: kSharedStorageSelectURLLimit
Documentation:
If enabled, limits the number of times per origin per pageload that
`sharedStorage.selectURL()` is allowed to be invoked.

Name: kAllowURNsInIframes
Documentation:
Enables URN URLs like those produced by FLEDGE auctions to be displayed by
iframes (instead of requiring fenced frames). This is only intended to be
enabled as part of the FLEDGE origin trial.

Name: kAvoidTrustedParamsCopies
Documentation: Avoids copying ResourceRequest::TrustedParams when possible.

Name: kOomIntervention
Documentation: Enables or disables the OOM intervention.

Name: kAutofillDisableProfileUpdates
Documentation:
If enabled, Autofill will not apply updates to address profiles based on data
extracted from submitted forms. This feature is mostly for debugging and
testing purposes and is not supposed to be launched.

Name: kTextBasedAudioDescription
Documentation: Turn on browser vocalization of 'descriptions' tracks.

Name: kClientAutomatedTest
Documentation:
Feature used in the tast tests to let the server know that the events are
coming from an automated client test. Only used in tast tests.

Name: kHappinessTrackingSurveysForComposeNudgeClose
Documentation: Enables or disables the Happiness Tracking System for nudge dismissal.

Name: kAndroidCancelPermissionPromptOnTouchOutside
Documentation: Alphabetical:

Name: kPostMessageThirdPartyToFirstPartyDifferentBucketSameOriginBlockedIfStorageIsPartitioned
Documentation:
Whether third-party to first-party different-bucket same-origin post messages
are blocked when storage partitioning is enabled.

Name: kWebPayments
Documentation: The JavaScript API for payments on the web.

Name: kSensitiveContentWhileSwitchingTabs
Documentation:
When enabled, the tab switching surfaces will be redacted if they offer a
preview of a tab with sensitive content. The feature works only on Android
API level >= 35.
TODO(crbug.com/371547489): Clean up when launched.

Name: kPrefetchServiceWorker
Documentation: Allow prefetching ServiceWorker-controlled URLs.

Name: kWaitForLateScrollEvents
Documentation:
Currently there is a race between OnBeginFrames from the GPU process and
input arriving from the Browser process. Due to this we can start to produce
a frame while scrolling without any input events. Late arriving events are
then enqueued for the next VSync.

When this feature is enabled we will use the corresponding mode definted by
`kScrollEventDispatchModeParamName`.

Name: kClientSideDetectionNotificationPrompt
Documentation:
Expand CSD-Phishing beyond phishing and trigger when a notification prompt
occurs on the page.

Name: kLensOverlayTranslateButton
Documentation: Enables the Lens overlay translate button.

Name: kHeavyAdIntervention
Documentation:
Enables or disables the intervention that unloads ad iframes with intensive
resource usage.

Name: kProduceCompileHints2
Documentation: Data producer side for the V8 Crowdsourced Compile hints feature.

Name: kNtpBackgroundImageErrorDetection
Documentation:
If enabled, NTP background image links will be checked for HTTP status
errors."

Name: kTextSafetyScanLanguageDetection
Documentation:
Whether to scan the full text when running the language detection in the text
safety classifier.

Name: kAutofillEnableCvcStorageAndFilling
Documentation:
When enabled, we will store CVC for both local and server credit cards. This
will also allow the users to autofill their CVCs on checkout pages.

Name: kMainRepaintScrollPrefersNewContent
Documentation:
Sets raster tree priority to NEW_CONTENT_TAKES_PRIORITY when performing a
unified scroll with main-thread repaint reasons.

Name: kByDateHistoryInSidePanel
Documentation: If enabled, the by date history will show in the side panel.

Name: kVerifyQWACs
Documentation:
If enabled, server certificates that successfully verify and that identify
as QWACs will be verified against the 1-QWAC specification as well.

Name: kUserMediaCaptureOnFocus
Documentation:
If enabled, GetUserMedia API will only work when the concerned tab is in
focus

Name: kAudioServiceLaunchOnStartup
Documentation: Launches the audio service on the browser startup.

Name: kZeroSuggestPrefetchDebouncing
Documentation:
Enables the use of a request debouncer to throttle the number of ZPS prefetch
requests initiated over a given period of time (to help minimize the
performance impact of ZPS prefetching on the remote Suggest service).

Name: kPasswordLeakToggleMove
Documentation:
Enable movement of password leak toggle out of standard protection and into
its own section.

Name: kPushMessagingGcmEndpointEnvironment
Documentation:
Feature flag to control which environment |kPushMessagingGcmEndpoint|
corresponds to.

Name: kInputPredictorTypeChoice
Documentation:
This flag is used to set field parameters to choose predictor we use when
kResamplingInputEvents is disabled. It's used for gathering accuracy metrics
on finch and also for choosing predictor type for predictedEvents API without
enabling resampling. It does not have any effect when the resampling flag is
enabled.

Name: kEnableComposeProactiveNudge
Documentation: Controls whether or not the proactive nudge is enabled.

Name: kAckOnSurfaceActivationWhenInteractive
Documentation:
If enabled, we immediately send acks to clients when a viz surface
activates. This effectively removes back-pressure. This can result in wasted
work and contention, but should regularize the timing of client rendering.

Name: kTrackCurrentShaders
Documentation:
Track current program's shaders at glUseProgram() call for crash report
purpose. Only effective on Windows because the attached shaders may only
be reliably retrieved with ANGLE backend.

Name: kPlusAddressesEnabled
Documentation: Controls the enabled/disabled state of the experimental feature.

Name: kDlpRegionalizedEndpoints
Documentation:
Sends the WebProtect content scanning request to the corresponding regional
DLP endpoint based on ChromeDataRegionSetting policy.

Name: kNtpModulesDragAndDrop
Documentation: If enabled, modules will be able to be reordered via dragging and dropping

Name: kWebAuthnEnclaveAuthenticatorDelay
Documentation: Send enclave requests with 5 seconds delay. For development purposes only.

Name: kAccessibilityBlockFlowIterator
Documentation:
A replacement algorithm for AbstractInlineTextBox + InlineCursor for
AXInlineTextBox creation.

Name: kOnDeviceClusteringBlocklists
Documentation: Specifies various blocklists for on-device clustering backend.

Name: kSyncAlwaysForceImmediateStartIfTransportDataMissing
Documentation:
If enabled, sync-the-transport will auto-start (avoid deferring startup) if
sync metadata isn't available (i.e. initial sync never completed).

Name: kAccessibilityOnScreenMode
Documentation:
Enable the experimental on-screen AXMode .
TODO(accessibility): Only turn on the experimental On-Screen mode for when
screen readers are not running. This is an experimental mode for now, so this
is fine for now.

Name: kWebAppEnableScopeExtensionsBySite
Documentation:
Controls scope extensions feature in web apps. Enables parsing of "site"
entries in "scope_extensions" field in web app manifests. See explainer for
more information:
https://github.com/WICG/manifest-incubations/blob/gh-pages/scope_extensions-explainer.md

Name: kPartitionConnectionsByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Partitions connections and other network states based on the
NetworkAnonymizationKey associated with a request.
See https://github.com/MattMenke2/Explainer---Partition-Network-State.

Name: kPrivateAggregationApiProtectedAudienceAdditionalExtensions
Documentation:
Adds some additional functionality (new reserved event types, base values)
to things enabled by
kPrivateAggregationApiEnabledInProtectedAudience.

Name: kHeadlessLiveCaption
Documentation: Enable experimental headless captions.

Name: kEnableResumableUploadOnConsumerScan
Documentation: Controls whether resumable upload is enabled on consumer scans.

Name: kDXGIWaitableSwapChain
Documentation: Use waitable swap chain on Windows to reduce display latency.

Name: kRecordMediaEngagementScores
Documentation:
Enables Media Engagement Index recording. This data will be used to determine
when to bypass autoplay policies. This is recorded on all platforms.

Name: kDownloadWarningSurvey
Documentation:
Enables HaTS surveys for users encountering desktop download warnings on the
download bubble or the downloads page.

Name: kEnableCanvas2DLayers
Documentation: Enables canvas 2d methods BeginLayer and EndLayer.

Name: kFetchDestinationJsonCssModules
Documentation:
Use "style" and "json" destinations for CSS and JSON modules.
https://crbug.com/1491336

Name: kStaticKeyPinningEnforcement
Documentation: Controls whether static key pinning is enforced.

Name: kClientSideDetectionLlamaForcedTriggerInfoForScamDetection
Documentation:
Inquire the on device model when the forced llama trigger info in
RTLookupResponse asks to scan the page.

Name: kWebRtcAllowWgcWindowCapturer
Documentation:
When enabled we will tell WebRTC that we want to use the
Windows.Graphics.Capture API based window capturer, if it is available.

Name: kAutofillEnableSyncingOfPixBankAccounts
Documentation:
When enabled, Pix bank accounts are synced from Chrome Sync backend and
stored in the local db.

Name: kClientHintsViewportWidth_DEPRECATED
Documentation: Enable legacy `viewport-width` client hint.

Name: kUseDisplaySDRMaxLuminanceNits
Documentation:
When enabled, SDR maximum luminance nits of then current display will be used
as the HDR metadata NDWL nits.

Name: kAndroidAutofillDeprecateAccessibilityApi
Documentation:
If enabled, autofill calls are never falling back to the accessibility APIs.
This feature is meant to be enabled after AutofillVirtualViewStructureAndroid
which provides alternative paths to handle autofill requests.

Name: kTrackingProtectionUserBypassPwaTrigger
Documentation: Triggers UserBypass logic for Progressive Web Apps on Android

Name: kWebAuthnNoAccountTimeout
Documentation:
Removes the timeout when downloading the account state for the enclave,
tweaking the UI:
* A loading screen is shown when the enclave is selected.
* The GPM error screen now has a "try another way" button.

Name: kApplyConstraintsRestartsVideoContentSources
Documentation:
If this feature is enabled, a call to applyConstraints() on a video content
source will make the source restart with the new format.

Name: kComputePressureBreakCalibrationMitigation
Documentation:
The features should be documented alongside the definition of their values
in the .cc file.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformUmaFromSqlDb
Documentation: Feature flag for using SQL database for UMA signals.

Name: kFedCmUseOtherAccountAndLabelsNewSyntax
Documentation:
Whether to support the newer syntax for the "Use Other Account"
and account labels features.

Name: kPlatformHEVCEncoderSupport
Documentation: Enables HEVC hardware accelerated encoding for Windows, Mac, and Android.

Name: kWebAssemblyTrapHandler
Documentation: Enable WebAssembly trap handler.

Name: kProtectedTabsAndroid
Documentation:
Put a higher memory priority to protected background tabs (e.g. tabs with
user edits in forms) to prevent them from being killed by LMKD before any
other non-protected tabs.

Name: kClayBackendConnectionV2
Documentation:
Enables the alternative behaviour for the connection to the default apps
choice internal backend in Android.

Name: kWaitForFirstPartySetsInit
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, the network service will wait until First-Party
Sets are initialized before issuing requests that use the HTTP cache or
cookies.

Name: kSplitCodeCacheByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Splits the generated code cache by the request's NetworkIsolationKey if one
is available. Note that this feature is also gated behind
`net::HttpCache::IsSplitCacheEnabled()`.

Name: kConversionMeasurement
Documentation: Note: "Conversion Measurement" is a legacy name for "Attribution Reporting"

Name: kUseWidgetSchedulerForIdlePeriodSignals
Documentation:
crbug.com/40785325 and crbug.com/378738907: If enabled, the signals used for
idle periods are requested via WidgetScheduler::Delegate instead of via
PageScheduler. This fixes a few issues where we might not get the requisite
RequestBeginMainFrameNotExpected signals from a BeginMainFrame source, but
are receiving BeginMainFrames, which can cause idle tasks to stop running.

Name: kMojoPredictiveAllocation
Documentation: Enables predictive allocation for Mojo serialization.

Name: kAutofillFixSplitCreditCardImport
Documentation:
If enabled, credit cards that are split into different fields are imported.
TODO: crbug.com/392179445 - Clean up when launched.

Name: kV8SingleThreadedGCInBackground
Documentation: Avoids background threads for GC if isolate is in background.

Name: kPlusAddressUserDidChooseEmailOverPlusAddressSurvey
Documentation: TODO: crbug.com/348139343 - Move back to components/plus_addresses.

Name: kDelayRequestsOnMultiplexedConnections
Documentation:
When kPriorityRequestsDelayableOnSlowConnections is enabled, HTTP
requests fetched from a SPDY/QUIC/H2 proxies can be delayed by the
ResourceScheduler just as HTTP/1.1 resources are. However, requests from such
servers are not subject to kMaxNumDelayableRequestsPerHostPerClient limit.

Name: kWebAuthnImmediateRequestRateLimit
Documentation: Enables rate limiting of immediate requests.

Name: kLoadingPredictorUseOptimizationGuide
Documentation:
Modifies loading predictor so that it can also use predictions coming from
the optimization guide.

Name: kWebAuthnICloudKeychainForInactiveWithoutDrive
Documentation: Not yet enabled by default.

Name: kReleaseResourceStrongReferencesOnMemoryPressure
Documentation:
Whether `blink::MemoryCache` and `blink::ResourceFetcher` release their
strong references to resources on memory pressure.

Name: kOidcAuthProfileManagement
Documentation: Controls whether OIDC-response profile management is enabled.

Name: kPrerender2WarmUpCompositor
Documentation:
Enables to warm up compositor on certain loading event of prerender initial
navigation. The feature `kWarmUpCompositor` in cc is required to enable this
feature. Please see crbug.com/41496019 for more details.

Name: kRetryGetVideoCaptureDeviceInfos
Documentation:
Enables retrying to obtain list of available cameras after restarting the
video capture service if a previous attempt failed, which could be caused
by a service crash.

Name: kFedCmShowFilteredAccounts
Documentation:
Enables showing filtered out accounts in FedCM UI after the user attempts to
login to an account. These accounts are shown greyed out.

Name: kEnableBookmarksSelectedTypeOnSigninForTesting
Documentation:
Normally, if kReplaceSyncPromosWithSignInPromos is disabled,
UserSelectableType::kBookmarks is disabled by default upon sign-in. This
flag makes the type enabled by default, for manual testing.

Name: kTaskPerMessage
Documentation:
Enables a task to be scheduled for each individual message dispatched to a
Mojo binding endpoint (or reply to an InterfacePtr).

When disabled, dispatch happens eagerly in batch, so when a binding is
scheduled to dispatch messages, it fully flushes and dispatches all queued
messages within the extent of a single scheduler task.

Enabling this feature allows for more fine-grained performance control
through the scheduler, but may initially cause some important edge cases to
regress in performance due to high-priority messages seeing increased
latency. Ideally we'd address these cases by giving the affected bindings
higher-priority TaskRunners.

Name: kUseTaskRunnerForMojoVEAService
Documentation:
Use TaskRunner for each MojoVideoEncodeAcceleratorService. Replaces
per-accelerator encoding task runner.

Name: kAutofillEnableAmountExtractionDesktopLogging
Documentation:
Enables logging of the result of checkout amount extraction on desktop.
This flag will allow amount extraction to run on any website when a CC
form is clicked. This flag should never be enabled.

Name: kEnableDiscountInfoApi
Documentation: Discount on navigation

Name: kMergeSubtypes
Documentation:
If enabled, merges the suggestion subtypes for the remote suggestions and the
local verbatim and history suggestion duplicates at the provider level. This
is needed for omnibox::kCategoricalSuggestions to function correctly but is
being controlled by a separate feature in case there are unintended side
effects beyond the categorical suggestions.

Name: kFetchGaiaHashOnSignIn
Documentation: Enables reading credentials from SharedPreferences.

Name: kLoadingPredictorTableConfig
Documentation: Configures the loading predictor table size and other base parameters.

Name: kAutofillAddressSuggestionsOnTyping
Documentation:
Feature flag to control displaying of Autofill suggestions on
unclassified fields based on prefix matching. These suggestions are displayed
after the user typed a certain number of characters that match some data
stored in the user's profile.
TODO(crbug.com/381994105): Cleanup when launched.

Name: kLocalNetworkAccessChecks
Documentation:
Enables Local Network Access checks.
Blocks local network requests without user permission to prevent exploitation
of vulnerable local devices.

This feature is being built as a replacement for Private Network Access
(PNA), and if this is on PNA features may stop working.

Public explainer:
https://github.com/explainers-by-googlers/local-network-access

Name: kAutofillDisableSuggestionStrikeDatabase
Documentation:
Kill switch for disabling suppressing suggestions based on the strike
database.

Name: kFledgeSellerWorkletThreadPool
Documentation: Enables multi-threaded seller worklet.

Name: kAutofillEnableAmountExtractionDesktop
Documentation:
When enabled, Chrome will extract the checkout amount from the checkout page
of the allowlisted merchant websites.

Name: kGlobalMediaControlsSeamlessTransfer
Documentation: Enable selection of audio output device in Global Media Controls.

Name: kEnableAccessibilityLanguageDetection
Documentation:
Use language detection to determine the language
of text content in page and exposed to the browser process AXTree.

Name: kPrefetchNIKScope
Documentation:
If enabled, navigational prefetch is scoped to the referring document's
network isolation key instead of the old behavior of the referring document
itself. See crbug.com/1502326

Name: kWebRtcLogCapturePipeline
Documentation: Whether we should log extra debug information to webrtc native log.

Name: kLensOverlaySimplifiedSelection
Documentation: Enables the Lens overlay simplified selection flow.

Name: kLensOverlayImageContextMenuActions
Documentation: Enables the Lens overlay image context menu actions.

Name: kServiceWorkerUpdateDelay
Documentation:
Experiment of the delay from navigation to starting an update of a service
worker's script.

Name: kWebAuthCableExtensionAnywhere
Documentation: Support the caBLE extension in assertion requests from any origin.

Name: kMerchantTrustEvaluationExperimentSurvey
Documentation:
Enables the 'Merchant trust' sentiment survey for experiment group. Used for
feature evaluation. The survey will be attempted to be shown on a new tab
when all the conditions apply. This should be set in the fieldtrial config
along with the trigger ID for the corresponding survey (as en_site_id) and
probability (as probability).

Name: kDesktopPWAsRunOnOsLogin
Documentation: Enables or disables Desktop PWAs to be auto-started on OS login.

Name: kAvoidForcedLayoutOnInitialEmptyDocumentInSubframe
Documentation:
When synchronousy loading the initial empty document, perform the layout
asynchronously.
TODO(http://crbug.com/324572951): Remove flag after Finch shows that this is
safe and has positive impact.

Name: kDirectCompositionUnlimitedOverlays
Documentation:
Do not consider hardware YUV overlay count when promoting quads to DComp
visuals. If there are more videos than hardware overlay planes, there may be
a performance hit compared to drawing all the videos into a single swap
chain. This feature is intended for testing and debugging.

Name: kWebAudioAllowDenormalInProcessing
Documentation:
Allow denormals in AudioWorklet and ScriptProcessorNode, to enable strict
JavaScript denormal compliance.  See https://crbug.com/382005099.

Name: kFledgeAndroidWorkletOffMainThread
Documentation: Makes FLEDGE worklets on Android not use the main thread for their mojo.

Name: kComposeInputParams
Documentation: Has flags for tweaking the valid sizes of input.

Name: kV8LazyFeedbackAllocation
Documentation: Enables lazy feedback allocation in V8.

Name: kCanvas2DHibernationReleaseTransferMemory
Documentation:
When hibernating, make sure that the just-used transfer memory (to transfer
the snapshot) is freed.

Name: kOmniboxTouchDownTriggerForPrefetch
Documentation:
Allows for touch down events to send a signal to |SearchPrefetchService| to
start prefetching the suggestion. The feature only applies to search
suggestions and only controls whether the signal is sent.

Name: kPreloadedDictionaryConditionalUse
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, preloaded dictionaries will not be used for
network requests if the binary has not yet been preloaded.

Name: kCanvas2DHibernation
Documentation:
Temporarily disabled due to issues:
- PDF blank previews
- Canvas corruption on ARM64 macOS
See https://g-issues.chromium.org/issues/328755781

Name: kAnnotatedPageContentExtraction
Documentation: Enables extraction of AnnotatedPageContent for every page load.

Name: kShowReadyToPayDebugInfo
Documentation:
If enabled, then Clank displays an alert dialog with the content of the
IS_READY_TO_PAY intent, whenever Clank fires this intent.

Name: kPrefetchFollowsNormalCacheSemantics
Documentation:
Prefetch to follow normal semantics instead of 5-minute rule
https://crbug.com/1345207

Name: kAndroidWarmUpSpareRendererWithTimeout
Documentation: Warm up a spare renderer after each navigation on Android.

Name: kGenericSensorExtraClasses
Documentation:
Enables an extra set of concrete sensors classes based on Generic Sensor API,
which expose previously unexposed platform features, e.g. ALS or Magnetometer

Name: kSyncSharedTabGroupAccountData
Documentation: Enables syncing account-local metadata for shared tab groups.

Name: kPostMessageThirdPartyToThirdPartyDifferentBucketSameOriginBlocked
Documentation:
Whether third-party to third-party different-bucket same-origin post messages
are blocked.

Name: kUseHardwareBufferUsageFlagsFromVulkan
Documentation:
Allows using recommended AHardwareBuffer usage from Vulkan, that should allow
drivers to pick most optimal layout.

Name: kPrivacySandboxFirstTimeNoticeV2
Documentation: If true, show the V2 of the Privacy Sandbox first time notice.

Name: kUkmFeature
Documentation: This feature controls whether UkmService should be created.

Name: kReclaimPrepaintTilesWhenIdle
Documentation:
When no frames are produced in a certain time interval, reclaim prepaint
tiles.

Name: kRichAutocompletion
Documentation:
If enabled, expands autocompletion to possibly (depending on params) include
suggestion titles and non-prefixes as opposed to be restricted to URL
prefixes. Will also adjust the location bar UI and omnibox text selection to
accommodate the autocompletions.

Name: kPrefetchProxy
Documentation: If explicitly disabled, prefetch proxy is not used.

Name: kAlwaysUpdateKAnon
Documentation: Please keep features in alphabetical order.

Name: kTouchTextEditingRedesign
Documentation:
Whether to enable new touch text editing features such as extra touch
selection gestures and quick menu options. Planning to release for ChromeOS
first, then possibly also enable some parts for other platforms later.
TODO(b/262297017): Clean up after touch text editing redesign ships.

Name: kAutofillVirtualViewStructureAndroid
Documentation:
Controls the whether the Chrome may provide a virtual view structure for
Android Autofill.
TODO: crbug.com/409579377 - Delete after M139.

Name: kTrackEmptyRendererProcessesForReuse
Documentation:
Controls whether the browser should track and reuse free and empty renderer
processes. When enabled, the browser maintains a list of renderer processes
that are currently not hosting any frames and are thus eligible for reuse
when a new renderer process is needed. Currently, only background renderer
processes are considered for reuse.

Name: kUsingCorrectWorkArea
Documentation:
Feature controlling how to compute work area on Android.
TODO(crbug.com/372385871): Cleanup flag after investigating nothing is broken
after changing the default behavior for
availWidth/availHeight/availTop/availLeft.

Name: kViewportProtection
Documentation: Enable blink viewport protection

Name: kSharedStorageCreateWorkletCustomDataOrigin
Documentation: For the Shared Storage API, allow custom data origins in `createWorklet`.

Name: kBookmarksTreeView
Documentation:
This is used to enable an experiment for the bookmarks tree view in the
side panel, providing users with a hierarchical view of their bookmarks.

Name: kTriggerNetworkDataMigration
Documentation:
Enables migration of the network context data from `unsandboxed_data_path` to
`data_path`. See the explanation in network_context.mojom.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformDeviceTier
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling device tier segment.

Name: kAutofillSharedAutofill
Documentation:
Controls whether Autofill may fill across origins.
In payment forms, the cardholder name field is often on the merchant's origin
while the credit card number and CVC are in iframes hosted by a payment
service provider. By enabling the policy-controlled feature "shared-autofill"
in those iframes, the merchant's website enable Autofill to fill the credit
card number and CVC fields from the cardholder name field, even though this
autofill operation crosses origins.
TODO(crbug.com/1304721): Enable this feature.

Name: kEnableVkPipelineCache
Documentation: Enable persistent storage of VkPipelineCache data.

Name: kAndroidDownloadableFontsMatching
Documentation:
Allows Blink to request fonts from the Android Downloadable Fonts API through
the service implemented on the Java side.

Name: kEnableGamepadMultitouch
Documentation: Enables gamepad multitouch

Name: kAutofillEnableFlatRateCardBenefitsFromCurinos
Documentation:
When enabled, flat rate card benefits sourced from Curinos will be shown in
Payments Autofill UI.

Name: kDocumentPolicyNegotiation
Documentation: Enable document policy negotiation mechanism.

Name: kOptimizationTargetPrediction
Documentation: Enables the prediction of optimization targets.

Name: kSelectFileOpenDocument
Documentation:
Use ACTION_OPEN_DOCUMENT rather than ACTION_GET_CONTENT when selecting a
file.

Name: kBundledSecuritySettings
Documentation: Enables Bundled Security Settings UI on chrome://settings/security

Name: kResolutionBasedDecoderPriority
Documentation:
Enables a platform-specific resolution cutoff for prioritizing platform
decoders over software decoders or vice-versa.

Name: kClaySnackbar
Documentation:
Enables showing a snackbar when users change their default search engine in
Android.

Name: kHistoryEmbeddingsAnswers
Documentation:
This feature specifies whether to answer queries using an answerer; it can be
considered a toggle for v2 answering functionality. Parameters are all kept
under the primary kHistoryEmbeddings feature. The kHistoryEmbeddingsAnswers
feature state is not applicable if kHistoryEmbeddings is disabled.
Note: This feature has no parameters. Since it entirely depends on the
above kHistoryEmbeddings feature, all parameters are owned by that
feature to avoid confusion about which feature owns which parameters.

Name: kAudioInputConfirmReadsViaShmem
Documentation:
Enables an optimization where audio input stream read confirmations are
written to shared memory instead of being sent through socket messages.

Name: kZeroSuggestPrefetchingOnWeb
Documentation:
Enables prefetching of the zero prefix suggestions for eligible users on the
Web (i.e. non-NTP and non-SRP URLs).

Name: kLensOverlayUploadChunking
Documentation: Enables uploading chunking for the Lens overlay.

Name: kSegmentationDefaultReportingSegments
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling default reporting segments.

Name: kHardwareSecureDecryptionExperiment
Documentation:
Same as `kHardwareSecureDecryption` above, but only enable experimental
sub key systems. Which sub key system is experimental is key system specific.

Name: kOptimizationGuideFetchingForSRP
Documentation:
Killswitch for fetching on search results from a remote Optimization Guide
Service.

Name: kEnableComposeWebUIAnimations
Documentation: Controls whether or not the Compose WebUI dialog has animations.

Name: kUIDebugToolsEnableSyntheticEvents
Documentation:
Enables UI debugging tools to send synthetic events.
This is used by the telemetry benchmarking tools only.

Name: kExternalClearKeyForTesting
Documentation:
Enables support for External Clear Key (ECK) key system for testing on
supported platforms. On platforms that do not support ECK, this feature has
no effect.

Name: kReportingStorageDegradationFeature
Documentation:
Temporary: enable/disable Storage degradation.
When enabled: If there is no disk space available at the time of writing a
new record then the storage queue will try to shed files sequentially from
lowest to highest priority.

Name: kAutofillImproveAddressFieldSwapping
Documentation:
When enabled, address field swapping suggestions will not include a
suggestion matching the field's current value. This decreases noises in the
suggestion UI.
TODO(crbug.com/381531027): Remove when launched.

Name: kUseFakeChromeML
Documentation: Whether the fake implementation is used in the OnDeviceModelService.

Name: kV8FlushBytecode
Documentation: Enables flushing of JS bytecode in V8.

Name: kCompressionDictionaryTransportBackend
Documentation:
Enables the backend of the compression dictionary transport feature.
When this feature is enabled, the following will happen:
  * The network service loads the metadata database.
  * If there is a matching dictionary for a sending request, it adds the
    `sec-available-dictionary` header.
  * And if the `content-encoding` header of the response is `dcb`, it
    decompresses the response body using the dictionary.

Name: kFledgePrepareSellerContextsInAdvance
Documentation:
Prepare seller contexts, including running top level scripts, before
we're ready to score a worklet's first ad.

Name: kAutofillEnableBuyNowPayLater
Documentation: When enabled, buy now pay later (BNPL) in Autofill will be offered.

Name: kQuoteEmptySecChUaStringHeadersConsistently
Documentation:
Whether Sec-CH-UA headers on subresource fetches that contain an empty
string should be quoted (`""`) as they are for navigation fetches. See
https://crbug.com/1416925.

Name: kFledgeStartAnticipatoryProcesses
Documentation:
Enables starting worklet processes at auction start time in anticipation
of needing them for future worklets.

Name: kStylusRichGestures
Documentation: Stylus gestures for editable web content.

Name: kAsyncMultiPortPath
Documentation: A flag to make multiport context creation asynchronous.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformLowEngagementFeature
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling low engagement segmentation key.

Name: kDataSharingJoinOnly
Documentation:
Join only feature flag for data sharing. Enabled partial data sharing related
functionalities.

Name: kTrackingProtectionUserBypassPwa
Documentation: Enables UserBypass logic for Progressive Web Apps on Android

Name: kWebOTP
Documentation:
This is intended as a kill switch for the WebOTP Service feature. To enable
this feature, the experimental web platform features flag should be set.

Name: kFledgeSampleDebugReports
Documentation:
Run sampling of forDebuggingOnly reports and let generateBid() and scoreAd()
know fDO's lockout/cooldown status through their browser signals, to allow
ad techs experimenting with and adapting to the algorithm.
But whether sending all or only sampled forDebuggingOnly reports depends on
flag kFledgeEnableFilteringDebugReportStartingFrom.

Name: kElasticOverscroll
Documentation: Cached in Java as well, make sure defaults are updated together.

Name: kUseFirstCoalescedFrameAsFlingGenerationTimestamp
Documentation: Flag guard for fix for crbug.com/404464598.

Name: kBuiltInHlsPlayer
Documentation:
This feature enables chrome's built-in HLS parser and demuxer instead of
Android's MediaPlayer based implementation. When this feature is enabled,
the media-player based HLS player will NOT be used. This will roll out first
on android, but will eventually land in desktop chrome as well.

Name: kComposeGraduated
Documentation:
Features that determine when a feature has graduated from experimental. These
should not be enabled at the same time as their respective settings
visibility features.

Name: kSkipSendingFeedbackReportInTastTests
Documentation: Disables dispatching reports in Tast tests.

Name: kGWSPrefetchHoldback
Documentation: Preconnects instead of prefetching from GWS.

Name: kReaderModeAutoDistill
Documentation: Feature declarations below -- alphabetical order.

Name: kSupervisedUserBlockInterstitialV3
Documentation: Whether supervised users see an updated URL filter interstitial.

Name: kUserMediaScreenCapturing
Documentation:
Screen Capture API support for Android.
This should not be enabled unless ENABLE_SCREEN_CAPTURE is on, otherwise
it won't work.

Name: kScrollBubblingFix
Documentation: Flag guard for fix for crbug.com/346629231.

Name: kAutoSpeculationRules
Documentation: https://crbug.com/1472970

Name: kAutofillFixFormTracking
Documentation:
Removes logic that resets form submission tracking data upon receiving a
FORM_SUBMISSION or PROBABLE_FORM_SUBMISSION signal. Also, fixes submission
deduplication so that it ignores submissions that PWM doesn't act upon.
TODO(crbug.com/40281981): Remove when launched.

Name: kLoadingTasksUnfreezable
Documentation:
Makes network loading tasks unfreezable so that they can be processed while
the page is frozen.

Name: kWebviewAccelerateSmallCanvases
Documentation: Enables small accelerated canvases for webview (crbug.com/1004304)

Name: kEnterpriseFileSystemAccessDeepScan
Documentation:
Adds support for enterprise deep scans initiated through the file system
access API.

Name: kEnableProbabilisticRevealTokens
Documentation: Enables the Probabilistic Reveal Tokens feature.

Name: kNtpOutlookCalendarModule
Documentation: If enabled, outlook calendar module will be shown.

Name: kAllowMultipleOriginsForWebKioskPermissions
Documentation:
When enabled, use the value of the `allowlist_urls` FeatureParam as the
list of origins which would be allowed to access browser permission and
device attribute API for a web kiosk session.

Name: kFastPathNoRaster
Documentation:
Adds a fast path to avoid waking up the thread pool when there are no raster
tasks.

Name: kAutoDisableAccessibility
Documentation:
Disable the accessibility engine after a certain
number of user input events spanning a minimum amount of time with no
accessibility API usage in that time.

Name: kNewEvSignalsUnaffiliatedEnabled
Documentation:
Feature flag for supporting the new private SecureConnect functions in
unaffiliated contexts via the consent flow.

Name: kAutofillDetectRemovedFormControls
Documentation:
If enabled, whenever form controls are removed from the DOM, the ChromeClient
is informed about this. This enables Autofill to trigger a reparsing of
forms.

Name: kReportingApiEnableEnterpriseCookieIssues
Documentation:
Enables enterprises to use the Reporting API to collect 3PCD-related
issues from sites used in their organization.

Name: kSystemCursorSizeSupported
Documentation:
When enabled, the feature will query the OS for a default cursor size,
to be used in determining the concrete object size of a custom cursor in
blink. Currently enabled by default on Windows only.
TODO(crbug.com/40845719) - Implement for other platforms.

Name: kAutofillAiCreateEntityDataManager
Documentation:
Kill switch. If enabled, the EntityDataManager is created irrespective of
whether other features are enabled. This is necessary so that cleaning up the
browsing data also removes data if the user left the study.

Name: kWebAudioRemoveAudioDestinationResampler
Documentation:
This feature flag controls whether the WebAudio destination resampler is
bypassed. When enabled, if the WebAudio context's sample rate differs from
the hardware's sample rate, the resampling step that normally occurs within
the WebAudio destination node is skipped. This allows the AudioService to
handle any necessary resampling, potentially reducing latency and overhead.

Name: kAutofillFixFieldsAssociatedWithNestedFormsByParser
Documentation:
If enabled, WebFormElement applies the same special case to nested forms
as it does for the outermost form. The fix is relevant only to Autofill.
For other callers of HTMLFormElement::ListedElements(), which don't traverse
shadow trees and flatten nested forms, are not affected by the feature at
all. This is a kill switch.

Name: kEnterpriseManagementDisclaimerUsesCustomLabel
Documentation:
Enables showing the EnterpriseCustomLabel` instead of the cloud policy
manager in the managed disclaimer "Managed by..." in the profile and app
menus.

Name: kOidcEnrollmentAuthSource
Documentation:
Controls whether to add a list of hosts that are eligible for OIDC profile
enrollments.

Name: kHashPrefixRealTimeLookups
Documentation:
Sends hash-prefix real-time lookup requests on navigations for Standard Safe
Browsing users instead of hash-prefix database lookups.

Name: kFledgeUseNonTransientNIKForSeller
Documentation: Enables a non-transient NIK for trusted selling signals.

Name: kPrefetchNewLimits
Documentation:
Does not enable any new behaviour; is only used to parameterize prefetch
limit values (see content/browser/preloading/prefetch/prefetch_params.cc).

Name: kAutofillEnableCvcStorageAndFillingStandaloneFormEnhancement
Documentation:
When enabled, this will enhance the CVV storage project. The enhancement will
enable CVV storage suggestions for standalone CVC fields.

Name: kAutofillSharedStorageServerCardData
Documentation: If enabled, we will store autofill server card data in shared storage.

Name: kNavigationPredictorPreconnectHoldback
Documentation:
All features in alphabetical order. The features should be documented
alongside the definition of their values in the .cc file.

Name: kDnsOverHttpsUpgrade
Documentation: Enable usage of hardcoded DoH upgrade mapping for use in automatic mode.

Name: kOmniboxAssistantVoiceSearch
Documentation:
Omnibox UI - these affect the UI or function of the location bar (not the
popup).

Name: kFedCm
Documentation:
Enables JavaScript API to intermediate federated identity requests.
Note that actual exposure of the FedCM API to web content is controlled
by the flag in RuntimeEnabledFeatures on the blink side. See also
the use of kSetOnlyIfOverridden in content/child/runtime_features.cc.
We enable it here by default to support use in origin trials.

Name: kAndroidWebAppLaunchHandler
Documentation: A feature to enable launch handler and file handler api for Chrome on Android

Name: kAllowDatapipeDrainedAsBytesConsumerInBFCache
Documentation:
Feature for allowing page into back/forward cache when datapipe has been
drained as bytes consumer for fetch requests.

Name: kWebAuthnSkipHybridConfigIfSystemSupported
Documentation:
When enabled, skips configuring hybrid when Windows can do hybrid. Hybrid may
still be delegated to Windows regardless of this flag.

Name: kAudioServiceOutOfProcess
Documentation: Runs the audio service in a separate process.

Name: kComposeSettingsVisibility
Documentation:
Features that control the visibility of whether a feature setting is visible
to the user. Should only be enabled for experimental features that have not
graduated yet.

Name: kWebXr
Documentation: Controls whether the WebXR Device API is enabled.

Name: kSkipCheckForAccountManagementOnSignin
Documentation:
Feature to bypass double-checking that signin callers have correctly gotten
the user to accept account management. This check is slow and not strictly
necessary, so disable it while we work on adding caching.
TODO(https://crbug.com/339457762): Restore the check when we implement
caching.

Name: kDownloadServiceForegroundSessionIOSFeature
Documentation:
Enable download service to download in foreground.
TODO(crbug.com/40190949): This is for iOS only and temporary fix to
circumvent issues with background downloads reported as crashes.

Name: kUseWindowBoundsForPip
Documentation:
Safety switch to allow us to revert to the previous behavior of using the

Name: kTransportSecurityFileWriterSchedule

Documentation: Enables using quiet prompts for notification permission requests.

Name: kPartitionAllocSortActiveSlotSpans

Name: kAiSettingsPageEnterpriseDisabledUi

Name: kReduceGpuPriorityOnBackground
Documentation:
Reduce the priority of GPU process when in background so it is more likely
to be killed first if the OS needs more memory.

Name: kAccessibilityIncludeLongClickAction
Documentation:
When enabled, includes the ACTION_LONG_CLICK action to all relevant nodes in

Reuses RenderProcessHost up to a certain threshold. This mode ignores the

sites, with an additional restriction that a process may only be reused while

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessPreflightShortTimeout

Reduce PNA preflight response waiting time to 200ms.
See: https://wicg.github.io/private-network-access/#cors-preflight

Name: kReduceTransferSizeUpdatedIPC
Documentation:
This feature will reduce TransferSizeUpdated IPC from the network service.
When enabled, the network service will send the IPC only when DevTools is
attached or the request is for an ad request.

Name: kPrefetchScheduler
Documentation:
Replace current prefetch queue with a new queue and scheduler, which allows

For more details, see
https://docs.google.com/document/d/1W0Nk3Nq6NaUXkBppOUC5zyNmhVqMjYShm1bydGYd9qc

Name: kChromeStructuredMetrics
Documentation: Controls the enablement of structured metrics on Windows, Linux, and Mac.

Name: kUseSequencedTaskRunnerForMediaService
Documentation: Use SequencedTaskRunner for MediaService.

Name: kPartitionProxyChains
Documentation:
When enabled, all proxies in a proxy chain are partitioned by the NAK for the
endpoint of the connection. When disabled, proxies carrying tunnels to other
proxies (i.e., all proxies but the last one in the ProxyChain) are not

Name: kShortLaxAllowUnsafeThreshold
Documentation:
When enabled, the time threshold for Lax-allow-unsafe cookies will be lowered
from 2 minutes to 10 seconds. This time threshold refers to the age cutoff
for which cookies that default into SameSite=Lax, which are newer than the
threshold, will be sent with any top-level cross-site navigation regardless
of HTTP method (i.e. allowing unsafe methods). This is a convenience for
integration tests which may want to test behavior of cookies older than the
threshold, but which would not be practical to run for 2 minutes.

Name: kIsolatedWebAppUnmanagedInstall
Documentation: Enables users on unmanaged devices to install Isolated Web Apps.

Name: kAllowJITInstallationWhenAppIconIsMissing
Documentation: Used to test icon refetch for JIT installed apps with missing icons.

Name: kNetworkQualityEstimator
Documentation:
Enables optimizing the network quality estimation algorithms in network
quality estimator (NQE).

Name: kDefaultAllowPrivacySandboxAttestations
Documentation:
Enable the Privacy Sandbox Attestations to default allow when the
attestations map is absent.

Name: kInternalServerSideSpeechRecognition
Documentation: TODO(b/288273641): Clean up the server speech recognition related flags.

Name: kSearchesFindUngroupedVisits
Documentation:
Enables Side Panel Grouped History and WebUI Grouped History to find
ungrouped visits as well when the user has typed a search query.

Name: kOptimizationGuideComposeOnDeviceEval
Documentation:
Whether to allow on device model evaluation for Compose. This has no effect
if OptimizationGuideOnDeviceModel is off.

Name: kWebRtcEncodedTransformDirectCallback
Documentation:
When performing Encoded Transform in-process transfer optimization, set the
encoded_audio_transformer_'s transform callback to directly call the new
underlying source rather than bouncing via the RTCRtpSender or
RTCRtpReceiver.

Name: kEnableFingerprintingProtectionFilter
Documentation: The primary toggle to enable/disable the Fingerprinting Protection Filter.

Name: kWebRtcAllowH265Send
Documentation:
When enabled, allow H.265 codec to be used for sending WebRTC streams.
Platform hardware H.265 encoder needs to be supported and enabled in order to
negotiate usage of H.265 in SDP in the direction of sending.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformTipsEphemeralCard
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling the Tips Ephemeral Card.

Name: kEnableADPFRendererMain
Documentation:
If enabled, Chrome includes the Renderer Main thread(s) into the
ADPF(Android Dynamic Performance Framework) hint session.
see https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/e7507d15614ac7f499fb89086b3a09772fa8deb4

Name: kReportingApiCorsOriginHeader
Documentation:
Enables sending the CORS Origin header on the POST request for Reporting API
report uploads.

Name: kPasswordManualFallbackAvailable
Documentation: Enables triggering password suggestions through the context menu.

Name: kUsePollForMessagePumpEpoll
Documentation:
Use poll() rather than epoll().

Why? epoll() is supposed to be strictly better. But it has one consequence
we don't necessarily want: when writing to a AF_UNIX socket, the kernel
will wake up the waiter with a "sync" wakeup. The concept of a "sync"
wakeup has various consequences, but on Android it tends to bias the
scheduler towards a "baton passing" mode, where the current thread yields
its CPU to the target. This is desirable to lower latency.

However, when using epoll_wait(), the "sync" flag is dropped from the
wakeup path. This is not the case with poll(). So let's use it to preserve
this behavior.

Caveat: Since both we and the kernel need to walk the list of all fds at
every call, don't do it when we have too many FDs.

Name: kImageDescriptionsAlternateRouting
Documentation: Use Alternative mechanism for acquiring image descriptions.

Name: kBackgroundNotPerceptibleBinding
Documentation: Enable not perceptible binding without cpu priority boosting.

Name: kFledgeOnlyUseIpAddressSpaceInClientSecurityState
Documentation:
When enabled, Protected Audience fetches (scripts, signals, and updates) use
ClientSecurityStates that only contain the IPAddressSpace of the frame
running the auction, to prevent leaks.

Name: kClipboardChangeEvent
Documentation:
Enable ClipboardChange event API
https://chromestatus.com/feature/5085102657503232

Name: kAutofillEnableCardBenefitsIph
Documentation: When enabled, card benefits IPH will be shown in Payments Autofill UI.

Name: kWebFeedKillSwitch
Documentation: Kill-switch for the web feed feature.

Name: kCastStreamingAv1
Documentation:
NOTE: callers should always use the free functions in
/media/cast/encoding/encoding_support.h instead of accessing these features
directly.
TODO(https://crbug.com/1453388): Guard Cast Sender flags with !IS_ANDROID.

Name: kWebRtcUseCaptureBeginTimestamp
Documentation:
Feature flag for making use of VideoFrameMetadata::capture_begin_time
if set, instead of relating incoming media timestamps to local time in the
WebRTC track source.

Name: kV8Maglev
Documentation:
Enables Maglev compiler. Note that this only sets the V8 flag when
manually overridden; otherwise it defers to whatever the V8 default is.

Name: kLeftHandSideActivityIndicators
Documentation: Move activity indicators to the left-hand side of Omnibox.

Name: kSyncSimulateBookmarksPingPongForTesting
Documentation:
Test-only flag to simulate a ping-pong behavior for bookmarks: two clients
sync-ing to the same account, using a different value for this flag, will
produce an active ping-pong, where one of them will try to clear the

Name: kAutofillEnableOffersInClankKeyboardAccessory
Documentation:
When enabled, offers will be displayed in the Clank keyboard accessory during
downstream.

Name: kComposeInnerText
Documentation: Enables/disables inner text context gathering.

Name: kBackForwardCacheNoTimeEviction
Documentation:
Removes the time limit for cached content. This is used on bots to identify
accidentally passing tests.

Name: kAddDelayToGLCompileShader
Documentation:
Add a small delay in shader compiling if validating command decoder is used.
This is to verify if passthrough command decoder impacting negatively top
level metrics could be due to slower shader compiling.

Name: kLazyUpdateTranslateModel
Documentation:
If enabled, we lazily initiate `TranslateAgent` in
`ChromeRenderFrameObserver` (crbug/361215212).

Name: kEyeDropper
Documentation: Used to enable the eye-dropper in the refresh color-picker.

Name: kAutofillEnableAllowlistForBmoCardCategoryBenefits
Documentation:
When enabled, card category benefits offered by BMO will be shown in Autofill
suggestions on the allowlisted merchant websites.

Name: kMediaDrmPreprovisioning
Documentation:
Enables MediaDrmOriginIdManager to provide preprovisioned origin IDs for
MediaDrmBridge. If disabled, MediaDrmBridge will get unprovisioned origin IDs
which will trigger provisioning process after MediaDrmBridge is created.

Name: kAutofillImproveCityFieldClassification
Documentation:
When enabled, new `negative_pattern` regex values will be used
in order to reduce false positive classifications of city fields.
TODO(crbug.com/330508437): Clean up when launched.

Name: kEducationalTipModule
Documentation:
Feature flag for enabling the Educational tip module in the home modules on
chrome android.

Name: kSystemKeyboardLock
Documentation: Allows system keyboard event capture via the keyboard lock API.

Name: kAndroidExtendedKeyboardShortcuts
Documentation: Extended physical keyboard shortcuts for Android.

Name: kMojoDedicatedThread
Documentation:
If enabled Mojo uses a dedicated background thread to listen for incoming
IPCs. Otherwise it's configured to use Content's IO thread for that purpose.

Name: kThreadedPreloadScanner
Documentation: If enabled, the HTMLPreloadScanner will run on a worker thread.

Name: kAutofillEnableVcn3dsAuthentication
Documentation:
When enabled, Chrome will trigger 3DS authentication during a virtual card
retrieval if a challenge is required, 3DS authentication is available for
the card, and FIDO is not.

Name: kAdpf
Documentation:
If enabled, Chrome uses ADPF(Android Dynamic Performance Framework) if the
device's SOC manufacturer satisifes the allowlist and blocklist rules.
If disabled, Chrome never uses ADPF.
The allowlist takes precedence - i.e. if the allowlist is non-empty, the
soc must be in the allowlist for Chrome to use ADPF, and the blocklist is
ignored. If there's no allowlist, the soc must be absent from the blocklist.

Name: kNtpTabResumptionModuleTimeLimit
Documentation: Dummy feature to set how recent tabs must be to be shown.

Name: kRestrictRendererPoliciesInBaseline
Documentation:
When enabled, this features restricts a set of syscalls in
BaselinePolicyAndroid that are used by RendererProcessPolicy.

Name: kPrefetchStateContaminationMitigation
Documentation:
If enabled, then prefetch serving will apply mitigations if it may have been
contaminated by cross-partition state.

Name: kContextualPageActionShareModel
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling reader mode action feature.

Name: kSearchEnginePreconnectInterval
Documentation: Changes the interval between two search engine preconnect attempts.

Name: kUsePageViewportInLCP
Documentation:
Uses page viewport instead of frame viewport in the Largest Contentful Paint
heuristic where images occupying the full viewport are ignored.

Name: kUseExtensionListForPSLMatching
Documentation:
Improves PSL matching capabilities by utilizing PSL-extension list from
affiliation service. It fixes problem with incorrect password suggestions on
websites like slack.com.

Name: kAutofillUnmaskCardRequestTimeout
Documentation: When enabled, adds a timeout on the network request for Unmask requests.

Name: kV8TurboshaftInstructionSelection
Documentation: Enable running instruction selection on Turboshaft IR directly.

Name: kOidcAuthResponseInterception
Documentation:
Controls whether OIDC profile enrollment can be started from navigation
response in addition to redirections.

Name: kProcessBoundStringEncryption
Documentation: Enable encryption for process bound strings, if supported by the platform.

Name: kIPv6Probing
Documentation: Enable IPv6 ping probes to RIPE DNS.

Name: kLazyInitializeMediaControls
Documentation: Enable lazy initialization of the media controls.

Name: kEnableSchemeBoundCookies
Documentation:
Enables binding of cookies to the scheme that originally set them. Also
enables domain cookie shadowing protection.

Name: kNetworkContextPrefetch
Documentation:
To actually use the prefetch results, it's also necessary to enable
kNetworkContextPrefetchUseCache, below.

Name: kUrgentMainFrameForInput
Documentation:
When BeginMainFrame() is throttled, whether input-related BeginMainFrame()s
are marked urgent, and thus unthtrottled.

Name: kPopularSitesBakedInContentFeature
Documentation:
This feature is enabled by default. Otherwise, users who need it would not
get the right configuration timely enough. The configuration affects only
Android or iOS users.

Name: kNtpDriveModuleSegmentation
Documentation:
If enabled, segmentation data will be collected to decide whether or not to
show the Drive module.

Name: kReduceAcceptLanguage
Documentation:
Enables support for the `Variants` response header and reduce
accept-language. https://github.com/Tanych/accept-language

Name: kTrackingProtectionContentSettingFor3pcb
Documentation: Enables TRACKING_PROTECTION content settings to control 3pcb.

Name: kWebPermissionsApi
Documentation:
Enable the navigator.permissions API.
Used for launch in WebView, but exposed in content to map to runtime-enabled
feature.

Name: kIncognitoFileSystemContextForTesting
Documentation:
Creates FileSystemContexts in incognito mode. This is used to run web tests
in incognito mode to ensure feature parity for FileSystemAccessAccessHandles.

Name: kFledgeCacheKAnonHashedKeys
Documentation:
Enables a cache of k-anon keys and whether or not each is k-anonymous,
written when keys are received these from queries to the k-anonymity server,
and used in subsequent key fetches to reduce unnecessary load on the
k-anonymity server. This is similar to the refresh behavior managed by the
KAnonymityServiceQueryInterval parameter, except that refresh loses keys
when ads are removed and then added back to an interest group in joins and
updates, whereas the k-anon key cache controlled by this feature retains keys
until the TTL, provided the `kFledgeCacheKAnonHashedKeysTtl` parameter below.

Name: kPreloadingViewportHeuristics
Documentation:
If enabled, a viewport based heuristic will be used to predict the next click
for speculation-rule based preloading.
Note: To work correctly, this also needs kNavigationPredictor enabled with
"random_anchor_sampling_period" set to 1, and
kNavigationPredictorNewViewportFeatures.
Note: The prediction will only be preloaded if the "enact_candidates" param
is set to true (false by default), otherwise it is only logged for metrics
purposes.

Name: kFrameRoutingCache
Documentation:
Whether to use the Frame Routing Cache to avoid synchronous IPCs from the
renderer side for iframe creation.

Name: kLegacyParsingOfXContentTypeOptions
Documentation:
Kill-switch for new parsing behaviour of the X-Content-Type-Options header.
(Should be removed after the new behaviour has been launched.)

Name: kWebOtpBackendAuto
Documentation:
Controls which backend is used to retrieve OTP on Android. When disabled
we use User Consent API.

Name: kNoAESHardwareMessage
Documentation: Show a warning message to user if aes hardware is not found

Name: kProcessReuseOnPrerenderCOOPSwap
Documentation:
When enabled, try to reuse an unlocked renderer process when COOP swap is
happening on prerender initial navigation. Please see crbug.com/41492112 for
more details.

Name: kUsePopularSitesSuggestions
Documentation: If this feature is enabled, we enable popular sites in the suggestions UI.

Name: kDocumentProvider
Documentation: Document provider and domain suggestions

Name: kEnableSearchAggregatorPolicy
Documentation: Enterprise search aggregators features.

Name: kTimerSlackMac
Documentation:
Under this feature, slack is added on mac message pumps that support it when
allowed per DelayPolicy.

Name: kClearUserDataUponProfileDestruction
Documentation: Killswitch that guards clearing all user data in the ProfileImpl destructor.

Name: kMessagesCloseButton
Documentation: Feature that enables a close button when mouses hovers over.

Name: kSuppressesSearchPrefetchOnSlowNetwork
Documentation: If enabled, suppresses SearchPrefetch (https://crbug.com/350519234)

Name: kDocumentProviderEnterpriseEligibilityWhenUnknown
Documentation:
If enabled, the enterprise eligibility requirement for Drive suggestions
is considered met even when the account capability is unknown. Has no effect
if kDocumentProviderEnterpriseEligibility is disabled.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformIosModuleRanker
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling ios module ranker.

Name: kCapReferrerToOriginOnCrossOrigin
Documentation:
When kCapReferrerToOriginOnCrossOrigin is enabled, HTTP referrers on cross-
